logy company that has been revolutionizing time management for years, offering advanced tools for productivity monitoring, project management, invoicing, and profitability analysis. With flexible pricing plans that cater to the needs of various organizations - from startups to large enterprises, our client enables its users to maximize work efficiency. Gaining the trust of over 18,000 teams worldwide, our client is constantly looking for talents ready to join their dynamically growing community. We are seeking individuals from various fields, such as programming, sales, project management, or marketing, who want to co-create the future of work time management. Join us and help shape the future of efficient teamwork, taking advantage of the opportunity to integrate with over 100 applications. This position offers not only the possibility of professional development but also the chance to impact the productivity and success of organizations around the globe.</p> React Developer with knowledge of C++ <p><strong>We offer:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Attractive salary</li>\n<li>Remote work possibility</li>\n<li>Medical package, sports package, training budget</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Developing and maintaining desktop applications in Electron with React/C++.</li>\n<li>Additionally, includes the development of native C++ applications using wxWidgets.</li>\n<li>Integrating applications with external systems.</li>\n<li>Collaborating with a team using Agile/Scrum methodologies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 3-4 years of experience in creating React applications</li>\n<li>Knowledge of Electron API (IPC, native modules, security)</li>\n<li>Minimum 1-2 years of experience in C++ programming</li>\n<li>Familiarity with C++ standards</li>\n<li>Ability and willingness to program with AI support</li>\n<li>Knowledge of cross-platform development</li>\n<li>Proficient in English - communicative level</li>\n<li>Proficient in Polish - fluent level</li>\n<li>Ability to work in a team</li>\n<li>Independence and proactivity</li>\n<li>Willingness for continuous development and learning of new technologies</li>\n<li>Analytical thinking and problem-solving</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Additional advantages:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Experience with wxWidgets/QT library is a big plus</li></ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(313,6829,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Job description<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Our client is a rapidly growing company specializing in digital business transformation, with over 10 years of market experience and more than 100 successfully completed projects. It offers comprehensive solutions that combine advisory, engineering, and managerial competencies, cooperating with clients from Poland and other European countries. The company is engaged in social initiatives such as tree planting and supporting children\'s theater, demonstrating its strong values and social responsibility. It is looking for ambitious employees who want to develop their skills and work in a team of experts, offering development opportunities in areas such as observability, cybersecurity, user experience, business analytics, and resource management. The company is open to new technological partnerships and encourages contact with cooperation proposals, offering a dynamic and supportive work environment.</p> APM/Observability Engineer - Presales <p><strong>We offer:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>attractive salary (base + bonus)</li>\n<li>real opportunity for professional development</li>\n<li>participation in interesting projects</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>code and architecture analysis of the application for performance and availability improvement;</li>\n<li>designing and implementing monitoring based on the Observability Dynatrace platform;</li>\n<li>integration and automation of monitoring within CI/CD, including quality gates;</li>\n<li>designing and implementing SRE;</li>\n<li>collaboration with DevOps teams of our Clients;</li>\n<li>sales support, solution presentation, and Proof of Concept implementation;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>knowledge of popular technologies and mechanisms not built in, e.g., JAVA, CLR, GC, JDBC/ODBC, Interface, FPM, WCF, http Client, http server</li>\n<li>understanding of popular standards and protocols: TCP/IP, Connection Pools, Thread Pools, SSL Certificates, Messaging Queue, In/Out Buffer, Proxy/LB, StickySession</li>\n<li>ability to read code and documentation in a way that enables performance analysis and identification of bottlenecks;</li>\n<li>familiarity with Kubernetes in the area of application deployment and basic administration (Helm charts are a plus);</li>\n<li>experience in building CI/CD pipelines using tools like Jenkins, GitLab, CircleCI, ArgoCD, Azure DevOps, GitHub Actions;</li>\n<li>communicative knowledge of the English language</li>\n<li>interpersonal skills enabling teamwork and building long-term relationships with clients</li>\n<li>ability to conduct presentations using MS PowerPoint and live product demonstrations will be an additional asset</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Additional advantages:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>programming skills in at least one of the languages: JAVA, .NET (including knowledge of design patterns); familiarity with PHP, Node.js, or Go will be an additional asset;</li>\n<li>experience in building/managing applications in public clouds AWS, Azure, GCP, especially for EKS, AKS, GKE, and serverless;</li>\n<li>experience with monitoring tools: Application Performance Monitoring, Infra, NPMD;</li>\n<li>experience in memory dump and thread dump analysis.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(314,6830,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Opis stanowiska<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Nasz klient to dynamicznie rozwijająca się firma specjalizująca się w cyfrowej transformacji biznesu, z ponad 10-letnim doświadczeniem na rynku i ponad 100 zrealizowanymi projektami. Oferuje kompleksowe rozwiązania łączące kompetencje doradcze, inżynierskie i managerskie, współpracując z klientami zarówno z Polski, jak i z innych krajów europejskich. Firma jest zaangażowana w inicjatywy społeczne, takie jak sadzenie drzew czy wsparcie teatru dla dzieci, pokazując swoje silne wartości i odpowiedzialność społeczną. Poszukuje ambitnych pracowników, którzy chcą rozwijać swoje kompetencje i pracować w zespole ekspertów, oferując możliwości rozwoju w obszarach takich jak obserwowalność, cyberbezpieczeństwo, user experience, analityka biznesowa oraz zarządzanie zasobami. Firma jest otwarta na nowe partnerstwa technologiczne i zachęca do kontaktu z propozycjami współpracy, oferując dynamiczne i wsparcie środowisko pracy.</p> APM/Observability Engineer (Inżynier Presales) <p><strong>Oferujemy:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>atrakcyjne wynagrodzenie (podstawa + premia_</li>\n<li>realna możliwość rozwoju zawodowego</li>\n<li>udział w ciekawych projektach</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Obowiązki:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>analiza kodu i architektury aplikacji pod kątem poprawy wydajności i dostępności;</li>\n<li>projektowanie i implementacja monitoringu w oparciu o platformę Observability Dynatrace;</li>\n<li>integracja i automatyzacja monitoringu w ramach CI/CD, w tym bramy jakości;</li>\n<li>projektowanie i implementacja SRE;</li>\n<li>współpraca z zespołami DevOps naszych Klientów;</li>\n<li>wsparcie sprzedaży, prezentacja rozwiązań i realizacja Proof of Concept;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Wymagania:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>znajomość popularnych technologii oraz mechanizmów w nie wbudowanych np.: JAVA, CLR, GC, JDBC/ODBC, Interface, FPM, WCF, http Client, http server</li>\n<li>wiedza w zakresie działania popularnych standardów oraz protokołów: TCP/IP, Pule Połączeń, Pule wątków, Certyfikaty SSL, Messaging Queue, In/Out bufor, Proxy/LB, StickySession</li>\n<li>umiejętność czytania kodu oraz dokumentacji w sposób umożliwiający analizę wydajności oraz potencjałów wąskich gardeł;</li>\n<li>znajomość Kubernetes w obszarze uruchamiania aplikacji oraz podstawowej administracji (Helm charts mile widziany);</li>\n<li>doświadczenie w budowaniu pipeline\'ow CI/CD z wykorzystaniem narzędzi takich jak Jenkins, GitLab, CircleCI, ArgoCD, Azure DevOps, GitHub Actions;</li>\n<li>komunikatywna znajomość języka angielskiego</li>\n<li>umiejętności interpersonalne pozwalające na pracę w zespole oraz budowanie długofalowych relacji z klientami</li>\n<li>umiejętność prowadzenia prezentacji w oparciu MS PowerPoint oraz prezentacji produktów na żywo będą dodatkowym atutem</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Dodatkowe atuty:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>umiejętność programowania w co najmniej jednym z języków: JAVA, .NET (w tym znajomość wzorców projektowych); znajomość PHP, Node.js lub Go będzie dodatkowym atutem;</li>\n<li>doświadczenie w budowaniu/zarządzaniami aplikacjami w chmurach publicznych AWS, Azure, GCP, szczególnie dla EKS, AKS, GKE oraz serverless;</li>\n<li>doświadczenie z narzędziami do monitoringu: Application Performance Monitoring, Infra, NPMD;</li>\n<li>doświadczenie w analizach zrzutów pamięci oraz zrzutów wątków.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(315,6831,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Opis stanowiska<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Nasz klient to innowacyjna polska firma technologiczna, która od kilkunastu lat tworzy własne rozwiązania biznesowe dla rynku pracodawców.</p> Programista React ze znajomością C++ <p><strong>Oferujemy:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Atrakcyjne wynagrodzenie</li>\n<li>Możliwość pracy zdalnej</li>\n<li>Pakiet medyczny, pakiet sportowy, budżet szkoleniowy</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Obowiązki:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Tworzenie i utrzymanie aplikacji desktopowych w Electron z React/C++.</li>\n<li>Dodatkowo obejmuje rozwój natywnych aplikacji C++ z wykorzystaniem wxWidgets.</li>\n<li>Integracja aplikacji z systemami zewnętrznymi</li>\n<li>Współpraca z zespołem w metodykach Agile/Scrum</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Wymagania:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 3-4 lata doświadczenia w tworzeniu aplikacji React</li>\n<li>Znajomość Electron API (IPC, native modules, security)</li>\n<li>Minimum 1-2 lata doświadczenia w programowaniu w C++</li>\n<li>Znajomość standardów C++</li>\n<li>Umiejętność i chęci programowania przy wsparciu z AI</li>\n<li>Znajomość cross-platform development</li>\n<li>Znajomość języka angielskiego - poziom komunikatywny</li>\n<li>Znajomość języka polski - poziom biegły</li>\n<li>Umiejętność pracy w zespole</li>\n<li>Samodzielność i proaktywność</li>\n<li>Chęć ciągłego rozwoju i nauki nowych technologii</li>\n<li>Analityczne myślenie i rozwiązywanie problemów</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Dodatkowe atuty:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Doświadczenie z biblioteką wxWidgets/QT dużym plusem</li></ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(316,6832,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Job description<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Our client is a renowned IT company that has been delivering innovative Microsoft technology-based solutions for over 15 years. As a Microsoft Gold Partner, it specializes in services related to Microsoft Dynamics 365, SharePoint, Office 365, Power BI, and Azure, offering comprehensive business support from custom application development to CRM and cloud solution implementations. Thanks to long-term partnerships with clients both domestically and internationally, the company has earned a reputation as a provider of the highest quality solutions, valuing professionalism and a personalized approach. We are currently looking for ambitious IT specialists, programmers, developers, and consultants who wish to join a team of technology enthusiasts and work together on interesting projects. We offer flexible working hours, a benefits package, the opportunity for development within two career paths – technical and business-analytical, as well as team-building trips and an atmosphere of mutual respect.</p> Senior Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central Consultant <p><strong>We offer:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>attractive remuneration on a B2B basis</li>\n<li>possibility to use paid time off</li>\n<li>work on projects \"from A to Z\"</li>\n<li>Polish and international projects</li>\n<li>co-financing for trainings and courses</li>\n<li>work in an office in Warsaw or hybrid work</li>\n<li>co-financing for Multisport card</li>\n<li>relaxation zone, chess, billiards, board games, PlayStation, as well as team outings and integration trips</li>\n<li>long-term cooperation (not looking for someone short-term).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>co-creating and developing the BC team</li>\n<li>developing and deepening knowledge of oneself and other team members</li>\n<li>analyzing customer requirements in selected areas of the company</li>\n<li>modeling business processes</li>\n<li>configuring systems according to customer requirements</li>\n<li>designing and testing solutions based on business requirements and expectations,</li>\n<li>consulting on functionalities with IT teams (Managers, Developers).</li>\n<li>creating and maintaining technical documentation</li>\n<li>participating in Dynamics 365 Business Central/NAV system implementation projects</li>\n<li>supporting customers in data migration to the system</li>\n<li>actively participating in project meetings</li>\n<li>training users in selected areas</li>\n<li>supporting users in the initial system operation period</li>\n<li>building good and lasting relationships with customers</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>minimum 5 years of experience in implementing Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central (NAV) systems, experience working with more than one module</li>\n<li>extensive knowledge of ERP systems operation</li>\n<li>familiarity with relational databases and SQL language (at least at a basic level)</li>\n<li>experience in functional consulting, business analysis, documentation creation, and reporting</li>\n<li>experience in user training and system testing</li>\n<li>ability to collaborate with business, understand business needs, and translate them into IT solutions</li>\n<li>analytical thinking skills</li>\n<li>ability to work according to established schedules and budgets</li>\n<li>ability to build long-term relationships with clients</li>\n<li>you have a high personal culture</li>\n<li>knowledge of English language at a minimum level of B2</li>\n<li>ability to work in agile methodologies</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Additional advantages:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>experience in team building and management</li></ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(317,6833,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Job description<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Our client is a modern, international technology company specializing in creating innovative solutions for the e-commerce and fintech industry, which values creativity, commitment, and teamwork.</p> Senior Frontend Developer (React + React Native) <p><strong>We offer:</strong></p>\n<p>Attractive salary and bonus system,</p>\n<p>Possibility of remote work and flexible working hours,</p>\n<p>Private medical care and life insurance,</p>\n<p>Access to the latest technologies and tools,</p>\n<p>Budget for training, conferences, and professional development,</p>\n<p>Friendly and supportive work atmosphere in an international environment,</p>\n<p>Modern offices in convenient locations.</p>\n<p><br><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Designing and implementing advanced user interfaces using React and React Native,</li>\n<li>Creating and maintaining reusable components and frontend libraries,</li>\n<li>Close collaboration with backend teams, UX/UI designers, and product owners to deliver high-quality solutions,</li>\n<li>Optimizing applications for performance and scalability,</li>\n<li>Conducting code reviews and mentoring junior team members,</li>\n<li>Participating in planning system architecture and technology selection.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 5 years of experience in creating web applications using React,</li>\n<li>Minimum 3 years of experience in creating mobile applications using React Native,</li>\n<li>Excellent knowledge of JavaScript (ES6+), HTML5, and CSS3,</li>\n<li>Experience with Redux or other state management tools,</li>\n<li>Familiarity with CI/CD tools and experience working with version control systems (Git),</li>\n<li>Ability to write unit and integration tests (Jest, Enzyme, Testing Library),</li>\n<li>Experience with integrating RESTful APIs and GraphQL,</li>\n<li>Knowledge of best practices related to frontend application security,</li>\n<li>Ability to work in agile methodologies (Agile, Scrum),</li>\n<li>Very good communication and interpersonal skills,</li>\n<li>Fluent in English (minimum B2 level).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Additional advantages:</strong></p>\n<p>Experience with TypeScript,</p>\n<p>Knowledge of other frontend frameworks and libraries (Vue.js, Angular),</p>\n<p>Experience in conducting technical training and workshops,</p>\n<p>Familiarity with tools for analyzing and monitoring application performance (e.g. Lighthouse, Sentry).</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(318,6834,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Opis stanowiska<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Nasz klient to innowacyjna firma technologiczna, która od 2025 roku specjalizuje się w rozwiązaniach związanych z chmurą obliczeniową, koncentrując się na platformie AWS. Dzięki bogatemu doświadczeniu w projektowaniu, budowie, wdrażaniu i utrzymaniu środowisk IT oraz aplikacji, zarówno w chmurze, jak i lokalnie, firma uznana jest za lidera w dziedzinie migracji do chmury, przetwarzania danych, sztucznej inteligencji, DevOps, optymalizacji chmury, cyberbezpieczeństwa oraz rozwoju aplikacji chmurowych. Zespół składa się z certyfikowanych ekspertów i partnerów, którzy posiadają kompetencje w kluczowych obszarach technologicznych, co pozwala na świadczenie usług na najwyższym poziomie. Firma współpracuje z klientami z różnych branż, pomagając im maksymalizować potencjał technologii chmurowych dla ich biznesu. Aktualnie poszukujemy utalentowanych specjalistów z doświadczeniem w technologiach chmurowych, którzy chcą dołączyć do naszego zespołu i wspierać nas w dostarczaniu innowacyjnych rozwiązań.</p> Senior Cloud Engineer - AWS <p><strong>Oferujemy:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Budżet szkoleniowy i sponsorowane certyfikaty AWS</li>\n<li>Płatny urlop, prywatna opieka medyczna, Multisport</li>\n<li>Elastyczny czas pracy, praca zdalna</li>\n<li>Darmowe lekcje angielskiego</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Obowiązki:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Projektowanie i implementacja architektur AWS (<strong>EC2, EKS, Lambda, RDS, S3, IAM, VPC, API Gateway, CloudWatch, Route 53</strong>)</li>\n<li>Tworzenie infrastruktury jako kod (<strong>Terraform, AWS CDK</strong>)</li>\n<li>Budowa i utrzymanie CI/CD (<strong>GitHub Actions, GitLab Pipelines, Jenkins, AWS CodePipeline</strong>)</li>\n<li>Tworzenie skryptów i automatyzacja z użyciem <strong>Python, TypeScript, Go, Bash</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Zarządzanie kontenerami (<strong>Docker, Kubernetes, Amazon ECS/EKS</strong>)</li>\n<li>Zapewnienie bezpieczeństwa (IAM policies, szyfrowanie, compliance, architektury HA)</li>\n<li>Monitoring i observability (<strong>CloudWatch, Prometheus, Grafana, ELK/EFK</strong>)</li>\n<li>Wsparcie techniczne, doradztwo i dzielenie się wiedzą z zespołem</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Wymagania:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Min. 4-5 lat doświadczenia w roli <strong>Cloud/DevOps/SRE</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Biegłość w usługach <strong>AWS</strong> i narzędziach IaC</li>\n<li>Doświadczenie w CI/CD, konteneryzacji i automatyzacji</li>\n<li>Znajomość praktyk bezpieczeństwa i projektowania sieci</li>\n<li>Bardzo dobra znajomość języka polskiego i angielskiego</li>\n<li>certyfikaty AWS</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(319,6835,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>The opportunity</h4>\n\n<p>We are creating from scratch new industrial IoT platform which will be used to provide best in class protection software for Power Grids. Our system is mission critical to keep lights on. </p>\n\n<p>Since project is creating from scratch, we are using cutting edge technologies on practice not only in paper. In daily work you will be able to get hands on experience on <strong>containerization</strong>, <strong>Kubernetes (k8s)</strong> and system designed in full fledge <strong>microservice architecture</strong> with all it benefits and drawbacks. We cannot promise you that this will be easy ride, but it will be for sure fun one.</p>\n\n<p>Concepts like <strong>scalability</strong>, <strong>reliability, and availability</strong> are the key base so it is required to have basic knowledge about how they can be achieved in microservice world.</p>\n\n<p>Main message bus and event platform in project is <strong>kafka</strong> which in our case is put on the stress of millions of messages per second. </p>\n\n<p>Low level system components are written in <strong>C#</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>Quality is unquestionable so we constantly invest in test automation, starting from <strong>Unit Test</strong> level which are written in language in which microservice is written, through component and system level, ending on E2E Test which are automated in <strong>Python</strong> using <strong>PyTest</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>Our tech stack and tools include .NET 6, REST API, SLQ (PostgreSQL, SQL Server), Git, Azure DevOps, Kafka, Docker, Kubernetes, Prometheus.</p>\n\n<h4>How You Will Make an Impact</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Working in a cross-disciplinary team using the Agile development methodology</li>\n<li>Ensure best in class product quality by performing configuration tasks and root cause analysis</li>\n<li>Automate deployment and delivery processes</li>\n<li>Report defects and issues in product</li>\n<li>Build, develop and maintain the Continuous Delivery toolchain, to achieve reliable and stable releases</li>\n<li>Develop and document the continuous deployment build and release process</li>\n<li>Interact with various global product teams to meet their specific needs</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot build and release issues, administrate servers daily</li>\n<li>Help implement process and tools improvements</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(320,6836,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>IT Project Manager for Business Solution Team</h4>\n\n<p><strong>Company Name:</strong> HITACHI ENERGY SERVICES SP. Z O.O.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Hitachi Energy Grid Automation - Business Solutions IT Team is seeking an experienced IT Project Manager to support our global business, drive value, and foster growth.</p>\n\n<p>This role offers a unique opportunity to lead impactful digital transformation projects on a global scale and contribute to the strategic growth of the business.</p>\n\n<p><strong>How you will make impact:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Project management:</strong> Team management in multiple time zones, planning, set up scope, budgeting, forecasting, reporting, manage projects using agile and iterative project methodologies and use various project management tools</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Project delivery:</strong> Drive on-time and on-budget delivery of project from Initiate to Close</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Stakeholder management:</strong> Facilitate internal and supplier meetings, pro-active Stakeholder Management and engage on individual needs</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Change management</strong>: Manage project scope and identify need for and develop change orders</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Project communication:</strong> determine communication plans</li>\n<li>*<em>Risk &amp; escalation management: *</em>identify and manage risks and issues, including escalations</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Project governance &amp; compliance:</strong> ensure adherence to Hitachi Energy delivery methodology, including project controls</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>More about us:</strong></p>\n\n<p>About Hitachi: <a href=\"http://www.hitachienergy.com/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.hitachienergy.com/</a></p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(321,6837,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Wolt</h4>\n\n<p>At Wolt, we create technology that brings joy, simplicity and earnings to the neighborhoods of the world. In 2014 we started with delivery of restaurant food. Now we’re building the delivery of (almost) everything and you’ll find us in over 500 cities in 30 countries around the world. In 2022 we joined forces with DoorDash and together we keep on dreaming big and expanding across the globe.</p>\n\n<p>Working at Wolt isn’t always easy, but it’s definitely exciting. Here you’ll learn more, build more, and ship more than in most other companies. You’ll be challenged a lot, but also have a lot of fun on the way. So, if you’re a self-starter with drive and entrepreneurial spirit, this could be the ride of your life.</p>\n\n<p>The Merchant Support Associate works in close cooperation with the Restaurant/Retail Development Managers and Support Associates to help our restaurant and retail partners maximise their opportunities for success.</p>\n\n<p>The MxSA is responsible for assisting our merchant partners, offer general day-to-day support and help merchants towards improving their commercial and operational performance.</p>\n\n<h4>What you\'ll be doing:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Answering partners’ inquiries and requests regarding their ongoing use of Wolt delivery services.</li>\n<li>Assisting our Support team in handling more complex partner support tickets.</li>\n<li>Managing our equipment enrollment, inventory and resolving tech-issues.</li>\n<li>Managing the administrative side of changes to partnership contracts.</li>\n<li>Managing ongoing improvements to restaurant menus and retail assortments on the platform.</li>\n<li>Support the merchant team in helping ensure the success of merchant partners with low sales and/or bad operational performance.</li>\n<li>Taking ownership of other projects in connection with merchant operations.</li>\n<li>Assisting the Merchant team with other ad-hoc tasks.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(322,6838,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior Full-Stack Engineer (Node.js + React)</h4>\n\n<p>Are you infatuated with both front-end and back-end development? Then we’d love to hear from you as we\'re currently seeking a passionate <strong>Senior</strong> <strong>Full-Stack Engineer</strong>. You\'ll be involved in developing both sides of the application - UI features parts and API endpoints. Moreover, you\'ll have a real impact on your work since we are solid vendors representing only the final result to the client. Sounds interesting? If so, we’d be delighted to receive your resume!&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>About the client:&nbsp;</strong>\nThis is an award winning, all-in-one gifting platform that helps companies reward their employees and customers - boosting loyalty and engagement through a fun and engaging digital experience. Product’s gifting algorithm automates the selection and sending off personal gifts and messages at scale, and notifies recipients through fun and personalized digital unboxing experiences. \n<br>They specialize in building recognition programs for all sorts of businesses - Amazon, Zoom, Salesforce, Microsoft, Uber, Deloitte and over 800 more, Plus, they\'re growing everyday - 400%, if you want to get technical! They\'ve seen firsthand that our experience boosts morale, improves performance, and (most importantly!) spreads joy.</p>\n\n<p><strong>About Innovecs:</strong> \nInnovecs is a global digital services company with a presence in the US, the UK, the EU, Israel, Australia, and Ukraine. Specializing in software solutions, the Innovecs team has experience in Supply Chain, Healthtech, Collaboration Tech, and Gaming. \nFor the fifth year in a row, Innovecs is included in the Inc. 5000, the list of fastest-growing private companies in the US, and a ranking of the best global outsourcing service providers by IAOP. Recently, Innovecs was honored with the prestigious Global Good Awards for the Employee Engagement &amp; Wellbeing, won gold at the Employer Brand Management Awards, and was included in the Global Top 100 Inspiring Workplaces Ranking.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(323,6839,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Join us as a Senior Product Manager @Webshare to play a key role in owning and driving core areas of the product. Webshare is a high-growth proxy service platform trusted by thousands of users around the world. Our self-serve product allows customers to easily deploy and manage proxy services, offering unmatched flexibility and control.</p>\n\n<p>Webshare is a part of Oxylabs: a team of 500+ professionals who develop cutting-edge web data gathering solutions for thousands of the world’s best known businesses.</p>\n\n<p>You’ll be joining a small, fast-paced and innovative team that deeply values thoughtful design, fast iteration, and user-first thinking. We’re now expanding the team to support continued growth and product scale. This role is ideal for someone hands-on, curious, detail-oriented, and excited to work at the intersection of design, engineering, and business.</p>\n\n<h4>Your day-to-day:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Drive product development from discovery to launch, owning specs, timelines, and iteration.</li>\n<li>Identify low-cost, high-impact improvements through user behavior analysis and internal feedback.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with frontend engineers to run experiments, write PRDs, answer implementation questions, and clarify feasibility.</li>\n<li>Work closely with backend engineers to understand technical constraints, especially around proxies, networking, and platform architecture.</li>\n<li>Guide the product designer to align features with user needs, product goals, and real usage data.</li>\n<li>Partner with the risk team to manage internal tool improvements that support fraud prevention and user verification</li>\n<li>Support the commerce lead (in charge of CS, account management, and marketing) by running pricing experiments and incorporating customer feedback from support channels into the product roadmap.</li>\n<li>Help prioritize engineering work based on cost, user impact, and business goals.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(324,6840,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Kyriba is a global leader in liquidity performance that empowers CFOs, Treasurers and IT leaders to connect, protect, forecast and optimize their liquidity. As a secure and scalable SaaS solution, Kyriba brings intelligence and financial automation that enables companies and banks of all sizes to improve their financial performance and increase operational efficiency. Kyriba’s real-time data and AI-empowered tools empower its 3,000 customers worldwide to quantify exposures, project cash and liquidity, and take action to protect balance sheets, income statements and cash flows. Kyriba manages more than 3.5 billion bank transactions and $15 trillion in payments annually and gives customers complete visibility and actionability, so they can optimize and fully harness liquidity across the enterprise and outperform their business strategy. For more information, visit <a href=\"http://www.kyriba.com/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">www.kyriba.com</a>.</p>\n\n<p>We are seeking a highly motivated <b>Junior Business Analyst</b> to join our Product Management team specifically in the area of financial transactions and valuation. The successful candidate will hold a Master’s degree in Finance, Quantitative Finance, or a related field, or 2 years practical experience alongside an undergraduate degree in a business related field. They will contribute to the continuous evolution of Kyriba’s financial SaaS solutions. This role offers an excellent opportunity for a recent graduate to combine financial expertise with product development, working in close collaboration with product managers, solution consultants, and engineering teams.</p>\n\n<p><b>Key Responsibilities</b></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Support product managers in defining, documenting, and prioritizing business requirements for new product features and enhancements.</li>\n<li>Translate complex financial concepts into functional specifications, user stories, and acceptance criteria.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with engineering teams to ensure accurate and timely implementation of requirements.</li>\n<li>Participate in product testing activities, including user acceptance testing (UAT) and validation of product enhancements.</li>\n<li>Analyze client feedback, product usage, and industry trends to identify opportunities for improvement.</li>\n<li>Assist in the preparation of product documentation, release notes, training materials, and stakeholder presentations.</li>\n<li>Maintain awareness of treasury management practices, liquidity optimization, and risk management developments to support product innovation.</li>\n<li>Conduct financial and market research to inform product strategy.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(325,6841,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Us</h4>\n\n<p>Kyriba is a global leader in liquidity performance that empowers CFOs, Treasurers and IT leaders to connect, protect, forecast and optimize their liquidity. As a secure and scalable SaaS solution, Kyriba brings intelligence and financial automation that enables companies and banks of all sizes to improve their financial performance and increase operational efficiency. Kyriba’s real-time data and AI-empowered tools empower its 3,000 customers worldwide to quantify exposures, project cash and liquidity, and take action to protect balance sheets, income statements and cash flows. Kyriba manages more than 3.5 billion bank transactions and $15 trillion in payments annually and gives customers complete visibility and actionability, so they can optimize and fully harness liquidity across the enterprise and outperform their business strategy. For more information, visit <a href=\"http://www.kyriba.com/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">www.kyriba.com</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Being an intern at Kyriba means more than simply getting involved in the day-to-day operations of the company. It is an opportunity to introduce you to your potential future work environment so that you can better decide if it meets your career goals.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for an enthusiastic <strong>QA Automation Engineer Intern</strong> to join our Risk Accounting team, which is part of our Engineering Department.\nThe main goal of this internship is to support our team with automating quality assurance.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Keywords :</strong> JUnit, Java, Playwright, Gherkin, Newman, Automation, Gatling, JavaScript, TypeScript, Agility, QA, Jenkins, CI.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Position Type:</strong> Internship (Open to both graduates and senior students)\n<strong>Duration:</strong> 6 months\n<strong>Location:</strong> Poland, Remote</p>\n\n<h4>Responsibilities</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Implement automation tests</li>\n<li>Participate in defining KPIs to measure performance and reliability</li>\n<li>Propose the changes in the tests</li>\n<li>Propose how to improve test environments</li>\n<li>Improve tests stability</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(326,6842,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>ABOUT US:</h4>\n\n<p>LSEG (London Stock Exchange Group) is more than a diversified global financial markets infrastructure and data business. We are dedicated, open-access partners with a dedication to excellence in delivering the services our customers expect from us. With extensive experience, deep knowledge and worldwide presence across financial markets, we enable businesses and economies around the world to fund innovation, manage risk and create jobs. It’s how we’ve contributed to supporting the financial stability and growth of communities and economies globally for more than 300 years. Through a comprehensive suite of trusted financial market infrastructure services – and our open-access model – we provide the flexibility, stability and trust that enable our customers to pursue their ambitions with confidence and clarity.</p>\n\n<p>LSEG is headquartered in the United Kingdom, with significant operations in 70 countries across EMEA, North America, Latin America and Asia Pacific. We employ 25,000 people globally, more than half located in Asia Pacific. LSEG’s ticker symbol is LSEG.</p>\n\n<h4>OUR PEOPLE:</h4>\n\n<p>People are at the heart of what we do and drive the success of our business. Our culture of connecting, creating opportunity and delivering excellence shape how we think, how we do things and how we help our people fulfil their potential. We embrace diversity and actively seek to attract individuals with unique backgrounds and perspectives. We break down barriers and encourage teamwork, enabling innovation and rapid development of solutions that make a difference. Our workplace generates an enriching and rewarding experience for our people and customers alike. Our vision is to build an inclusive culture in which everyone feels encouraged to fulfil their potential.</p>\n\n<p>We know that real personal growth cannot be achieved by simply climbing a career ladder – which is why we encourage and enable a wealth of avenues and interesting opportunities for everyone to broaden and deepen their skills and expertise. As a global organization spanning 70 countries and one rooted in a culture of growth, opportunity, diversity and innovation, LSEG is a place where everyone can grow, develop and fulfil your potential with meaningful careers!</p>\n\n<h4>ROLE SUMMARY:</h4>\n\n<p>Ready to build scalable data systems with real-world impact?</p>\n\n<p>Join us at FTSE Russell! We’re establishing a team of engineers passionate about data, software craftsmanship, and substantial impact. As a Lead Software Data Engineer, you’ll help power the indices trusted by financial institutions worldwide. You’ll work in a modern AWS environment, build robust pipelines, and collaborate closely with product and business teams to deliver reliable, high-quality data solutions. We care about code quality, ownership, and helping each other grow. If you’re excited about building systems that matter, we’d love to meet you!</p>\n\n<h4>WHAT YOU\'LL BE DOING:</h4>\n\n<p>We are building the next-generation data platform at FTSE Russell — and we want you to shape it with us. Your role will involve:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Designing and developing scalable, testable data pipelines using Python and Apache Spark</li>\n<li>Orchestrating data workflows with AWS tools like Glue, EMR Serverless, Lambda, and S3</li>\n<li>Applying modern software engineering practices: version control, CI/CD, modular design, and automated testing</li>\n<li>Contributing to the development of a lakehouse architecture using Apache Iceberg</li>\n<li>Collaborating with business teams to translate requirements into data-driven solutions</li>\n<li>Building observability into data flows and implementing basic quality checks</li>\n<li>Participating in code reviews, pair programming, and architecture discussions</li>\n<li>Continuously learning about the financial indices domain and sharing insights with the team</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(327,6843,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Customer Support Specialist with German</h4>\n\n<p>The Advisor I, Customer Service position interfaces with customers via inbound calls, outbound calls, or through the Internet depending upon client requirements. This position provides customer service support and resolution of routine problems regarding client\'s product or services.</p>\n\n Your responsibilities \n\n<ul>\n<li>Customer Support: Assist customers with all kinds of inquiries and provide top-notch service before and after their purchases.</li>\n<li>Product Advice: Share expert advice and offer personalized product comparisons, helping customers make smart purchasing decisions.</li>\n<li>Call Handling: Manage inbound and outbound calls, always aiming for clarity, efficiency, and customer satisfaction.</li>\n<li>Data &amp; Documentation: Keep things running smoothly by managing customer data, records, and documentation with precision.</li>\n<li>Tech Troubleshooting: Help customers solve technical issues quickly and effectively.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Location:\nPOL Katowice - Global Office Park, Building A2 Flrs 10 thru 13</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(328,6844,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Team Leader with German On-Site</h4>\n\n<p><strong>Job Description</strong>\nThe Team Leader, Operations is responsible for the day-to-day supervision of a group of call center associates. This position ensures performance metrics are achieved by providing adequate coaching, motivation and accountability.</p>\n\n<p>*<em>Essential Functions/Core Responsibilities\n*</em>\n* Responsible for the day-to-day supervision of a group of call center associates including work and attendance monitoring in accordance with organization policy and applicable legal requirements.\n* Effectively coach direct reports on their performance on a regular basis to ensure performance metrics are achieved at a minimum weekly.\n* Identify performance related issues, develop an action plan for improvement, implement corrective action, up to and including termination of employment.\n* Ensure service delivered to our customers meets contractual Key Performance Indicator (‘KPIs’) and financial expectations.\n* Communicate expectations to employees and provide timely updates.\n* Provide subject matter expertise in handling escalated customer calls as needed.\n* Conduct Team Meetings to ensure expedient communication of relevant information and as an open forum for input. Schedule and organize team activities.\n* Stay current on internal work processes, policies and procedures. Attend required manager development training.\n* Promote the Concentrix values through both behavior and attitude, including being an advocate for team members.</p>\n\n<p>*<em>Career Level Description\n*</em>\nReceives assignments in tasks oriented terms and supervises subordinates to set priorities and complete assignments. Coordinates and supervises the daily activities of business or technical support or production team members. In charge of handling single and medium-sized line of business. Decisions are guided by policies, procedures and business plan; receives guidance and oversight from manager. Drives direct reports to achieve set metrics and business goals thru coaching, mentoring and providing regular feedback. Typically does not spend more than 20% of time performing the work supervised. Handles escalated issues. Supervises non-exempt employees who generally perform either a single task or multiple, but closely related tasks.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Location:</strong>\nPOL Katowice - Global Office Park, Building A2 Flrs 10 thru 13</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(329,6845,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Our Purpose</h4>\n\n<p>Mastercard powers economies and empowers people in 200+ countries and territories worldwide. Together with our customers, we’re helping build a sustainable economy where everyone can prosper. We support a wide range of digital payments choices, making transactions secure, simple, smart and accessible. Our technology and innovation, partnerships and networks combine to deliver a unique set of products and services that help people, businesses and governments realize their greatest potential.</p>\n\n<h4>Senior Software Engineer - GO</h4>\n\n<p><strong>1) Overview</strong>\nAs a member of the Software Defined Networking Operations team, you will own and deliver the code to bring our Operations group to the next level. As a \"militantly automated\" team, we work in Source Control and let pipelines drive our work. We believe in configuration modeling and defining standards via automation so the tooling can do the heavy lifting for us. You will participate on a high performing team that designs, builds, and runs world-class and leading-edge networking technology on many exciting platforms. As a member of the SDN Ops team, you will be building internal-facing tools to improve our tooling and increase our efficiency to support our customers.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong>\n*   Tool Development: Build and maintain internal tools that automate network operations, improve observability, and streamline workflows.\n*   Infrastructure as Code: Model configurations and enforce standards through code, enabling consistent and repeatable deployments.\n*   Pipeline-Driven Engineering: Leverage CI/CD pipelines to manage code delivery, testing, and deployment.\n*   SDN Integration: Work with SDN controllers and APIs to abstract and automate network provisioning, policy enforcement, and lifecycle management.\n*   Collaboration: Partner with network engineers, architects, and other software teams to align tooling with operational needs and business goals.\n*   Mentorship: Mentor engineers on the Operations team and act as the team expert in all things software engineering.</p>\n\n<p><strong>2) Role</strong>\nYou will design, build, and maintain internal-facing tools that support the SDN Operations team’s mission to deliver scalable, resilient, and automated networking solutions. The team operates with a “militantly automated” philosophy—favoring pipelines, source control, and configuration modeling over manual processes. Your work will directly impact how networking infrastructure is provisioned, monitored, and managed across platforms.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(330,6846,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior Security Compliance Specialist</h4>\n\n<p>Acronis is revolutionizing cyber protection—providing natively integrated, all-in-one solutions that monitor, control, and protect the data that businesses and lives depend on. We are looking for a Senior Security Compliance Specialist to join our mission to create a #CyberFit future and protect all data, applications and systems across any environment.</p>\n\n<p>A specialist is responsible for developing and implementing frameworks to ensure an organization adheres to governance, risk management, and compliance requirements. They identify and mitigate risks, ensure regulatory compliance, and maintain effective communication and reporting to uphold organizational integrity.</p>\n\n<h4>WHAT YOU\'LL DO</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Maintain company certifications (such as ISO 27001, ISO 9001, PCI DSS etc.);</li>\n<li>Conduct an internal audits (ISO 27001, ISO 9001, etc)</li>\n<li>Ensure that policies and procedures are up-to-date and compliant with all applicable laws and regulations;</li>\n<li>Research and implement controls required by security standards and data protection regulations;</li>\n<li>Develop and deliver security awareness training programs to educate employees on security best practices and compliance requirements.</li>\n<li>Take a part in external security and compliance audits;</li>\n<li>Conduct security risk assessment and analysis;</li>\n<li>Facilitate suppliers\' risk assessment process;</li>\n<li>Respond to clients and regulatory due-diligence requests</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>WHO WE ARE</h4>\n\n<p>A Swiss company founded in Singapore in 2003, Acronis offers over twenty years of innovation with 15 offices worldwide and more than 1800 employees in 50+ countries. Acronis Cyber Protect is available in 26 languages in 150 countries and is used by over 20,000 service providers to protect over 750,000 businesses.</p>\n\n<p>Our corporate culture is focused on making a positive impact on the lives of each employee and the communities we serve. Mutual trust, respect and belief that we can contribute to the world everyday are the cornerstones of our team. Each member of our “A-Team” plays an instrumental role in driving the success of our innovative and expanding business. We seek individuals who excel in dynamic, global environments and have a never give up attitude, contributing to our collective growth and impact.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(331,6847,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Veeam</h4>\n\n<p>Veeam, the #1 global market leader in data resilience, believes businesses should control all their data whenever and wherever they need it. Veeam provides data resilience through data backup, data recovery, data portability, data security, and data intelligence. Based in Seattle, Veeam protects over 550,000 customers worldwide who trust Veeam to keep their businesses running. Join us as we move forward together, growing, learning, and making a real impact for some of the world’s biggest brands. The future of data resilience is here - go fearlessly forward with us.</p>\n\n<h4>About the Role</h4>\n\n<p>Join as a C# developer and help shape the internal tools for automating development processes of Veeam products, enhancing data protection and driving business resilience.</p>\n\n<h4>What You’ll Do</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Work on tooling to automate different aspects of the development process</li>\n<li>Develop tools for optimizing, automating, and monitoring the code build process</li>\n<li>Improve the process of creating and publishing build artifacts</li>\n<li>Create static code analyzers to improve code quality</li>\n<li>Improve build configurations of .NET projects, working with MSBuild internals</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Technologies You\'ll Work With</h4>\n\n<p>C#, .Net 8, Azure DevOps, MSBuild, etc.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(332,6848,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Job Overview</h4>\n\n<p>We are looking for responsible and self-motivated <strong>Linux System Administrator</strong> who will be part of Global IT department. We interact with employees of all company offices, regardless of position, line of business and time zones. &nbsp;\nWorking in our team you will provide internal services for our company, support internal development, and vendors solutions.</p>\n\n<h4>Reports to</h4>\n\n<p>Maintenance Team Lead</p>\n\n<h4>What will you do?</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Deployment</li>\n<li>Support and maintenance of internally developed products and vendor solutions&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>About Wargaming&nbsp;\nWargaming is an award-winning online game developer and publisher headquartered in Nicosia, Cyprus. Operating since 1998, Wargaming has become one of the leaders in the gaming industry with 15 offices worldwide, including studios in Chicago, Prague, Shanghai, Tokyo, and Vilnius. Our diverse and multicultural team works together to deliver a top-class experience to millions of players who enjoy Wargaming\'s titles across all major gaming platforms. Our flagship products include free-to-play hits World of Tanks, World of Warships and World of Tanks Blitz.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(333,6849,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>You\'ll be working in the Neo Access POD team, based in Poland. We look after the login and entitlements experience for \"Neo\", a globally distributed platform with 2m+ users. Authentication standards and technology are constantly shifting and we need to stay up-to-date with the latest trends. We strive to provide our clients with the highest standards of security and reliability. The Neo team has around 100 people, spread globally.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Design, develop, and maintain desktop applications using OpenFin and Electron on Windows</li>\n<li>Integrate applications with the global Neo platform, focusing on authentication and entitlements</li>\n<li>Implement solutions aligned with the latest security and authentication standards</li>\n<li>Collaborate with globally distributed teams on architecture and new features</li>\n<li>Conduct code reviews and ensure high-quality coding practices</li>\n<li>Monitor and troubleshoot issues related to performance, stability, and security of desktop applications</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(334,6850,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>We are looking for a colleague to join the development team of sophisticated software for the global leader in Innovative Orthodontics. The team develops APIs and other services to integrates all internal systems and applications around the process of orthodontic manufacturing.</p>\n<p>We\'re looking for a Software Business Analyst (BA) who would help drive development of a user-facing desktop application. You will work in an agile environment alongside a Product Manager (PM) of your project, its development team and alongside PMs and BAs of related projects in the ecosystem. Your main tasks will include communication with various stakeholders to gather, analyze, clarify, decompose and describe business requirements, supporting and guiding an R&amp;D team in developing features according to specified requirements and expectations and preparing and maintaining a reasonable amount of documentation for the developed software product. To succeed in this role you should have a natural analytical way of thinking, good attention to detail and excellent communication skills.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(335,6851,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>We are supporting Our client in a strategic automotive project focused on Functional Safety (FuSa) and next-generation ECU development. The role involves working on multi-core configurations, Classic AUTOSAR, and Basic Software (BSW) stacks, ensuring compliance with ISO 26262 standards. The architect will collaborate with global teams to design and configure ECU systems that meet ASIL-D certification requirements.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Define and maintain system and software architecture for automotive ECUs.</li>\n<li>Evaluate ECUs with the goal of achieving ASIL certification.</li>\n<li>Perform HARA (Hazard Analysis and Risk Assessment) and TARA (Threat Analysis and Risk Assessment) activities.</li>\n<li>Design, configure, and implement BSW stacks as per AUTOSAR standards.</li>\n<li>Provide guidance on hardware configuration for platforms such as Aurix TC3XX, Traveo, and S32K.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure compliance with ISO 26262 and ASPICE processes.</li>\n<li>Support integration and configuration of Vector tooling and other AUTOSAR toolchains.</li>\n<li>Communicate technical concepts and safety strategies to stakeholders.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(336,6852,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Job description<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Join a Quality Assurance team that is passionate and works together to ensure the highest quality for our products. Our objective is to infuse quality into every stage of the development process, from the initial idea to the final release. We support guidelines, promote enhancements in processes, and collaborate closely with development, product, and design teams to deliver exceptional user experiences. We cultivate an environment of continual learning and technical excellence, empowering our team with the necessary resources and freedom to have a genuine impact.\nThe Senior QA Engineer position entails being a primary quality advocate in the QA team. Your tasks include crafting comprehensive test strategies for complex features and systems. In addition to test execution, you will pinpoint risks, improve QA processes, and guide junior team members. By collaborating with engineers, product managers, and designers, you will uphold quality standards to deliver durable, reliable, and user-centric products.\nWhat You\'ll Do\n* Design, develop, and own comprehensive, risk-based test plans for sophisticated features and system integrations.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Proactively identify potential quality issues and risks in requirements and architecture, providing constructive feedback.</p></li>\n<li><p>Define the scope of testing (manual, automated, performance, security) required for projects, ensuring optimal coverage across client and server.</p></li>\n<li><p>Complete sophisticated manual and automated tests across the full stack, analyzing results and identifying root causes of defects.</p></li>\n<li><p>Manage the full defect lifecycle, ensuring high-quality reporting and timely resolution for critical integration issues.</p></li>\n<li><p>Establish and report on key quality metrics, providing clear access to product health to customers.</p></li>\n<li><p>Demonstrate expert proficiency in our testing tools and systems (e.g., Bug Tracking, Test Case Management, SQL).</p></li>\n<li><p>Have a meaningful impact on the advancement and upkeep of test automation frameworks for both API and client-side testing.</p></li>\n<li><p>Act as a mentor and technical resource for QA engineers, providing guidance on end-to-end testing, problem-solving, and career growth.</p></li>\n<li><p>Partner effectively with developers and product managers to ensure a shared understanding of requirements and quality expectations.</p></li>\n<li><p>Champion a \"quality-first\" culture by promoting continuous improvement, sharing knowledge, and facilitating discussions on quality.</p></li>\n<li><p>Drive tangible improvements in the team\'s multi-functional testing processes and tooling.</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>What We\'re Looking For<em>Must-Have:</em></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Proven QA Experience: 5+ years of professional experience in QA, with a proven track record of testing complex, distributed systems.</p></li>\n<li><p>Testing Acumen: Expert understanding of SDLC, QA methodologies, and a range of testing approaches (closed system, grey box, integration).</p></li>\n<li><p>Technical Skills: Skilled in RESTful API testing, SQL/database principles, and client-side testing.</p></li>\n<li><p>Strategic Pragmatism: Excellent ability to analyze complex systems, identify risks, and make pragmatic decisions. Strong problem-solving skills are essential.</p></li>\n<li><p>Communication &amp; Influence: Proficient communication skills. Ability to articulate complex technical concepts clearly, influence customers, and lead quality initiatives.</p></li>\n<li><p>Growth Mindset: A history of continuously learning, actively developing personal and team skills, and spearheading process enhancements.</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Nice-to-Have:\n* Experience working in the gaming industry.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines (e.g., Jenkins).</p></li>\n<li><p>Experience with performance and load testing tools.</p></li>\n<li><p>Proficiency with monitoring and analytics tools (e.g., New Relic, Redash).</p></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><em>Why *</em>Product Madness*<em>?</em>\nAs part of the Aristocrat family, we share their mission of bringing joy to life through the power of play, with a world-class team who creates top-grossing, leading titles in the social casino genre, including Heart of Vegas, Lightning Link, Cashman Casino.&nbsp;With 800 team members across the globe, Product Madness is headquartered in London, with offices in Barcelona, Gdańsk, Lviv, Montreal and a remote team spanning the USA, making us a truly global powerhouse.\nWe live by our People First principle. Regardless of where, when, or how they work, our team members have opportunities to elevate their careers, and grow alongside us. We take pride in fostering an inclusive culture, where our people are encouraged to be their very best, every day. But don’t just take our word for it. In 2024, we made the Global Inspiring Workplace Awards list, and won a bronze award at the Stevies for Great Employers in the ‘Employer of the Year - Media and Entertainment’ category.\nSo, what’s stopping you?\n<em>Travel Expectations</em>\nNone<em>Additional Information</em>\nAt this time, we are unable to sponsor work visas for this position. Candidates must be authorized to work in the job posting location for this position on a full-time basis without the need for current or future visa sponsorship. </p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(337,6853,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Opis stanowiska<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>W chwili obecnej nie jesteśmy w stanie zapewnić sponsoringu wiz pracowniczych w związku z tym stanowiskiem. Kandydaci muszą posiadać upoważnienie do pełnoetatowej pracy w miejscu, w którym ogłoszono nabór na to stanowisko, bez konieczności korzystania obecnie oraz w przyszłości ze sponsoringu w celu otrzymania wizy.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(338,6854,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Opis stanowiska<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Nasz klient to dynamicznie rozwijająca się firma, która od 2020 roku zajmuje się świadczeniem kompleksowych usług z zakresu audytu, doradztwa, rozwoju, testowania użytkownika oraz UX/UI. Specjalizując się w tworzeniu innowacyjnych rozwiązań cyfrowych, współpracuje z renomowanymi klientami, takimi jak Sodexo, oferując nowoczesne podejście do zarządzania benefitami pracowniczymi poprzez aplikacje mobilne. Dzięki zespołowi ekspertów i biurom w Genewie, Paryżu, Brukseli, Liège oraz Gdańsku, nasz klient nieustannie poszukuje nowych talentów, którzy chcą dołączyć do ich międzynarodowego zespołu. Jeśli jesteś osobą, która pasjonuje się najnowszymi technologiami i chcesz pracować nad projektami zmieniającymi oblicze cyfrowego świata, ta firma oferuje wyjątkowe możliwości rozwoju i realizacji zawodowych ambicji.</p> iOS Developer <p><strong>Oferujemy:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Dopłaty do prywatnego ubezpieczenia zdrowotnego,</li>\n<li>Karta sportowa i dofinansowanie aktywności fizycznych,</li>\n<li>Kursy językowe,</li>\n<li>Nowoczesny sprzęt i elastyczny tryb pracy.</li>\n<li>Projekty dla międzynarodowych klientów w dynamicznym zespole.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Obowiązki:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Tworzenie i rozwijanie aplikacji iOS w Swift,</li>\n<li>Implementacja logowania, autoryzacji i zarządzania kontami użytkowników.</li>\n<li>Integracja z API (REST/GraphQL) i backendem.</li>\n<li>Przygotowanie aplikacji do publikacji w App Store (certyfikaty, provisioning, metadane).</li>\n<li>Optymalizacja wydajności, analiza błędów i utrzymanie aplikacji.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Wymagania:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 2-3 lata doświadczenia w tworzeniu aplikacji iOS.</li>\n<li>Bardzo dobra znajomość języka Swift i środowiska Xcode.</li>\n<li>Znajomość systemów logowania, autoryzacji i ochrony danych w aplikacjach mobilnych.</li>\n<li>Doświadczenie w publikowaniu aplikacji do App Store.</li>\n<li>Doświadczenie z CI/CD i automatyzacją buildów.</li>\n<li>Biegła znajomość języka angielskiego w mowie i piśmie.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Dodatkowe atuty:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Podstawowa znajomość Flutter / Dart.</li>\n<li>Znajomość SwiftUI, Combine lub RxSwift.</li>\n<li>Zrozumienie architektury MVVM lub Clean Architecture.</li>\n<li>Znajomość narzędzi analitycznych (Firebase, Sentry).</li>\n<li>Zainteresowanie nowymi technologiami mobilnymi.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(339,6855,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Opis stanowiska<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Nasz klient to innowacyjna firma działająca w branży IT od kilkunastu lat, specjalizująca się w projektowaniu i tworzeniu nowoczesnych rozwiązań mobilnych. Oferuje szeroki zakres usług, w tym projektowanie stron internetowych, tworzenie aplikacji mobilnych, zarządzanie procesami, wsparcie techniczne oraz zarządzanie projektami.</p> PHP Developer (Full Stack) <p><strong>Oferujemy:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Atrakcyjne wynagrodzenie</li>\n<li>Edukacja w formie kursów / szkoleń / konferencji / książek</li>\n<li>Praca z 15. piętra z widokiem na Tatry</li>\n<li>Spotkania integracyjne</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Obowiązki:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Aktywny udział w procesie tworzenia oprogramowania - nie tylko dostarczysz kod, ale także pomożesz nam w szacowaniu, planowaniu pracy i testowaniu</li>\n<li>Bezpośredni wpływ na jakość kodu - stosujemy przegląd kodu, bez niego nie ma wdrożeń</li>\n<li>Udział w cotygodniowych podsumowaniach pracy i codziennych spotkaniach stand-up</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Wymagania:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Od 3 do 5-6 lat doświadczenia na podobnym stanowisku</li>\n<li>Znajomość JS, Vue2/3, Nuxt 2/3</li>\n<li>Doświadczenie z Laravel</li>\n<li>Doświadczenie z:<ul>\n<li>DRY, KISS, SOLID</li>\n<li>PHP7+</li>\n<li>HTML5, CSS3</li>\n<li>OOP</li>\n<li>Git &amp; git-flow</li>\n<li>Agile, Scrum</li>\n<li>Mysql</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Dobra znajomość języka angielskiego</li>\n<li>Jeśli masz doświadczenie z Symfony, Zend lub Angular, React i chciałbyś zacząć pracę w Laravel i Vue - jest taka możliwość</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Dodatkowe atuty:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Doświadczenie z Zend</li>\n<li>Doświadczenie z Elasticsearch lub Solr</li>\n<li>Doświadczenie z:<ul>\n<li>Composer</li>\n<li>REST, SOAP</li>\n<li>DDD, CQRS</li>\n<li>PSR-4</li>\n<li>UML</li>\n<li>Jira, Stride</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(340,6856,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Opis stanowiska<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Nasz klient to wiodący partner Amazon Web Services, stworzony przez ekspertów ds. chmury z wieloletnim doświadczeniem. Firma skutecznie wdraża projekty dla klientów w całej Europie, w branżach takich jak telekomunikacja, bankowość, medycyna i farmacja.</p> Gen AI Engineer <p><strong>Oferujemy:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Atrakcyjne wynagrodzenie</li>\n<li>Ciągłe kształcenie</li>\n<li>Płatny urlop</li>\n<li>Sponsorowany certyfikat AWS</li>\n<li>Budżet szkoleniowy</li>\n<li>Pakiet opieki medycznej</li>\n<li>Elastyczny grafik</li>\n<li>Bezpłatne lekcje angielskiego</li>\n<li>Dofinansowanie karty Multisport</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Obowiązki:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Projektowanie, wdrażanie i testowanie rozwiązań opartych na GenAI w środowisku chmury AWS</li>\n<li>Opracowywanie i optymalizowanie modeli GenAI przy użyciu narzędzi i usług AWS, takich jak SageMaker, Lambda, EC2, S3 oraz innych narzędzi AI/ML</li>\n<li>Integracja rozwiązań opartych na sztucznej inteligencji z istniejącą infrastrukturą, opartą na architekturach bezserwerowych</li>\n<li>Wdrażanie mechanizmów automatyzacji dla szkolenia modeli, potoków ML oraz CI/CD dla rozwiązań opartych na AI</li>\n<li>Analiza danych szkoleniowych i ich przygotowanie do szkolenia modeli generatywnych</li>\n<li>Opracowywanie i wdrażanie rozwiązań przetwarzania danych w czasie rzeczywistym oraz szkolenia modeli</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Wymagania:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Minimum 1,5-2 lata doświadczenia w obszarze ML / MLOps, inżynierii danych, GenAI (lub pokrewnych w AWS)</li>\n<li>Biegła znajomość języka Python i znajomość frameworków AI</li>\n<li>Praktyczne doświadczenie w szkoleniu i optymalizacji modeli GenAI</li>\n<li>Doskonałe umiejętności werbalne (polski i angielski) oraz przyjazne podejście do ludzi</li>\n<li>Ogólna chęć pomocy klientom w trudnościach z problemami technicznymi</li>\n<li>Dobre zrozumienie praktyk inżynierii oprogramowania, takich jak przeglądy kodu, zarządzanie kontrolą źródła, procesy budowania, testowanie, wdrożenie, wydanie i zarządzanie zmianami</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(341,6857,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Opis stanowiska<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Nasz klient to nowoczesna firma działająca w branży IT, specjalizująca się w systemach NMS/OSS, platformach systemowych oraz jako Software House. Oferuje szeroki zakres usług, od indywidualnych produktów po rozwiązania komercyjne i oparte na otwartym oprogramowaniu, wszystko dostosowane do specyficznych potrzeb klienta. Posiadają doświadczoną kadrę zarządzającą, która skupia ekspertów z wieloletnim doświadczeniem w projektowaniu, wdrażaniu, obsłudze i serwisowaniu zaawansowanych systemów teleinformatycznych. Obecnie poszukują utalentowanych specjalistów z branży IT, DevOps oraz programistów, którzy dołączą do ich zespołu w celu tworzenia i wdrażania innowacyjnego oprogramowania biznesowego. To doskonała okazja dla tych, którzy chcą pracować w dynamicznie rozwijającej się firmie, oferującej możliwości rozwoju i pracy nad projektami, które naprawdę mają znaczenie.</p> Java Full Stack Developer (Angular2+) <p><strong>Oferujemy:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>atrakcyjne wynagrodzenie w oparciu o umowę b2b</li>\n<li>pracę hybrydową (4 dni pracy zdalnej+1 dzień pracy w biurze klienta w Warszawie)</li>\n<li>udział w interesujących projektach</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Obowiązki:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>praca jako programista Full Stack w zespole Scrum / Agile,</li>\n<li>tworzenie oprogramowania i rozwiązań wspierających proces planowania i utrzymania sieci</li>\n<li>dbanie o jakość kodu (w tym kodu testowego) i całego produktu</li>\n<li>pisanie dokumentacji stworzonych rozwiązań</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Wymagania:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>minimum 3 lata doświadczenia na podobnym stanowisku</li>\n<li>kreatywność i nastawienie zespołowe</li>\n<li>dobra znajomość Java 8+</li>\n<li>znajomość JEE</li>\n<li>znajomość HTML i JavaScript,Boostrap, Angular 2+</li>\n<li>znajomość stosu technologicznego JAVA do tworzenia aplikacji webowych (JPA, Hibernate, Spring Boot)</li>\n<li>znajomość Jenkins</li>\n<li>podstawowa znajomość narzędzi testowych takich jak JMeter, TestNG, JUnit</li>\n<li>doświadczenie w pracy z Maven</li>\n<li>znajomość relacyjnych baz danych (Oracle, PostgreSQL) oraz zaawansowana znajomość SQL</li>\n<li>znajomość REST, Swagger</li>\n<li>znajomość architektury mikroserwisowej</li>\n<li>doświadczenie w praktycznym stosowaniu wzorców projektowych</li>\n<li>chęć ciągłego doskonalenia wiedzy i kwalifikacji</li>\n<li>dobra znajomość języka angielskiego</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Dodatkowe atuty:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>umiejętność programowania Python</li>\n<li>doświadczenie z BPMN (Kamunda),</li>\n<li>znajomość branży Telco (doświadczenie w pracy w telekomunikacji, znajomość TMF)</li>\n<li>znajomość systemów klasy CRM</li>\n<li>znajomość systemów klasy Order Management</li>\n<li>Billing</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(342,6858,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Opis stanowiska<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Nasz klient to innowacyjna firma technologiczna, która od 2025 roku specjalizuje się w rozwiązaniach związanych z chmurą obliczeniową, koncentrując się na platformie AWS. Dzięki bogatemu doświadczeniu w projektowaniu, budowie, wdrażaniu i utrzymaniu środowisk IT oraz aplikacji, zarówno w chmurze, jak i lokalnie, firma uznana jest za lidera w dziedzinie migracji do chmury, przetwarzania danych, sztucznej inteligencji, DevOps, optymalizacji chmury, cyberbezpieczeństwa oraz rozwoju aplikacji chmurowych. Zespół składa się z certyfikowanych ekspertów i partnerów, którzy posiadają kompetencje w kluczowych obszarach technologicznych, co pozwala na świadczenie usług na najwyższym poziomie. Firma współpracuje z klientami z różnych branż, pomagając im maksymalizować potencjał technologii chmurowych dla ich biznesu. Aktualnie poszukujemy utalentowanych specjalistów z doświadczeniem w technologiach chmurowych, którzy chcą dołączyć do naszego zespołu i wspierać nas w dostarczaniu innowacyjnych rozwiązań.</p> Senior Cloud Engineer - AWS <p><strong>Oferujemy:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Budżet szkoleniowy i sponsorowane certyfikaty AWS</li>\n<li>Płatny urlop, prywatna opieka medyczna, Multisport</li>\n<li>Elastyczny czas pracy, praca zdalna</li>\n<li>Darmowe lekcje angielskiego</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Obowiązki:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Projektowanie i implementacja architektur AWS (<strong>EC2, EKS, Lambda, RDS, S3, IAM, VPC, API Gateway, CloudWatch, Route 53</strong>)</li>\n<li>Tworzenie infrastruktury jako kod (<strong>Terraform, AWS CDK</strong>)</li>\n<li>Budowa i utrzymanie CI/CD (<strong>GitHub Actions, GitLab Pipelines, Jenkins, AWS CodePipeline</strong>)</li>\n<li>Tworzenie skryptów i automatyzacja z użyciem <strong>Python, TypeScript, Go, Bash</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Zarządzanie kontenerami (<strong>Docker, Kubernetes, Amazon ECS/EKS</strong>)</li>\n<li>Zapewnienie bezpieczeństwa (IAM policies, szyfrowanie, compliance, architektury HA)</li>\n<li>Monitoring i observability (<strong>CloudWatch, Prometheus, Grafana, ELK/EFK</strong>)</li>\n<li>Wsparcie techniczne, doradztwo i dzielenie się wiedzą z zespołem</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Wymagania:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Min. 4-5 lat doświadczenia w roli <strong>Cloud/DevOps/SRE</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Biegłość w usługach <strong>AWS</strong> i narzędziach IaC</li>\n<li>Doświadczenie w CI/CD, konteneryzacji i automatyzacji</li>\n<li>Znajomość praktyk bezpieczeństwa i projektowania sieci</li>\n<li>Bardzo dobra znajomość języka polskiego i angielskiego</li>\n<li>certyfikaty AWS</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(343,6859,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-h