2 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Our Client is a global leader in e-Health, operating for over 20 years, during which it has established cooperation with over 200 hospitals. The company provides comprehensive services and streamlines communication in the healthcare sector, enabling simple management of patient information while delivering highest quality healthcare services.</p> Delphi Programmer <p><strong>We offer:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Remote work</li>\n<li>Attractive remuneration based on an employment contract or b2b</li>\n<li>Stable employment in an international organization</li>\n<li>Work in an atmosphere of cooperation in a team, trust, mutual respect and help</li>\n<li>Possibility of gaining experience working with an Enterprise class system</li>\n<li>Work according to agile methodologies</li>\n<li>Attractive social package, flexible working hours</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Implementation, integration, testing and deployment of ERP class software</li>\n<li>Maintenance and development of proprietary software</li>\n<li>Designing of future functional requirements</li>\n<li>Creation and maintenance of technical documentation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>At least 3-year experience as a Delphi Programmer</li>\n<li>Knowledge of XML and ability to use Delphi</li>\n<li>Knowledge of SOAP and ability to create WebService in Deplhi</li>\n<li>Knowledge of version control systems SVN, GIT</li>\n<li>Good knowledge of SQL, with particular emphasis on functions in PostgreSQL 11 and 12</li>\n<li>Ability to design relational databases</li>\n<li>Ability to think analytically</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(641,7157,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Job description<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Our Client is a global leader in e-Health, operating for over 20 years, during which it has established cooperation with over 200 hospitals. The company provides comprehensive services and streamlines communication in the healthcare sector, enabling simple management of patient information while delivering highest quality healthcare services.</p> Delphi Programmer <p><strong>We offer:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Remote work</li>\n<li>Attractive remuneration based on an employment contract or b2b</li>\n<li>Stable employment in an international organization</li>\n<li>Work in an atmosphere of cooperation in a team, trust, mutual respect and help</li>\n<li>Possibility of gaining experience working with an Enterprise class system</li>\n<li>Work according to agile methodologies</li>\n<li>Attractive social package, flexible working hours</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Implementation, integration, testing and deployment of ERP class software</li>\n<li>Maintenance and development of proprietary software</li>\n<li>Designing of future functional requirements</li>\n<li>Creation and maintenance of technical documentation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>At least 3-year experience as a Delphi Programmer</li>\n<li>Knowledge of XML and ability to use Delphi</li>\n<li>Knowledge of SOAP and ability to create WebService in Deplhi</li>\n<li>Knowledge of version control systems SVN, GIT</li>\n<li>Good knowledge of SQL, with particular emphasis on functions in PostgreSQL 11 and 12</li>\n<li>Ability to design relational databases</li>\n<li>Ability to think analytically</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(642,7158,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Manage the maintenance of technical infrastructure</li>\n<li>Manage and maintain systems and applications</li>\n<li>Collaborate and build relationships with internal departments, both within T-Mobile Polska and Deutsche Telekom, to ensure continuity of cooperation at the systems and applications level</li>\n<li>Support the GCD Colleagues in their daily IT issues/challenges</li>\n<li>Support technical onboarding of the new colleagues</li>\n<li>Ensure operational continuity of technical infrastructure and applications</li>\n<li>Implement new technological solutions to improve efficiency and optimize operations</li>\n<li>Prepare cost estimates and participate in budget planning</li>\n<li>Monitor progress, report on implementation status, and ensure deadlines are met</li>\n<li>Willingness to learn new tools and applications and train employees in their use</li>\n<li>Knowledge (or willingness to learn) of basic health and safety principles to enable proper task execution</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(643,7159,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Join the team at Operational Services GmbH, within Deutsche Telekom Systems Solutions Slovakia, providing opportunities for German-speaking talents in Slovakia. OS is one of the leading ICT service providers in the German market and is considered the backbone of digitization in medium-sized companies. With almost 1,000 highly qualified employees, OS develops and operates the most modern IT systems for our customers, ensures long-term system support, and maintains the availability of critical business processes.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Design, develop, implement, and support ICT components, cloud solutions, and applications to deliver a high-quality product and service portfolio.</li>\n<li>Act as a senior technical expert and lead architect, responsible for the design, implementation, and operation of Microsoft and cloud-based solutions, ensuring stability, scalability, and efficiency.</li>\n<li>Perform, coordinate, and improve complex activities (3rd level environment) to provide IT services and supporting infrastructure, fulfilling relevant KPIs.</li>\n<li>Build, consult, and implement cloud architectures (public, private, hybrid, multi-cloud), with strong focus on Microsoft Azure and related technologies.</li>\n<li>Support migrations of IT infrastructures and software solutions to the Azure cloud and manage related customer projects.</li>\n<li>Design, develop, and implement architectures of services based on platform requirements, ensuring compliance with business needs and industry standards.</li>\n<li>Provide consulting and advisory services to customers, management, and project teams regarding IT, cloud, and DevOps architecture.</li>\n<li>Mentor and train co-workers to share expertise, spread knowledge, and build internal competencies.</li>\n<li>Research and adopt new technologies, processes, and methods for automation, optimization, and innovation.</li>\n<li>Manage relationships with key vendors, particularly Microsoft, to stay up to date on innovations, licensing, and best practices.</li>\n<li>Identify weaknesses in processes, propose improvements, and implement cost optimization and efficiency measures.</li>\n<li>Act as the key technical lead, coordinating activities across related technologies and multiple stakeholders.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4></h4></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(644,7160,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>In your role as a Senior Solution Architect, you will operate in a diverse environment and take on the following responsibilities\"</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Solution design: You are the contact person and consultant for the development of complex IT architectures and work closely with our customers and internal teams.</li>\n<li>Cost estimation: You calculate costs for highly complex solutions and support you with budget planning.</li>\n<li>System architecture: You design innovative and highly complex system architectures that define the future of our IT landscape.</li>\n<li>Technology roadmap: You are responsible for the strategic development of this and support in its implementation.</li>\n<li>Concepts: The creation of implementation and operating concepts rounds off your area of responsibility.</li>\n<li>Customer support: You support our SDM with existing customers and contribute to the further development of customer solutions.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(645,7161,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Experienced Flight Operations Fleet Support Engineer</h4>\n\n<p><strong>Company:</strong>\nBoeing Poland sp. z o.o. EFS</p>\n\n<p>Boeing Poland is seeking an Experienced Flight Operations Fleet Support Engineer to join our Flight Operations – Customer Support team in Rzeszow, Poland.</p>\n\n<p>The successful candidate is a qualified and highly motivated individual who will support safe, efficient, and compliant flight operations of the Global Boeing fleet. As part of the Flight Operations – Customer Support team you will manage complex work in a fast paced and multifaceted environment and have the opportunity to work with both internal and external stakeholders to deliver world class support to our airline customers and the flying public.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Position Responsibilities:</strong>\n* Respond to customer inquiries on subjects including Master Minimum Equipment List (MMEL) and Dispatch Deviation Guide (DDG), Flight Crew Procedures (FCOM/QRH, FCTM), and ferry flight requests\n* Provide on and off hours support to Boeing’s 24-hour Operations Center for ferry flight requests and other time-critical customer inquiries related to flight operations\n* Use resourcefulness to conduct fast-paced, high-level research into customer inquiries\n* Coordinate with and integrate engineering teams and technical pilots to develop detailed responses\n* Document work with good technical details so that others can use this information to efficiently develop similar future customer responses\n* Continually champion improvements to technologies, tools, and processes to enhance technological readiness and reduce cycle time and cost\n* Assist in training others in work processes and work products</p>\n\n<p>This position is expected to be 100% onsite. The selected candidate will be required to work onsite at Rzeszow.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(646,7162,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior UI/UX Designer</h4>\n\n<p>Elsewhere Entertainment is looking for a Senior UI/UX Designer to join the development of a new IP. </p>\n\n<p>Join us in shaping experiences where UI design not only complements gameplay but transforms it. This position blends the creative and functional aspects of UI design, focusing on developing intuitive, player-centric interfaces that elevate the player experience.</p>\n\n<p><strong>You’ll help us by…</strong> </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Designing UI solutions—player flows, wireframes, and interactive prototypes—that balance form and function, in close collaboration with game designers and artists.</li>\n<li>Pioneering new interaction design approaches to elevate the player experience.</li>\n<li>Implementing UI in partnership with engineering teams.</li>\n<li>Creating and maintaining design documentation and style guides to ensure clear, consistent team communication.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Our World</strong> </p>\n\n<p>At Activision, we strive to create the most iconic brands in gaming and entertainment. We’re driven by our mission to deliver unrivaled gaming experiences for the world to enjoy, together. We are home to some of the most beloved entertainment franchises including Call of Duty®, Crash Bandicoot™, Tony Hawk’s™ Pro Skater™, and Guitar Hero®. As a leading worldwide developer, publisher and distributor of interactive entertainment and products, our “press start” is simple: delight hundreds of millions of players around the world with innovative, fun, thrilling, and engaging entertainment experiences. </p>\n\n<p>We’re not just looking back at our decades-long legacy; we’re forging ahead to keep advancing gameplay with some of the most popular titles and sophisticated technology in the world. We have bold ambitions to create the most inclusive company as we know our success comes from the passionate, creative, and diverse teams within our organization. </p>\n\n<p>We’re in the business of delivering fun and unforgettable entertainment for our player community to enjoy. And our future opportunities have never been greater — this could be your opportunity to level up.</p>\n\n<p>Ready to Activate Your Future? </p>\n\n elsewhere</div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(647,7163,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior Sales Support Specialist | Global Marketing &amp; Sales</h4>\n\n<p>Are you ready to play a pivotal role in driving global account success? In this dynamic position, as a member of Hitachi’s Global Marketing &amp; Sales (GM&amp;S) team, you’ll provide strategic, operational, and analytical support to Global Account Support Managers and the Sales Process Manager. You’ll be at the heart of opportunity governance, delivery coordination, and stakeholder engagement, ensuring process excellence across global accounts and business units. Your contribution will help shape account planning and enhance the effectiveness of sales processes.</p>\n\n<p>You’ll be the go-to person for coordinating account planning workshops, managing logistics, and ensuring follow-up actions are completed. Working closely with market intelligence and segment teams, you’ll help develop account plans and build player maps to understand customer decision-making environments. Your role also involves acting as a key liaison between Business Units, Service Providers, and Account Teams to ensure alignment and value delivery.</p>\n\n<p>Collaboration is central to this role. You’ll represent Global Account Managers in internal forums, support training and enablement sessions, and contribute to the deployment of standardized sales processes. By tracking performance metrics and preparing insightful reports, you’ll help drive continuous improvement. If you thrive in a fast-paced, global environment and enjoy making an impact through structured coordination and strategic insight, this is the role for you.</p>\n\n<h4>About GM&amp;S</h4>\n\n<p>Hitachi is transforming to ensure sustainable growth and profitability in digital and green sectors by establishing a customer-centric business model. Part of this transformation is setting up global account management to better understand customer needs and increase Hitachi\'s market share.</p>\n\n<p>This transformation is led by GM&amp;S, whose vision is to become our customers’ preferred partner of choice for their most critical challenges by providing impactful, sustainable solutions, delivered by experts spanning the full breadth of Hitachi’s portfolio.</p>\n\n<h4>What you\'ll be doing</h4>\n\n Opportunity Governance &amp; Delivery Support \n\n<ul>\n<li>Govern opportunity lifecycle through structured tracking, documentation, and follow-up actions.</li>\n<li>Coordinate with GAMs, BUs, and service providers to ensure timely delivery and value realization.</li>\n<li>Support operational requirements and add value through proactive engagement and action tracking.</li>\n</ul>\n\n Account Planning &amp; Workshop Administration \n\n<ul>\n<li>Support the execution of Account Planning Workshops, including logistics, documentation, and post-work-shop follow-up.</li>\n<li>Contribute to the development of account plans by working closely with market intelligence, segment, and reference cases development in coordination with associated functions, consultants and business.</li>\n<li>Assist in building and maintaining player maps to understand customer decision-making environments.</li>\n</ul>\n\n Market Intelligence &amp; Core Technologies \n\n<ul>\n<li>Provide actionable intelligence to account teams to refine strategies and identify growth opportunities, by working closely with segment teams and consultants.</li>\n</ul>\n\n Sales Process Support &amp; Reporting \n\n<ul>\n<li>Support the deployment and monitoring of standardized sales processes and workflows.</li>\n<li>Assist in tracking performance metrics and preparing dashboards and reports for management review.</li>\n<li>Ensure adherence to governance frameworks and process documentation standards.</li>\n</ul>\n\n Training, Meetings &amp; Enablement \n\n<ul>\n<li>Coordinate and support training programs for BU teams on tools, processes, and account strategies.</li>\n<li>Facilitate cadence meetings and enablement sessions to ensure alignment and progress tracking.</li>\n<li>Ad hoc support requests from Account Support Manager, to manage and deliver.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>About Hitachi</h4>\n\n<p>Since its founding in 1910, Hitachi has supported the development of society and the improvement of people\'s lives. Throughout the world, Hitachi Group employees exemplify outstanding teamwork that transcends the boundaries of geographical regions and business fields. Together, we share the Hitachi group identity and put it into practice worldwide.</p>\n\n<p>With a mission to deliver the best experience to employees and customers, you will be joining a global team setting the standard for excellence and innovation in Marketing and Sales (M&amp;S).</p>\n\n<p>In pursuit of sustainable growth and profitability in the digital and green sectors, the Global Marketing &amp; Sales transformation team, established in 2022, seeks to position Hitachi as a trusted partner for its customers.</p>\n\n<h4>Our values</h4>\n\n<p>We are proud of Japanese heritage, with our values expressed through the Hitachi Spirit:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Wa</strong> – Harmony, Trust, Respect</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Makoto</strong> – Sincerity, Fairness, Honesty, Integrity</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Kaitakusha-Seishin</strong> – Pioneering Spirit, Challenge</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If, like us, you’re motivated by delivering first class services, thrive in a fast paced and supportive environment and want to help Hitachi drive social innovation, we’d love to hear from you.</p>\n\n<p>Fostering innovation through diverse perspectives</p>\n\n<p>Hitachi is a global company operating across a wide range of industries and regions. One of the things that sets Hitachi apart is the diversity of our business and people, which drives our innovation and growth.</p>\n\n<p>We are committed to building an inclusive culture based on mutual respect and merit-based systems. We believe that when people feel valued, heard, and safe to express themselves, they do their best work.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(648,7164,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>We are looking for an experienced and forward-thinking E2E Solution Architect to help shape the future of IoT solutions in the telecommunications space. This role is for innovators, problem-solvers, and team players who want to design and deliver solutions that connect people, devices, and industries in new and impactful ways.</p>\n<p>Our team provides end-to-end mobile network engineering for the Deutsche Telekom Group, covering core, transport, and RAN domains, as well as driving business model innovation. We lead the engineering work that powers the launch of new IoT services worldwide. You’ll be based in Warsaw with occasional travel to Germany (up to 10%).</p>\n<p>As a member of the IoT Solution Design Team, you may also act as the technical representative in RFQs where Deutsche Telekom participates as a supplier—assessing feasibility, coordinating technical inputs from various teams, and supporting Proofs of Concept. You will work closely with customers, business teams, sales, and technology groups to fully understand requirements and deliver optimal solution designs.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop end-to-end solution architectures and high-level designs (HLD) for customer IoT demands</li>\n<li>Evaluate solutions during the demand management or RFQ phases</li>\n<li>Estimate required resources and costs for proposed solutions</li>\n<li>Conduct feasibility analyses for new requests</li>\n<li>Plan budgets for new solutions</li>\n<li>Provide guidance on the effective use of solutions and architectures to meet business outcomes and comply with architecture guidelines</li>\n<li>Collaborate with stakeholders across product, sales, network planning, and operations to ensure successful delivery</li>\n<li>Translate business and product requirements into technical solutions</li>\n<li>Work with other architects to ensure alignment and delivery across programs and projects</li>\n<li>Support contract preparation and create high-quality technical documentation</li>\n</ul>\n<h4></h4></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(649,7165,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>As part of the Global Service Management tower, we design and deliver a comprehensive approach to managing IT services and processes across an entire organization on a global scale. This includes establishing standardised processes and practices to ensure consistent service delivery across locations.</p>\n<p>The IT Service Manager will play a crucial role in the Service Reporting &amp; Measurement area, ensuring consistent, reliable, and automated measurement and reporting on IT service performance. The role bridges ITIL-based Service Management practices with technical data analysis, transforming raw operational data into actionable insights that support decision-making, KPI management, and Service Level Agreement (SLA) performance tracking.</p>\n<p><strong>How you will get the job done</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>developing and maintaining standard definitions of metrics and metadata (sources, frequency, accuracy)</li>\n<li>ensuring consistency across all reported metrics and indicators</li>\n<li>integrating data from systems such as monitoring, CMDB, ticketing, APM, log management, and others</li>\n<li>transforming raw technical data into meaningful management information (ETL, data normalization, transformation)</li>\n<li>designing and automating KPI/SLA reports, service status dashboards, etc.</li>\n<li>maintaining and developing reporting tools (e.g., ServiceNow modules or other required components)</li>\n<li>supporting Continual Improvement (CSI) through data-driven insights and analyses</li>\n<li>recommending automation and standardization opportunities for data collection and reporting</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(650,7166,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p><strong>THE WORK:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be responsible for designing business processes or solutions that support clients and configuring systems according to client requirements.</li>\n<li>Prepare and maintain project documentation, including creating and updating test scenarios and performing manual system testing.</li>\n<li>Develop presentations and training materials for end users and supporting the mapping and modeling of business processes.</li>\n<li>Act as a liaison between clients and IT teams, support analysts and consultants in daily project operations.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with experienced team members to gain knowledge and continuously improve your skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Flexible: The work location for this role may include a mix of working remotely, onsite at a client or in an Accenture office - depending on specific project circumstances.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(651,7167,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you’d like, where you’ll be supported and inspired by a collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you’ll be able to reimagine what’s possible. Join us and help the world’s leading organizations unlock the value of technology and build a more sustainable, more inclusive world.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Defining and ensuring a comprehensive and coherent view across Business, Information, Systems and Technology</li>\n<li>Going beyond designing IT systems to deliver business change while securing sustainability</li>\n<li>Provide top level business and technology architecture consultancy services to our clients</li>\n<li>Provide input to the design of ServiceNow based ITSM solutions as a recognized Architect or Design Authority</li>\n<li>Provide input to bids and assist in presenting proposals to potential clients</li>\n<li>Lead or support creation of innovative digital offers as complete enterprise solutions</li>\n<li>Support implementation programs for complex enterprise scale solutions</li>\n<li>Provide input to and/or create specialist points of view for the market and where appropriate present at industry events</li>\n<li>Work with: Customer Managers, Architects, Subject Matter Experts, Solution Designers and senior level representatives on client side</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(652,7168,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you’d like, where you’ll be supported and inspired by a collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you’ll be able to reimagine what’s possible. Join us and help the world’s leading organizations unlock the value of technology and build a more sustainable, more inclusive world.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR ROLE:</strong></h4>\n<p>You will start your journey with ServiceNow performing simpler task to help experts deliver project. This will consist of smaller configuration and customization activities to help you get used to the platform and our way of working. After that you will move to more complicated/independent tasks and specific module specialization.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Taking part in ServiceNow testing, administration and development activities,</li>\n<li>Working directly with the client (customer mindset),</li>\n<li>Creating and updating documentation and procedures,</li>\n<li>Expanding ServiceNow knowledge through self-paced trainings,</li>\n<li>Collaborating with Senior Developers and Architects.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(653,7169,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you’d like, where you’ll be supported and inspired by a collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you’ll be able to reimagine what’s possible. Join us and help the world’s leading organizations unlock the value of technology and build a more sustainable, more inclusive world.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<p>We are seeking a&nbsp;motivated&nbsp;Squad Lead to join our team. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in team leadership, project management, and excellent communication skills. As a Squad Lead, you will be&nbsp;responsible&nbsp;for guiding your squad to success, ensuring projects are completed on time and to the highest standards<strong>.</strong></p>\n<p><strong><span>﻿</span></strong></p>\n<h4><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></h4>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<strong>Team Leadership</strong>: Guide and motivate technical team, ensuring everyone is aligned with the squad\'s objectives. Act as a promoter: develop career paths in collaboration with team members,&nbsp;responsible&nbsp;for identification, assessment and alignment of the key competencies required to be successful on the available career paths.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Communication</strong>: Act as the main point of contact between the squad and other stakeholders, facilitating clear and effective communication.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Performance Monitoring</strong>: Track the squad\'s performance, providing feedback and support to help team members improve and succeed.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Problem-Solving</strong>: Address any issues or obstacles that arise, helping the team to find solutions and maintain progress.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Project Management</strong>: Ensure the monitoring of project status, share business constraints,&nbsp;validate&nbsp;transition to operation</li>\n</ol></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(654,7170,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you’d like, where you’ll be supported and inspired by a collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you’ll be able to reimagine what’s possible. Join us and help the world’s leading organizations unlock the value of technology and build a more sustainable, more inclusive world.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR ROLE:</strong></h4>\n<p>The Cloud Platform Engineer is a permanent role in support of CIS delivery tools responsible for deployment of environments and services, real-time monitoring, alerting, automation, Service Management and Reporting of the enterprise infrastructure (Network, Servers, Storage, Databases, etc.) and applications for the CIS managed services offering. This role is positioned in the Deploy &amp; Run organization and works closely with Design &amp; Build teams adopting, applying standard designs in secure/sovereign client environments and supporting platform run.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Maintaining cloud services according to best practices and ensuring they are deployed correctly in the cloud environment whilst championing automation</li>\n<li>Working on large scale, technically challenging projects</li>\n<li>Using open-source technology, CI/CD, and modern software architectures such as microservices, to name but a few</li>\n<li>Supporting and improving business capabilities, processes, and applications in the cloud</li>\n<li>Building supportable, sustainable, and reliable services</li>\n<li>Defining and maintaining technical designs according to Cloud best practices</li>\n<li>Championing for agile delivery automation</li>\n<li>Consistently improving by expanding your knowledge, relationships, and certifications with our Cloud partners - which will be fully supported</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(655,7171,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you’d like, where you’ll be supported and inspired by a collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you’ll be able to reimagine what’s possible. Join us and help the world’s leading organizations unlock the value of technology and build a more sustainable, more inclusive world.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR ROLE:</strong></h4>\n<p>The Cloud Platform Architect is a permanent role in support of CIS delivery tools responsible for the detailed technical design of real-time monitoring, alerting, automation, Service Management and Reporting of the enterprise infrastructure (Network, Servers, Storage, Databases, etc.) and applications for the CIS managed services offering. This role is positioned in the Deploy &amp; Run organization and works closely with Design &amp; Build teams adopting, applying standard designs in secure/sovereign client environments and supporting platform run.</p>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Defining and ensuring a comprehensive and coherent view across Business, Information, Systems and Technology</li>\n<li>Being at front to help our clients create the sustainable, inclusive future we all want and need</li>\n<li>Guide and mentor engineering teams in cloud and data best practices</li>\n<li>Provide input to the design of Container based solutions as a recognized Architect or Design Authority</li>\n<li>Lead or support creation of innovative digital offers as complete enterprise solutions.</li>\n<li>Support implementation programs for complex enterprise scale solutions</li>\n<li>Bring thought leadership and innovative solution ideas to existing clients and bids alike</li>\n<li>Work with Customer Managers, Architects, Subject Matter Experts, Solution Designers</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(656,7172,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you’d like, where you’ll be supported and inspired by a collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you’ll be able to reimagine what’s possible. Join us and help the world’s leading organizations unlock the value of technology and build a more sustainable, more inclusive world.</p>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Design, develop, and maintain integrations using iPaaS (Integration Platform as a Service) and xPaaS (Extended Platform as a Service) solutions.</li>\n<li>Build and optimize data flows, APIs, and application integrations across cloud and on-premises systems.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with enterprise architects and business stakeholders to understand integration requirements.</li>\n<li>Implement best practices for API management, event-driven architectures, and workflow automation.</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot integration issues and ensure high availability, performance, and security.</li>\n<li>Contribute to automation, monitoring, and continuous improvement of integration processes.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(657,7173,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4><strong>YOUR ROLE:</strong></h4>\n<p>We are looking for a skilled Ansible Engineer to join our platform support team. The ideal candidate will have hands-on experience with configuration management, infrastructure automation, and CI/CD pipelines. You will be responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining automated workflows using Ansible and supporting technologies.</p>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Develop, maintain, and optimize Ansible playbooks, roles, and collections for automated configuration management.</li>\n<li>Implement and maintain CI/CD pipelines using GitHub Actions.</li>\n<li>Manage and collaborate on code repositories using GitHub, including version control, branching strategies, and pull request workflows.</li>\n<li>Create and maintain infrastructure as code using Terraform and Terragrunt.</li>\n<li>Write and execute automated tests for Ansible roles and playbooks using Molecule.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with development and operations teams to streamline deployment processes and ensure reliable, scalable infrastructure.</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot and resolve issues in existing automation workflows and infrastructure.</li>\n<li>Document processes, configurations, and workflows to ensure maintainability and knowledge sharing.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(658,7174,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you’d like, where you’ll be supported and inspired by a collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you’ll be able to reimagine what’s possible. Join us and help the world’s leading organizations unlock the value of technology and build a more sustainable, more inclusive world.</p>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<p>As a Lead Architects you will define and ensure a comprehensive and coherent view across Business, Information, Systems and Technology. It goes beyond designing IT&nbsp;systems&nbsp;to deliver business change, which may also be supported and enabled by IT.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(659,7175,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Choosing Capgemini means choosing a company where you will be empowered to shape your career in the way you’d like, where you’ll be supported and inspired by a collaborative community of colleagues around the world, and where you’ll be able to reimagine what’s possible. Join us and help the world’s leading organizations unlock the value of technology and build a more sustainable, more inclusive world.</p>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Day to day management of enterprise class&nbsp;storage&nbsp;environments,</li>\n<li>Provide top level technology consultancy services to our clients and other technical teams,</li>\n<li>Work with Architects, Subject Matter Experts, Solution Designers and engineers on both Capgemini and customer side.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(660,7176,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p><strong>Project Manager</strong>&nbsp;– Ensure client needs are met by overseeing the design, development, implementation, and delivery of IT solutions—including infrastructure services, cloud computing, migrations, transitions, tool implementations, and cybersecurity—in response to approved service requests. Project Managers are responsible for the overall project plan, budget, structure, schedule, and staffing requirements within the delivery organization.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>End-to-end IT projects and programs management such as cloud migrations/ cloud implementations/ transformations/ new tools implementation, infrastructure assessments/security/integrations/data centers migrations,</li>\n<li>Full project documentation management (project charter, project planning, risks/issues/dependencies, project changes, financial management, reporting),</li>\n<li>International cooperation with customers, project teams, third parties,</li>\n<li>Mentoring and knowledge sharing.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(661,7177,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior AI/ML Engineer</h4>\n\n<p>We are looking for a Senior AI/ML Engineer to join the AI Center of Excellence (CoE) in ROCKWOOL in Poznan. In this job, you can expect to travel about 10% of the time in support of global projects.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Ready to help build a better future for generations to come?</strong></p>\n\n<p>In an ever-changing, fast paced world, we owe it to ourselves and our future generations to live life responsibly. At ROCKWOOL, we work relentlessly to enrich modern living through our innovative stone wool solutions.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Your future team</strong></p>\n\n<p>We have recently started a journey towards using AI at scale, general digitalization, automation and better use of data – and this is where your abilities come into play. You will join the AI CoE team and work at the forefront of AI and machine learning. This role reports to the Team Lead of the AI CoE based in Poland with most of the team in Poznan office. You will work closely with teams from Denmark, Poland and Malaysia and be an integral part of a larger global Data &amp; AI team.</p>\n\n<p><strong>What you will be doing</strong></p>\n\n<p>We are seeking a talented and experienced Senior AI/ML Engineer with Machine Learning, Generative AI and software development experience. In this role, you will work closely with Data Scientists, ML engineers, Data Engineers and cross-functional stakeholders to design, develop and deploy custom AI products and analytics solutions at ROCKWOOL. You will be part of a growing team that focuses on developing custom AI products &amp; LLM solutions. The role requires a blend of technical and communication skills. More concretely, you will have the following responsibilities:</p>\n\n<p>Develop and deploy AI products &amp; applications</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use various modern technologies, tools and packages such Azure OpenAI, LLMs, vector databases, Langchain etc. to engineer AI products at scale</li>\n<li>Maintain custom GenAI products such as in house developed LLM solution.</li>\n<li>Develop and maintain various LLM APIs and backend functionality that supports custom AI products</li>\n<li>Use cloud technologies such as Azure, OpenShift, VertexAI, etc. to support the ML Engineer by contributing to the development of our core AI platform</li>\n<li>Automate infrastructure provisioning (IaC) and CI/CD processes for custom AI workloads</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Follow Machine Learning processes and Best Practices</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Develop and maintain best practices and standards for carrying out AI based projects</li>\n<li>Collaboration with the team in identifying areas for improvement and recommend strategies to enhance the data science function in our organization</li>\n<li>Ensure continuous learning and development</li>\n<li>Stay up to date with the latest developments in AI to ensure that our practices are cutting-edge</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Who we are</strong></p>\n\n<p>We are the world leader in stone wool solutions. Founded in 1937 in Denmark, we transform volcanic rock into safe, sustainable products that help people and communities thrive. We are a global company with more than 12,000 employees, located in 40+ countries with 51 manufacturing facilities, all focused on one common purpose – to release the natural power of stone to enrich modern living.</p>\n\n<p>Sustainability is central to our business strategy. ROCKWOOL was one of the first companies to commit to actively contributing to the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDG’s) framework and are actively committed to 11 SDGs, including SDG 14, Life Below Water. Through our partnership with the One Ocean Foundation and in connection with our sponsorship of the Denmark SailGP team, we will help raise awareness around ocean health challenges in an effort to accelerate solutions to protect it.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Diverse and Inclusive Culture</strong></p>\n\n<p>We want all our people to feel valued, respected, included and heard. We employ 79 different nationalities worldwide and are committed to providing equal opportunities to all employees, promote diversity, and work against all forms of discrimination among ROCKWOOL employees.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(662,7178,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Data Analyst</h4>\n\n<p>Hello, we\'re IG Group. We are a publicly-traded FTSE250 FinTech company who run mobile, web and desktop platforms that help our clients trade stocks &amp; shares, leveraged products, Futures &amp; Options and Crypto.</p>\n\n<p>We are ambitious. Over 340,000 people already use our platforms. We\'re global with offices in 18 countries and products in 16 regions. We\'re hungry to move faster, ship better product for our customers and grow our user base. We believe in high autonomy, and we want people who are looking to do things differently in order to create better experiences for our customers.</p>\n\n<p>We work in cross-functional teams and are laser focused on increasing the number of active clients we serve to drive sustainable growth.</p>\n\n Your role in the Team\'s Success \n\n<p>We are seeking a Data Analyst to join our cross-functional Insight &amp; Analytics Team at IG Europe.</p>\n\n<p>The ideal candidate will help bridge the gap between raw data and strategic decision-making, working closely with Marketing, Product, Sales, Trading, Legal, and Compliance departments in the Europe Division.</p>\n\n<p>You\'ll help uncover opportunities for growth and operational efficiency while providing actionable insights to stakeholders at all levels of the organization.</p>\n\n What you\'ll do \n\n<ul>\n<li>Extract data from multiple database sources using SQL queries</li>\n<li>Transform and clean data using SQL, Python, or Excel to ensure accuracy and usability</li>\n<li>Analyse Google Analytics (GA) data to track website performance, user platform behaviour, and conversion metrics</li>\n<li>Build and maintain dashboards in Looker or Tableau that track KPIs and campaign performance</li>\n<li>Perform analyses to identify trends, opportunities, and areas for optimization</li>\n<li>Generate clear, actionable insights and recommendations for stakeholders</li>\n<li>Communicate findings through presentations, reports, emails, and interactive dashboards</li>\n<li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business needs, market and competitive landscape to develop relevant analyses.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(663,7179,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior Product Designer</h4>\n\n<p><strong>Purpose of the Role:</strong>\nTo design best-in-class experiences of merchants and users in all customer journeys.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities and Key Activities:</strong>\nDesigning user experience features and user flows, and testing them heavily with end users\nPlanning, supervising and conducting user research (qualitative and quantitative)\nTransforming ideas into products of user-friendly interfaces and communication\nCreating wireframes, mockups and clickable prototypes for desktop and mobile screens\nBringing ideas to improve the experience with PayU products and services\nMaintaining the highest standards of design and applying the best practice\nCooperating with colleagues from different teams in and outside the region: product, development, customer support, marketing, legal, treasury, sales, external partners\nOther UX-related tasks requested by direct manager</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(664,7180,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Who we are</h4>\n\n<p>Samsara (NYSE: IOT) is the pioneer of the Connected Operations™ Cloud, which is a platform that enables organizations that depend on physical operations to harness Internet of Things (IoT) data to develop actionable insights and improve their operations. At Samsara, we are helping improve the safety, efficiency and sustainability of the physical operations that power our global economy. Representing more than 40% of global GDP, these industries are the infrastructure of our planet, including agriculture, construction, field services, transportation, and manufacturing — and we are excited to help digitally transform their operations at scale.</p>\n\n<p>Working at Samsara means you’ll help define the future of physical operations and be on a team that’s shaping an exciting array of product solutions, including Video-Based Safety, Vehicle Telematics, Apps and Driver Workflows, and Equipment Monitoring. As part of a recently public company, you’ll have the autonomy and support to make an impact as we build for the long term.</p>\n\n<h4>About the role:</h4>\n\n<p>Samsara’s Release Management team is responsible for how features are created, gated, and delivered to both internal stakeholders and external customers.</p>\n\n<p>We build the systems and tooling that product managers and engineers use to move features through their lifecycle from internal visibility to beta, early adopters, and general availability (GA). We also power the customer-facing release management experience, where each customer can view available features, discover new capabilities, opt-in and self-serve access to early releases.</p>\n\n<p>Our work spans features and feature flag management, feature gating, and the infrastructure that ensures features are launched safely, reliably, and with the right visibility for every audience.</p>\n\n<p>As a Senior Full-Stack Engineer on the Release Management team, you will design and build the internal tools and customer-facing experiences that make feature lifecycles safe, scalable, and transparent. You will collaborate across product and engineering teams to ensure features are discoverable, gated appropriately, and delivered with minimal risk, while also shaping how customers interact with and adopt new features.</p>\n\n<p>We build with Golang on the backend and React on the frontend, but what matters most is your experience working across the full stack.</p>\n\n<p>This is a remote position open to candidates residing in the UK or Poland.</p>\n\n<h4>In this role, you will:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Lead the design and development of internal and customer-facing systems that power feature visibility, gating, and lifecycle progression.</li>\n<li>Own and evolve the architecture of multiple services that underpin release management, balancing near-term delivery with long-term scalability</li>\n<li>Work with data and storage systems to ensure release states, feature flags, and customer-facing visibility are tracked and reliable at scale.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with product managers and engineering leadership to influence roadmaps and set multi-quarter plans for release lifecycle tooling.</li>\n<li>Drive cross-team initiatives that improve feature discoverability, adoption, and reliability for customers.</li>\n<li>Mentor and guide engineers across the team, raising the bar on technical design, execution, and code quality.</li>\n<li>Champion, role model, and embed Samsara’s cultural principles (Focus on Customer Success, Build for the Long Term, Adopt a Growth Mindset, Be Inclusive, Win as a Team) as we scale globally and across new offices</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(665,7181,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Join Vonage and help us innovate cloud communications for businesses worldwide!</h4>\n\n<p>As an emerging leader in the $10B+ communications API market, we empower global brands to connect better with their customers, employees, and partners through transformative communications experiences. For example, Vonage API solutions empower organizations to build their custom omnichannel communications structure. This allows them to reach and engage customers on their preferred schedule and channel — including voice, video, and messaging. Think of a rideshare service instantly connecting with customers, hospital staff conducting remote monitoring, customers verifying their identity before completing a purchase, AI virtual agents servicing customers around the clock, and much more.</p>\n\n<h4>Why this role matters</h4>\n\n<p>Developers rely on our Client SDKs to deliver seamless video streaming experiences across web and mobile applications. As Product Manager for Client Video Streaming, you’ll own the vision and execution for client SDKs, API usability, and streaming performance. The role is a great fit for a product manager with a background in software development, who is looking to guide product capabilities that directly impact developer adoption and customer success.</p>\n\n<h4>What you will do</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Define and manage the product roadmap for Client SDKs (JavaScript, iOS, Android) and media streaming capabilities.</li>\n<li>Partner with engineering to prioritize features, resolve technical trade-offs, and ensure developer-first product design.</li>\n<li>Drive adoption of client-side AI capabilities, including live captions and intelligent media enhancements.</li>\n<li>Lead initiatives to improve video/audio streaming quality, latency, and performance.</li>\n<li>Conduct market and competitive analysis to identify trends, portfolio gaps and new product opportunities to guide differentiation.</li>\n<li>Drive global cross-functional teams including engineering, PM, marketing, customer success to develop new video product offerings</li>\n<li>Serve as the voice of the developer, collaborating with Developer Relations and Marketing to drive product adoption.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Who we are:</h4>\n\n<p>Vonage is a global cloud communications leader. And your talent will further help brands - such as Airbnb, Viber, WhatsApp, and Snapchat - accelerate their digital transformation through our fully programmable-based unified communications, contact center solutions, and communications APIs. Ready to innovate? Then join us today.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(666,7182,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Staff Software Engineer</h4>\n\n<p>At Qualtrics, we create software the world’s best brands use to deliver exceptional frontline experiences, build high-performing teams, and design products people love. But we are more than a platform—we are the creators and stewards of the Experience Management category serving over 18K clients globally. Building a category takes grit, determination, and a disdain for convention—but most of all it requires close-knit, high-functioning teams with an unwavering dedication to serving our customers.</p>\n\n<p>When you join one of our teams, you’ll be part of a nimble group that’s empowered to set aggressive goals and move fast to achieve them. Strategic risks are encouraged and complex problems are solved together, by passing the microphone and iterating until the best solution comes to light. You won’t have to look to find growth opportunities—ready or not, they’ll find you. From retail to government to healthcare, we’re on a mission to bring humanity, connection, and empathy back to business. Join over 5,000 people across the globe who think that’s work worth doing.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Why We Have This Role</strong></p>\n\n<p>Our team is a collection of extremely passionate engineers who are riding the cutting edge of cloud computing and web scalability. We organize and sort terabytes of data and develop solutions used by millions of users every day. We design tools that make sophisticated research simple. Our teams are empowered to choose technologies that are best to solve each problem. In our collaborative culture, you find plenty of opportunities to impact our full-stack product; from Web &amp; mobile UI to data visualization &amp; analysis to microservices APIs to data storage &amp; processing.</p>\n\n<p><strong>How You’ll Find Success</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Actively participate in agile practices, collaborating closely with cross-functional teams to iteratively design, develop, and deploy scalable software solutions that meet evolving business needs.</li>\n<li>Own the quality of the codebase by implementing best practices in testing and code review, ensuring that all solutions are not only performant but also maintainable and robust in the face of rapid growth.</li>\n<li>Leverage your creativity and problem-solving skills to architect elegant, straightforward solutions that effectively address complex scalability challenges, facilitating long-term success for the platform.</li>\n<li>Provide guidance and support to junior engineers, fostering a culture of learning and innovation within the team. Share knowledge about system design and best practices to empower others and elevate team performance.</li>\n<li>Stay up-to-date with the latest industry trends and technologies, actively seeking opportunities for process improvements and enhancements that can lead to more efficient development workflows and higher-quality deliverables.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>How You’ll Grow</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Take on challenging assignments that have a direct impact on the company\'s success, allowing you to hone your technical skills while contributing to meaningful outcomes in a rapidly evolving environment.</li>\n<li>Gain hands-on experience with the latest tools and technologies in the industry, broadening your skill set and keeping your expertise at the forefront of software engineering trends.</li>\n<li>Work alongside a diverse group of like-minded engineers and thought leaders who are passionate about technology, fostering an environment of knowledge exchange that encourages personal and professional development.</li>\n<li>Improve your troubleshooting capabilities by tackling complex problems on a daily basis, enabling you to build resilience, adaptability, and innovative thinking in fast-paced, dynamic situation</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Things You’ll Do</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Develop scalable, fast, robust, and simple web-based solutions to solve complex business problems</li>\n<li>Implement new features and optimize existing ones to drive maximum performance</li>\n<li>Work closely with, and incorporate feedback from other engineers, tech-ops, and product managers</li>\n<li>Attend daily stand-up meetings, collaborate with your peers, prioritize features, and work with a sense of urgency to deliver value to your customers</li>\n<li>Mentor junior engineers and participate in code reviews to foster a culture of continuous improvement and knowledge sharing within the team.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>What You Should Know About This Team</strong></p>\n\n<p>With millions of responses per day and a goal to grow their data platform 10x over the next year, the Qualtrics engineers are tackling interesting challenges across the stack. As a team we\'ll build the next industry-leading XM Platform - helping every business to become more customer-centric. We will not only shape our product, but improve the direction of the companies that use our platform through our choices. Come help us change the world!</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(667,7183,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About us</h4>\n\n<p>At Auctane, we are united by a passion to help sellers — wherever they are, however they operate — fulfill the promises they make to consumers. The Auctane mission is to fuel commerce through exceptional delivery. We make it possible for businesses to meet the ever rising expectations of their customers, and we make the world smaller and more accessible to consumers everywhere. Auctane brands enable hundreds of thousands of merchants to annually deliver billions of products — over $200 billion worth — to customers around the globe. And Auctane is just getting started.\nAuctane is a team of shipping and software experts with a passion for helping merchants move their ideas, dreams and innovations around the globe. The Auctane family includes ShipStation, ShipWorks, ShipEngine, ShippingEasy, Stamps, Endicia, Metapack, GlobalPost, and Packlink. Our partners include Amazon, UPS, USPS, eBay, BigCommerce, Shopify, WooCommerce, and Walmart.</p>\n\n<h4>About the role</h4>\n\n<p>As a Software Mobile Engineer, you will design, develop, and maintain complex software components that align with business and technical requirements. You will take ownership of feature implementation, troubleshoot technical challenges, and collaborate with cross-functional teams to deliver scalable solutions. Your role will involve contributing to technical discussions, refining best practices, and supporting junior engineers through code reviews and knowledge sharing. Your expertise in programming and software engineering will be essential for achieving project goals and ensuring the delivery of high-quality products.</p>\n\n<h4>What will you be doing?</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Designing system architectures and developing complex software components while considering both functional and non-functional requirements.</li>\n<li>Creating high-quality software code in accordance with industry best practices and standards.</li>\n<li>Managing software testing processes, identifying and resolving issues, and optimizing system performance and scalability.</li>\n<li>Delivering cloud-oriented API-based components and microservices adhering to the highest engineering standards.</li>\n<li>Mentoring junior team members by providing technical support, guidance, and sharing knowledge and experience to facilitate their professional growth.</li>\n<li>Influencing team direction and task prioritization.</li>\n<li>Tackling complex problems requiring deep analysis and evaluation of diverse factors.</li>\n<li>Collaborating closely with other departments, such as product teams, and management, to ensure solution consistency and compliance.</li>\n<li>Engaging in effective cooperation with team members.</li>\n<li>Working collaboratively with internal and external stakeholders.</li>\n<li>Inspiring and facilitating constructive discussions around complex topics.</li>\n<li>Providing timely, concise, and actionable feedback to team colleagues.</li>\n<li>Promoting a knowledge-sharing mindset.</li>\n<li>Participating in recruitment interviews for your team.</li>\n<li>Maintaining openness to communication with both local and external partners.</li>\n<li>Developing mentoring skills, fostering learning, and sharing deep engineering expertise with peers.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(668,7184,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>We work for the financial industry, and you will play a crucial role in a DevOps approach designing, building, and maintaining the infrastructure that underlies data-driven decision-making. Your primary responsibility is to ensure the efficient and reliable flow of data from various sources to support business intelligence, trading and risk management.</p>\n<p>The tools and frameworks we use: Azure OpenAI, Azure Data Factory, Azure Blob Storage, Azure DevOps, Databricks, Python, Docker, JavaScript, .Net.</p>\n<h3>How you will get the job done</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>designing and implementing data models and architectures that support financial data management</li>\n<li>developing and maintaining ETL processes to integrate data from diverse sources, including market data feeds, customer information systems, and transactional databases</li>\n<li>ensuring data quality, security, and compliance with regulatory requirements</li>\n<li>collaborating with business owners, data analysts and scientists, software engineers, and DevOps specialists to support the development of predictive models and business intelligence tools</li>\n<li>optimizing data processing workflows for performance, scalability, and reliability</li>\n<li>working in an international Scrum team</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(669,7185,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p><span>As a Junior QA Engineer​, you will be responsible for ensuring the quality, reliability, and performance of Data Hubs and data processing pipelines in Azure &amp; Databricks. You will develop automated test frameworks, conduct regression testing, and validate large-scale data processing workflows.</span></p>\n<h3>How you will get the job done</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>designing, developing, and maintaining automated test frameworks for data processing and orchestration</li>\n<li>conducting regression, performance, and scalability testing for data ingestion and transformation</li>\n<li>implementing data quality validation and anomaly detection in Azure-based data pipelines</li>\n<li>collaborating with Data Engineers and DevOps teams to integrate testing into CI/CD pipelines</li>\n<li>ensuring compliance with data security, governance, and privacy standards</li>\n<li>defining test strategies, best practices, and documentation for Data &amp; AI solutions</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(670,7186,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>driving multiple complex projects and taking responsibility for their delivery using formal project management techniques </li>\n<li>planning and follow-up on assigned projects, including time scheduling, cost planning, resource management, quality assurance, etc.</li>\n<li>collaborating with internal ERGO partners to troubleshoot project planning issues</li>\n<li>facilitating design, planning, and implementation workshops with internal, and external stakeholders</li>\n<li>proactively managing project risks and issues, developing effective mitigation/treatment plans</li>\n<li>managing project meetings, schedules, milestones, and delivery</li>\n<li>preparing project correspondence and presentations, as needed, for status reports, executive updates, meetings, annual planning, etc.</li>\n<li>ensuring all project costs (actuals) are actively tracked, and managed, including SOWs/Purchase Orders, contracts, internal resource assignments</li>\n<li>coordinating the completion of all documentation, project plans, change requests, approvals, lifecycle steps, and compliance gate requests on time</li>\n<li>building and maintaining a successful relationship with teams, and business partners</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(671,7187,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"2-header\" aria-controls=\"2-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What we offer<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"2-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"2-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Salary based on&nbsp;<strong>B2B contract</strong>&nbsp;(via<strong>&nbsp;Devire</strong>)&nbsp;<strong>160-180 pln/h net+vat</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Long-term employment</li>\n<li>Private HealthCare</li>\n<li>Sports card&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Life insurance</li>\n<li><strong>Working for a leading corporation with a stable market position</strong></li>\n<li>Working in the international environment</li>\n<li>Hybrid work (<strong>3 days a week office work</strong>) with&nbsp;<strong>supportive&nbsp;</strong>and<strong>&nbsp;positive environment</strong>\n</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(672,7188,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"2-header\" aria-controls=\"2-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Co oferujemy<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"2-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"2-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Kontrakt B2B via Devire,</li>\n<li>Model hybrydowy,</li>\n<li>Współpraca długofalowa,</li>\n<li>Współpraca z firmą o stabilnej pozycji na rynku.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(673,7189,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>ICON plc is a world-leading healthcare intelligence and clinical research organization. We’re proud to foster an inclusive environment driving innovation and excellence, and we welcome you to join us on our mission to shape the future of clinical development.</p>\n\n<p>To be responsible for the overall direction, coordination, implementation, execution, control and completion of global cross-functional or single service phase I projects ensuring consistency with ICON SOPs, study contracts and budgets.</p>\n\n<p>Project Management </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Create, execute, maintain a detailed project plan in accordance with the approved scope of work and revise as appropriate to meet changing needs and requirements.</li>\n<li>Conduct study feasibility and ensure proper site selection, set-up and management of site(s).</li>\n<li>Oversee clinical monitoring from site qualification to site closure visits to ensure compliance with project requirements and ICON standards.</li>\n<li>Create, finalize, monitor, and close out project charters (where applicable).</li>\n<li>Identify resources needed and assigns individual responsibilities.</li>\n<li>Manage day-to-day operational aspects of a project and scope.</li>\n<li>Review deliverables prepared by team before passing to client.</li>\n<li>Effectively apply EPS project management methodology and enforces project standards.</li>\n<li>Utilize risk management methodologies to identify risks.</li>\n<li>Lead the process to document lessons learned and resultant recommendations for the project</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Project Accounting</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Track, report and approve team hours and expenses on a weekly basis.</li>\n<li>Manage project budget to ensure financial targets are met through regular review of direct/indirect costs and project resources.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Collaborate with Finance and Project Analysis to ensure accurate revenue recognition, invoicing, and other financial reconciliations.</li>\n<li>Recognize and submit out of scope requests for costing and approval.</li>\n<li>Stakeholder Management</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Business Development/Commercial Awareness</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Participate in bid defence presentations.</li>\n<li>Effectively convey ICON capabilities relating to Project Management and related disciplines in both written and verbal business development discussions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Communication</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Facilitate effective communication among all project-related parties.</li>\n<li>Effectively communicate information.</li>\n<li>Hold regular status meetings with project team both internal and external.</li>\n<li>Understand how to communicate difficult/sensitive information tactfully.</li>\n<li>Drive discussions on resolution of project issues; critically evaluate root cause and develop options for resolution; effectively communicate recommendation for resolution to stakeholders.</li>\n<li>Demonstrate conflict resolution capabilities: exhibit solution seeking behaviours and promote team building</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Teamwork</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Manage roles and responsibilities within the project team, ensuring that each team member understands requirements for project deliverables as within the scope of work</li>\n<li>Mitigate team conflict and communication problems.</li>\n<li>Works to ensure that all team members are aware of pending deliverables and assignments and that the required resources are secured to complete deliverables on-time</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Leadership</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Inspires team members to attain goals and pursue excellence.</li>\n<li>Identifies opportunities for improvement and makes constructive suggestions for change</li>\n<li>Manages the process of change effectively.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Client Management</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Be the principle contact for Sponsors, especially as it relates to timelines, deliverables and financial objectives for the project.</li>\n<li>Manage day-to-day client interaction.</li>\n<li>Manage client expectations and convey these expectations to the project team</li>\n<li>Communicate effectively with clients to identify needs and evaluate alternative business solutions.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(674,7190,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Truv</h4>\n\n<p>Truv is transforming the financial data industry with a secure and real-time API platform for payroll account access. Our technology streamlines income and employment verification, direct deposit switching, and more—eliminating outdated processes and unlocking greater financial opportunities. Backed by $30M from top investors like Kleiner Perkins and NYCA, we’re disrupting a $2B legacy market with cutting-edge innovation and a customer-first approach. Our leadership team brings expertise from industry giants like Apple, Carta, Venmo, MX, and Okta, driving the future of financial data access.</p>\n\n<p>What you’ll do:\n* Design, implement, and test cloud-based server-side code\n* Use best programming practices to optimize code performance\n* Write and maintain unit and integration tests</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(675,7191,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About PayU</h4>\n\n<p>PayU, a leading payment and Fintech company in 50+ high-growth markets throughout Asia, Central and Eastern Europe, Latin America, the Middle East and Africa, part of Prosus group, one of the largest technology investors in the world is redefining the way people buy and sell online for our 300.000+ merchants and millions of consumers. As a leading online payment service provider, we deploy more than 400 payment methods and PCI-certified platforms to process approximately 6 million payments every single day.</p>\n\n<p>We’re looking for an <strong>Application Security Specialist</strong> who’s ready to turn security into a core part of how we build. If you love digging into code, automating defenses, and making applications safer every day - this role is for you!</p>\n\n<p>RESPONSIBILITIES:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Implement and monitor <strong>security measures</strong> across applications, systems, and networks.</li>\n<li>Define and refine <strong>security requirements</strong> in collaboration with development and infrastructure teams.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Configure, harden, and troubleshoot</strong> application and security components.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Build tools and solutions</strong> to detect, mitigate, and automate remediation of vulnerabilities.</li>\n<li>Manage <strong>vulnerability assessments</strong>, <strong>penetration tests</strong>, and <strong>external bug bounty reports</strong>.</li>\n<li>Champion <strong>secure coding practices throughout the SDLC</strong> through reviews, threat modeling, and security gates.</li>\n<li>Integrate <strong>automated security checks</strong> into CI/CD pipelines with development teams.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Investigate and respond to security incidents</strong>, performing technical analysis and containment.</li>\n<li>Assess <strong>overall security posture</strong>, identify gaps, and drive continuous improvement.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Deliver clear reports</strong>, dashboards, and executive summaries on risks, remediation progress, and trends.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(676,7192,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Kaseya</h4>\n\n<p>Kaseya<sup>®</sup> is the leading provider of complete IT infrastructure and security management solutions for Managed Service Providers (MSPs) and internal IT organizations worldwide powered by AI. Kaseya’s best-in-breed technologies allow organizations to efficiently manage and secure IT to drive sustained business success. Kaseya has achieved sustained, strong double-digit growth over the past several years and is backed by Insight Venture Partners (www.insightpartners.com), a leading global private equity firm investing in high-growth technology and software companies that drive transformative change in the industries they serve.</p>\n\n<p>Founded in 2000, Kaseya currently serves customers in over 20 countries across a wide variety of industries and manages over 15 million endpoints worldwide. To learn more about our company and our award-winning solutions, go to www.Kaseya.com and for more information on Kaseya’s culture.</p>\n\n<p>Kaseya is not your typical company. We are not afraid to tell you exactly who we are and our expectations. The thousands of people that succeed at Kaseya are prepared to go above and beyond for the betterment of our customers.</p>\n\n<h4>About the Role</h4>\n\n<p>We’re looking for a proactive <strong>DevOps Engineer</strong> to join our growing infrastructure team. You’ll take ownership of our AWS-based environments, build scalable automation with Terraform and Jenkins, and help us maintain secure, high-performing systems.</p>\n\n<p>You’ll have a real voice in infrastructure decisions and the freedom to implement your ideas.</p>\n\n<h4>Your Daily Work</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Design, deploy, and manage AWS infrastructure with <strong>Terraform / Terragrunt</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Build &amp; optimize <strong>Jenkins</strong> pipelines for CI/CD</li>\n<li>Automate with <strong>Puppet</strong>, <strong>Shell</strong>, and <strong>Python</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Monitor performance with <strong>Grafana</strong> and <strong>Prometheus</strong>\n</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot issues &amp; collaborate with developers</li>\n<li>Share knowledge and mentor junior engineers</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(677,7193,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Capgemini</h4>\n\n<p>When you join Capgemini, you don’t just start a new job. You become part of something bigger.</p>\n\n<p>We bring together passionate, skilled people, a tech-driven approach to innovation, and a deep commitment to our clients to help organizations unlock the true value of technology. As a graduate or an experienced professional, you will be working with the world’s leading brands to enhance and transform the way they do business.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(678,7194,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>This role will join Cognitive &amp; Robotics team which is responsible for managing the global Tools Splunk infrastructure. This is a strategic position and will be instrumental in the design, implementation, support, performance, and integrity of the Splunk ecosystem. You will work closely with multiple stakeholders and global partners. This is a multi-disciplinary role that will interact directly with developers and different functional IT, Security and Engineering teams to gather requirements, architect solutions and ensure the Splunk platform is leveraged as a key data collection.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(679,7195,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>You will be responsible for database reliability and optimization</li>\n<li>You will implement measurement tools and performance metrics to</li>\n<li>You will need to administer DB2, SQLServer, Oracle, Postgres, CouchBase, databases</li>\n<li>You will manage backup, restore and automate them</li>\n<li>You manage the changes and the realization of the requests for evolution</li>\n<li>You will be analyze and ensure resolution of complex incidents</li>\n<li>You will maintain technical administration procedures and data access security rules</li>\n<li>You will deal with level 2 and 3 support</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(680,7196,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>We are looking for a skilled Messaging service and shared space Consultant to join our IT team. The Consultant will be responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining end-user computing environments, including desktop and mobile devices, collaboration tools, and software deployment. You will ensure that employees have access to the right tools and technologies to optimize productivity and work efficiency, both in-office and remotely.</p>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Managing messaging service (Exchange 2016, 2019, Office 365, Microsoft Defender, proofpoint, ironport, archive Exchange, archive Enterprise Vault).</li>\n<li>Implementation and administration of messaging solutions, email archiving and securing associated services (provision provided by Helpdesk and local service).</li>\n<li>Configuration and Securing of Mail Flows DNS Management.</li>\n<li>Provision of Level 2 support for escalated issues related to messaging solutions.</li>\n<li>Administration of shared Space : Onedrive, Sharepoint, Cloud, Filer Nutanix, Sharefile Citrix.</li>\n<li>Provide storage spaces for professional and personal data.</li>\n<li>Installation, configuration and administration of file servers.</li>\n<li>Provision of storage folders, management of sharing authorizations and security permissions.</li>\n<li>Administration and securing of cloud storage solutions.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to optimize the digital workplace experience and drive productivity improvements.</li>\n<li>Stay current with emerging workplace technologies and trends, recommending improvements to enhance user experience and productivity.</li>\n<li>Document processes and maintain up-to-date configurations, policies, and troubleshooting guides.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(681,7197,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>The role of Major Incident Manager falls within the Service Management domain. This role will have the responsibility of managing the Capgemini Major Incident Management process and therefore will work closely with Incident Management, Problem Management, Change Management, Capgemini Tower Management and Leads, SDMs, Service Desks and at times directly with the Customer. The role requires an assertive person who has experience in dealing with challenging and complex customer issues and who is mature in business acumen. The successful candidate will be an excellent communicator, able to negotiate, plan and communicate major incident activities. You will use your influencing skills to ensure that resolutions are agreed and achieved swiftly and efficiently. This role requires an experience in dealing with challenging and difficult customer issues as well as the ability to deflate these types of situations without leadership escalation.</p>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Management and delivery of Major Incident Management</li>\n<li>Coordination, planning, escalation, communication and resourcing during Major Incidents</li>\n<li>Production and maintenance of the Major Incident communication</li>\n<li>Monitor and escalate status as needed for Priority 1 and 2 outage tickets</li>\n<li>Provide non-technical administrative support for Major Incident Response Teams (MIRTs)</li>\n<li>Ensure timely provision of agreed regular reports and documents</li>\n<li>Participation in Major Incident reviews</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(682,7198,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Configure, deploy, and maintain MDM solutions</li>\n<li>Manage mobile device policies, profiles, and compliance settings</li>\n<li>Provide technical support and troubleshooting for mobile devices and AirWatch platform issues or Intune</li>\n<li>Monitor and analyze system performance to ensure optimal operation.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with IT and security teams to implement best practices and security standards</li>\n<li>Stay updated with the latest industry trends and technologies related to MDM.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(683,7199,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Design, implement, and manage enterprise virtualization infrastructure (Windows VM, Linux/unix VM, VMWARE, Nutanix and AIX, Storage, Backup and Archiving).</li>\n<li>Managing CIS Infra services (Systems &amp; virtualization, storage &amp; backup, databases, network &amp; telephony, monitoring &amp; operations).</li>\n<li>Monitor and optimize the performance, availability, and scalability of virtual machines (VMs) and virtualized environments.</li>\n<li>Perform capacity planning, load balancing, and ensure high availability and disaster recovery capabilities for virtualized systems.</li>\n<li>Manage and maintain virtual networking, storage, and security configurations within the virtualization environment.</li>\n<li>Develop and maintain automation scripts (e.g., PowerShell, Python) to streamline virtualization tasks, including VM provisioning, backups, and performance tuning.</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot and resolve complex issues related to virtualization infrastructure, working closely with cross-functional IT teams.</li>\n<li>Perform regular upgrades, patches, and maintenance of the virtual infrastructure to ensure security and compliance with industry standards.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with application and database teams to ensure that virtualization infrastructure meets performance and availability requirements for business applications.</li>\n<li>Provide guidance and mentorship to junior team members and participate in knowledge-sharing sessions.</li>\n<li>Stay current with emerging virtualization technologies and trends, recommending improvements to enhance performance and efficiency.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(684,7200,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Install, configure, and maintain Linux-based servers (e.g., Ubuntu, CentOS, Red Hat).</li>\n<li>Monitor system performance, ensuring high availability and reliability.</li>\n<li>Perform regular system updates, patches, and kernel upgrades to ensure security and compliance.</li>\n<li>Automate routine system tasks using scripting languages such as Bash, Python, or Perl.</li>\n<li>Implement security best practices including firewalls, VPN, access controls, and file permissions.</li>\n<li>Perform system backups, recovery procedures, and disaster recovery planning.</li>\n<li>Manage storage solutions, including NFS, RAID, LVM, and SAN systems.</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot and resolve hardware, software, and network issues.</li>\n<li>Manage user access and permissions, maintaining compliance with internal policies.</li>\n<li>Document system configurations, procedures, and troubleshooting steps.</li>\n<li>Implement and monitor logging and alerting tools to track system health and prevent outages.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(685,7201,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Managing virtualized environment based on Citrix and Microsoft technologies</li>\n<li>Troubleshooting, maintenance and operational support for the Citrix Virtual Apps and Desktops environment, including VDI infrastructure</li>\n<li>Performing common activities like incident management, service request management and change management</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(686,7202,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Be the point of contact for external and internal communications</li>\n<li>Cost/ SIM Card Asset management</li>\n<li>Maintain maintenance &amp; telephony (mobile phone) contracts</li>\n<li>Manage SIM Cards for contracted mobile phone devices for client</li>\n<li>Handover to delivery skills</li>\n<li>Ensure deliverables are up to quality standards</li>\n<li>Cost controlling and reporting</li>\n<li>Inventory Audits</li>\n<li>Cooperation with other delivery teams &amp; client</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(687,7203,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>We are looking for a skilled and proactive&nbsp;<strong>French speaking</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Production Engineer</strong>&nbsp;to join our team. This role involves maintaining the stability and performance of critical applications, resolving complex incidents, and collaborating with cross-functional teams to ensure seamless operations.</p>\n<h4></h4>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Troubleshoot and resolve OS-level incidents across Linux and Windows environments</li>\n<li>Resolve Level 2 and Level 3 support tickets</li>\n<li>Process service requests and implement approved changes</li>\n<li>Maintain and update operational documentation (DEX)</li>\n<li>Ensure the availability of high-impact applications</li>\n<li>Communicate directly with stakeholders when required</li>\n<li>Leverage a good understanding of application architecture to diagnose and resolve issues</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(688,7204,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>We are looking for a skilled and proactive French speaking Application Support Engineer to join our team supporting the EDF project. This role involves maintaining the stability and performance of critical applications, resolving complex incidents, and collaborating with cross-functional teams to ensure seamless operations.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Troubleshoot and resolve OS-level incidents across Linux and Windows environments</li>\n<li>Resolve Level 2 and Level 3 support tickets</li>\n<li>Process service requests and implement approved changes</li>\n<li>Maintain and update operational documentation (DEX)</li>\n<li>Ensure the availability of high-impact applications</li>\n<li>Communicate directly with stakeholders when required</li>\n<li>Leverage a good understanding of application architecture to diagnose and resolve issues</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(689,7205,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>We are seeking an experienced Oracle DBA Engineer with French to join our team. This role will be crucial in database reliability and optimization. The ideal candidate will have experience in resolving complex incidents, implementing measurement tools and administrating databases.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>You will be responsible for database reliability and optimization;</li>\n<li>You will manage backup, restore and automate them;</li>\n<li>You manage the changes and the realization of the requests for evolution;</li>\n<li>You will be analyze and ensure resolution of complex incidents;</li>\n<li>You will implement measurement tools and performance metrics</li>\n<li>You will need to administer DB2, MySQL, Oracle, Postgres, CouchBase, databases ;</li>\n<li>You will maintain technical administration procedures and data access security rules;</li>\n<li>You will deal with level 2 and 3 support.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(690,7206,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Monitor database performance, troubleshoot issues, and ensure high availability.</li>\n<li>Manage database backups, restoration, and disaster recovery processes.</li>\n<li>Implement security measures to safeguard sensitive data, ensuring compliance with company policies and regulations (GDPR, HIPAA, etc.).</li>\n<li>Optimize and tune database performance, including queries, indexes, and storage.</li>\n<li>Design and implement database schemas, tables, and procedures to support business applications.</li>\n<li>Install, configure, and maintain database systems (for example : SQL Server, MySQL, Oracle, PostgreSQL).</li>\n<li>Develop and maintain database documentation.</li>\n<li>Perform database migrations, upgrades, and patches with minimal downtime.</li>\n<li>Manage database access and user permissions.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(691,7207,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>As a Senior Engineer/ Consultant at Nutanix, you will play a critical role in designing, implementing, and supporting cutting-edge cloud and virtualization solutions. You’ll work closely with cross-functional teams to deliver high-performance, scalable, and secure infrastructure using Nutanix technologies.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Design and develop scalable cloud architectures.</li>\n<li>Install, configure, and maintain Nutanix solutions tailored to client requirements.</li>\n<li>Perform system testing, troubleshooting, and performance optimization.</li>\n<li>Apply patches, updates, and security configurations.</li>\n<li>Provide advanced technical support and root cause analysis.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with teams to design and implement virtualization solutions.</li>\n<li>Develop and maintain documentation.</li>\n<li>Engage with customers to understand and solve technical challenges.</li>\n<li>Understand storage and networking principles in virtualized environments.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(692,7208,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>The role of Transition Manager is a very dynamic position for a person willing to work on IT service transitions / project management. The successful candidate will have the opportunity to develop within a team of 10+ Transition Managers and work on international projects. Transition Managers are responsible and manage significant transition programs inclusive of transferring services and staff from one delivery model to another or from one service provider to another (internal or external). They ensure that service levels are maintained throughout and are responsible for the budget, project plans and for the reporting to the customer and internal management.</p>\n<h4><strong>YOUR TASKS:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Lead the transition activities and ensure that the new service is fully accepted into RUN</li>\n<li>Validate service scope and service measurement criteria, ensure that service levels are documented and that a contract summary is created</li>\n<li>Conduct quality gate reviews and undertake project audits as agreed</li>\n<li>Build and maintain a strong working relationship with key internal and external stakeholders</li>\n<li>Own project financials (billing, forecasting)</li>\n<li>Take part in Bid process and influence transition solutioning together with solution analysts and architects</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(693,7209,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Lead and mentor a team of network engineers, fostering a collaborative and high-performance culture.</li>\n<li>Design, implement, and maintain scalable and secure network architectures across on-premises and cloud environments.</li>\n<li>Act as the technical authority for network-related projects, ensuring alignment with business and security requirements.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams including infrastructure, security, and application teams.</li>\n<li>Manage and optimize network performance, availability, and reliability.</li>\n<li>Oversee firewall and security configurations, ensuring compliance with internal and external standards.</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot complex network issues and provide guidance on resolution strategies.</li>\n<li>Stay current with emerging technologies and industry trends to drive innovation and continuous improvement.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(694,7210,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>As a DevOps provider for the BMW Web Platform, the stable, secure and efficient operation of the platform is ensured. The platform is based on an AWS microservices architecture and Adobe Experience Manager (AEM) and enables the implementation of customer-oriented web experiences.</p>\n<p>Be part of a small, self-managed, fast-paced DevOps team working on SaaS/PaaS platforms work with AWS, AEM and whatever you deem necessary to get the job done</p>\n<p>perform and define operational tasks related to best practices for service operations in our AWS environments</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience in working with AWS and application-, platform-operations as well as Adobe Experience Manager / Adobe Cloud</li>\n<li>Experience in working with K8S (Kubernetes), Docker</li>\n<li>Experience in working with Grafana / OpenSearch, Prometheus</li>\n<li>Experience in working with Linux, Bash, Python</li>\n<li>On call Duty</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(695,7211,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p><span>Our&nbsp;</span><strong>GMS Tax Technology</strong><span>&nbsp;team deals with creating and implementing advanced IT solutions that support a wide range of processes and automations. They are related to international personal income taxes (</span><strong>GMS – Global Mobility Services</strong><span>) and management of human resources. We are a globally distributed team with members from various locations. We are looking for candidates with passion who would like to join our rapidly growing team in Warszawa. In our daily work we are focused on creating safe, innovative, and ergonomic solutions that join specific business knowledge with new technologies. We also support many world-wide corporations which appreciate the highest level of services we deliver.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Creating and implementing modern business applications according to business and technical specification (main responsibility)</li>\n<li>Providing post-implementation services (maintenance) for already existing modules and creating new functionalities</li>\n<li>Keeping project documentation up to date</li>\n<li>Providing support to end-users (advice, guidance, assistance and training)</li>\n<li>Participation in deployments processes as well as cooperating with end-users in terms of ongoing problem solving of their business related issues</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(696,7212,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Interpret and apply development skills to build IAM solutions to support globally dispersed businesses, personnel and customers</li>\n<li>Work with IAM leads and business IT managers to understand business requirements, enterprise IT standards and other considerations that influence how IAM solutions and services should perform and operate</li>\n<li>Engineer solutions to ensure that identity and access management solutions and services perform according to defined processes, meet defined policies and comply with information security requirements</li>\n<li>Develop technical IAM solutions, engaging during the lifecycle of solutions delivery, service owners, architects, project managers, global infrastructure teams, regional IT teams and key IAM product vendors</li>\n<li>Integrate IAM systems with in-house and third-party applications for provisioning, identity authentication and systems resources authorization, developing connectors between IAM tools and systems resources</li>\n<li>Work with application developers and IT operations to develop, test, roll out and maintain enterprise-wide IAM solutions and services</li>\n<li>Lead quality control and quality assurance activities, such as developing and executing test plans / scripts and resolving deviations or exceptions, for newly developed and/or enhanced IAM solutions</li>\n<li>Work with the broader IT security, risk and compliance organization to interpret policies and standards, ensuring policies and standards are properly followed by new and existing IAM solutions</li>\n<li>Contribute to evaluation, selection and configuration of IAM products and services from vendors</li>\n<li>Support in troubleshooting and resolving complex authentication, authorization and integration problems Identify opportunities and outline action plans to improve how existing IAM solutions are implemented</li>\n<li>Lead and/or execute of daily, weekly and monthly support activities to maintain the overall global IAM environment, in coordination with IT operations and regional IT team’s Offshore coordination</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(697,7213,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>At Ensono, our purpose is to be a relentless ally, disrupting the status quo and unleashing our clients to Do Great Things! We enable our clients to achieve key business outcomes that reshape how our world runs. As an expert technology adviser and managed service provider with cross-platform certifications, Ensono empowers our clients to keep up with continuous change and embrace innovation. </p>\n\n<p>Developing impactful solutions is something we do together at Ensono because Ideas Start Here. Great things happen when many voices are heard, and people are supported to run with their ideas. On our teams, you will be backed by leaders with a passion for our business. This is a place where your ideas can Do Great Things. </p>\n\n<p>We can Do Great Things because we have great Associates. The Ensono Core Values unify our diverse talents and are woven into how we do business. </p>\n\n<p>Adventure starts here. Here you will be a part of a team that encourages you to master your craft, ask tomorrow’s questions today, and chart your path. Our Associates focus on client impact with curiosity and a feeling of relentless commitment. </p>\n\n<p>About the role and what you will be doing:</p>\n\n<p>This is an exciting opportunity to join a friendly team working on some of the hottest AWS technologies. This team is primarily focused on the deployment, automation and support of mission-critical client solutions in AWS. \nYou will be working on a variety of projects and environments for household names using the latest technology including AWS, Terraform, Ansible, PowerShell, Datadog, Jenkins, Bitbucket, Jira, Containers etc. Learning, collaboration, training and certification are strongly encouraged, and opportunities to do so will be provided. \nThe successful candidate will be someone who can demonstrate a genuine desire and passion for AWS, client service and automation. </p>\n\n<p>Key Responsibilities \n* Act as the lead engineer on large or complex client deploy projects. \n* Act as the lead engineer on product engineering projects to further develop our service. \n* Provide AWS subject matter expertise advice and assistance to pre-sales architects. \n* Installation, configuration, and ongoing management of O/S and AWS services. \n* Implementing and maintaining custom client machine images and centralised configuration management to enable quick repeatable builds and auto-scaling. \n* Maintaining high availability through proactive measures. \n* Troubleshooting and resolving complex technical issues. \n* Ensuring clients &amp; partners are updated on current status of work and issues. \n* Raise, investigate and resolve problems and known errors in line with the problem management process. \n* Ability and willingness to proactively improve ways of working, automation and processes via our continual improvement Kanban board. \n* Partake in an on-call rota to provide 24x7 4th line support for Ensono’s AWS clients. \n* Proactively keep up to date on AWS services and developments. \n* Buddy new members of the team and train other teams.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(698,7214,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Azure Engineer</h4>\n\n<p><strong>Azure Engineer</strong> plays a key role in the design, development, and management of our Azure infrastructure. This position is responsible for managing, maintaining, and enhancing Azure public cloud environments. The ideal candidate will have hands-on experience in provisioning and troubleshooting Azure infrastructure resources, as well as strong skills in identifying and resolving complex issues efficiently and professionally.</p>\n\n<p>In this role, the Azure Engineer will contribute to building new environments for our cloud customers and ensure that these environments are developed and maintained for high availability, scalability, and ease of maintenance. Collaboration with customers will also be an important part of the job, particularly when scheduling maintenance windows and coordinating change management activities.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Pod: ** Azure Delivery&nbsp;<br></strong>Leader<strong>: Cloud Implementation Leader<br></strong>Location<strong>:  Tampa, FL (hybrid), US (remote), Poland (remote), Ukraine (remote)<br></strong>Working Schedule: **EST office hours&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><em>All new hires in North America complete in-person onboarding at our Tampa office, which typically lasts 3 to 5 days.</em></p>\n\n<h4>Responsibilities:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Implement, support, and maintain 24x7 Azure CSP environments, RDS deployments and Windows technologies. </li>\n<li>Make ongoing recommendations of Azure and Windows policies and standards – strategic planning. </li>\n<li>Manage multiple large-scale projects in a fast-paced challenging environment and provide leadership to other members of the team. </li>\n<li>Quickly convert business problems into technical solutions and opportunities. </li>\n<li>Resolve Azure, Windows, and RDS escalations from clients and other team members. </li>\n<li>Collaborate with customers and team members to troubleshoot and resolve issues. </li>\n<li>Maintain and prioritize incidents, ensuring timely resolution. </li>\n<li>Manage configuration and deployment of Azure resources in compliance with established technology policies. </li>\n<li>Recommend technical solutions that will enhance performance, increase redundancy, and add flexibility to the existing infrastructure. </li>\n<li>Troubleshoot Azure and Windows performance issues. </li>\n<li>Maintain system availability and monitoring of critical services. </li>\n<li>Maintain appropriate relationships with 3rd party vendors and evaluate vendor software, and communications products to provide recommendations to leadership. </li>\n<li>Regular participation in change control activities that comply with ITIL change management. </li>\n<li>Establish upgrade and backup strategies for core infrastructure. </li>\n<li>Participate in on-call rotation as needed. </li>\n<li>Additional responsibilities may be assigned as needed. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>ABOUT ENAVATE</h4>\n\n<p><strong>Transforming Businesses and the Lives They Touch</strong></p>\n\n<p>At Enavate, we are more than just a <strong>Microsoft Gold Partner</strong>—we’re a trusted partner in Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) consulting, Cloud services, and managed services. We help businesses embrace the future by guiding them through ERP implementations, migrations to the cloud, and integrations that streamline their operations, allowing them to thrive in an ever-evolving business landscape.</p>\n\n<p>Our work isn’t just about technology—it’s about <strong>transforming the way businesses operate</strong>, empowering them to grow, innovate, and succeed. By partnering with our clients, we provide peace of mind, enabling them to focus on what matters most while we handle the complexity of their systems and processes.<br><br>To learn more about what we do and how we make an impact, please check out our \"<a href=\"https://enavate.sharepoint.com/:b:/s/EnavateTAPortal/EZFjQhyVFSpIsRk9Ydt71GYBnBiuZ-EjFaxYedvQzcxWOQ?e=YYXGfR\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">What We Do?</a>\" 1-pager.</p>\n\n<h4>Our Culture</h4>\n\n<p>Whether you’re joining us in North America, Europe, or beyond, Enavate offers a dynamic and collaborative environment where you’ll have the opportunity to make a real impact.</p>\n\n<p>At Enavate, we’re driven by our core values, and our people are at the heart of everything we do:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Team Members:</strong> We take care of our own.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Innovation:</strong> We explore, evolve, and seek excellence at every level.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Results:</strong> We are achievers who set high goals and reach them.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Integrity:</strong> We are trustworthy. Our word is our bond.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We believe that a diverse and inclusive team leads to better innovation and outcomes. We actively support diversity and inclusion through a variety of initiatives, creating a workplace where everyone is respected and valued.<br><br>To gain a deeper understanding of our values and the environment we foster at Enavate, take a look at our \"<a href=\"https://enavate.sharepoint.com/:b:/s/EnavateTAPortal/EVTI2ygLv_RDsrrhFVxRk_IBvH3xUho4NEMQVuH6AZc7Xw?e=FefaD5\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Enavate Culture</a>\" Guide.</p>\n\n<h4>Work Structure &amp; Collaboration</h4>\n\n<p>At Enavate, we embrace flexibility in how we work, but we also believe that collaboration is key to our success. Our office locations in Tampa, FL, Fargo, ND, and Kyiv, Ukraine are central to our culture and provide a hub for team interaction and innovation. </p>\n\n<p>We prioritize hiring candidates who are based in or near these locations. For team members based in <strong>Tampa</strong> and <strong>Fargo</strong>, we encourage team members to spend <strong>at least three days per week in the office</strong> to foster collaboration, connection, and contribute to our vibrant team culture.</p>\n\n<p>All North American new hires are <strong>onboarded in person</strong> at our Tampa office. Onboarding typically lasts 3 to 5 days, depending on the role, and provides a dedicated opportunity to connect with your leader, teammates, and our company culture.</p>\n\n<h4>Join Us in Our Mission!</h4>\n\n<p>At Enavate, we believe in transforming businesses and the lives they touch – because to us, it’s personal. If you\'re ready to make an impact, we invite you to be part of a team that listens, challenges, collaborates, and takes action. Together, we’re reshaping the future of ERP and how businesses operate, offering fresh perspectives and innovative solutions.</p>\n\n<p>Are you ready to transform your career and help us shape the future? Enavate is the place for you.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(699,7215,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior Software Engineer</h4>\n\n<p>Location: Krakow, Poland, EMEA</p>\n\n<p><strong>Position Overview</strong> </p>\n\n<p>At Autodesk, we are reinventing how everything you see or touch is imagined, designed and created. In Autodesk Construction Cloud, we are revolutionizing how every building, bridge, hospital, campus and stadium is built. Our platform allows customers to effectively and easily manage the complex collaboration and coordination necessary to see their projects through all phases of construction.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for a talented Senior Software Developer to join our growing team in Krakow. As a senior developer, you will be an integral part of the team tasked with building and improving the critical workflows within the Autodesk Construction Cloud. You will be helping our customers refine and improve how they design and construct large projects using our cloud services. You will be working with an excellent international team of skilled developers and collaborating with all kinds of Autodesk teams around the world. If you want to help change the world, come help our customers Make Anything.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Write clean, reliable and secure code in different languages and technologies (mostly Typescript, JavaScript, React, HTML)</li>\n<li>Develop and maintain unit tests and E2E tests; strive to automate testing as much as possible</li>\n<li>Help divide large features into clear, manageable tasks</li>\n<li>Align activities with stakeholders, influence decisions and help lead projects to completion</li>\n<li>Actively collaborate within and outside of the team, bringing new ideas and challenging the status quo</li>\n<li>Participate in code reviews to ensure new code conforms to highest standards</li>\n<li>Understand, embrace, and promote agile methodologies, principles, and values within the team</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About Autodesk</strong>\nWelcome to Autodesk! Amazing things are created every day with our software – from the greenest buildings and cleanest cars to the smartest factories and biggest hit movies. We help innovators turn their ideas into reality, transforming not only how things are made, but what can be made.</p>\n\n<p>We take great pride in our culture here at Autodesk – our Culture Code is at the core of everything we do. Our values and ways of working help our people thrive and realize their potential, which leads to even better outcomes for our customers.</p>\n\n<p>When you’re an Autodesker, you can be your whole, authentic self and do meaningful work that helps build a better future for all. Ready to shape the world and your future? Join us!</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(700,7216,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Whatnot is the largest livestream shopping platform in North America and Europe to buy, sell, and discover the things you love. We’re re-defining e-commerce by blending community, shopping, and entertainment into a community just for you. As a remote co-located team, we’re inspired by innovation and anchored in our <a href=\"https://www.whatnot.com/careers\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">values</a>. With hubs in the US, UK, Ireland, Poland, and Germany, we’re building the future of online marketplaces—together.</p>\n\n<p>From fashion, beauty, and electronics to rare collectibles like trading cards, comic books, and even live plants, our live auctions have something for everyone.</p>\n\n<p>And we’re just getting started! As one of the <a href=\"https://a16z.com/marketplace-100/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">fastest growing marketplaces</a>, we’re looking for bold, forward-thinking problem solvers across all functional areas. Check out the latest Whatnot updates on our <a href=\"https://blog.teamwhatnot.com/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">news</a> and <a href=\"https://medium.com/whatnot-engineering\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">engineering</a> blogs and join us as we enable anyone to turn their passion into a business, and bring people together through commerce.</p>\n\n Role \n\n<p>The Payments team at Whatnot is fundamental to the product’s global operations. We power every order, collect every payment across a wide range of local and international methods, and manage returns, refunds, and seller payouts at scale. Each year, we process billions of dollars in payments, making us one of the most trusted and essential systems in the business.</p>\n\n<p>As Whatnot grows rapidly, our team is directly responsible for enabling that growth—by building reliable, scalable infrastructure and developing innovative ways for users to transact. We play a central role in shaping the future of commerce on the platform and are accountable for supporting the continued expansion of both buyers and sellers in the years ahead.</p>\n\n<p>Each member of the team has a lot of individual responsibility and many more freedoms, so we need to hire people we can trust. Your ability to make good trade-offs and exercise good judgment is essential to us.</p>\n\n<p>Team members in this role are required to be within commuting distance of Kraków or Wrocław, Poland.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(701,7217,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Waymo</h4>\n\n<p>Waymo is an autonomous driving technology company with the mission to be the world\'s most trusted driver. Since its start as the Google Self-Driving Car Project in 2009, Waymo has focused on building the Waymo Driver—The World\'s Most Experienced Driver™—to improve access to mobility while saving thousands of lives now lost to traffic crashes. The Waymo Driver powers Waymo’s fully autonomous ride-hail service and can also be applied to a range of vehicle platforms and product use cases. The Waymo Driver has provided over ten million rider-only trips, enabled by its experience autonomously driving over 100 million miles on public roads and tens of billions in simulation across 15+ U.S. states.</p>\n\n<p>Want to build the next generation of infrastructure for driverless cars? Join the Waymo Simulation Infrastructure team, and help power the future of transportation! We are looking for a passionate Staff SWE who wants to help build and manage planet-scale distributed systems. If you\'re someone who\'s curious and passionate about solving deep technical problems, and love collaborating across many teams to develop and deliver reliable, scalable, and cost-effective Infra services and tools, then we\'d like to meet you!</p>\n\n<p>In this role will report to a Senior Staff Software Engineer/TLM.</p>\n\n<h4>You will:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Lead an Infrastructure team that builds and maintains reliable, highly-scalable, and cost-effective production services to run Simulation-based Evaluation of the Waymo Driver</li>\n<li>Set the technical vision and direction for your team, and also influence the direction of the broader Infrastructure Organization.</li>\n<li>Manage a team of 3-4 junior and senior SWEs,</li>\n<li>Contribute production grade code, execute code reviews, drive and influence detailed technical designs</li>\n<li>Align and define plans for your team in addition to influencing planning and strategy of partners and the larger Organization</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(702,7218,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>About the Project: Our client is looking for Software Developers in Test with Networking and Test Automation skillset, within the Team which is currently developing new automation work for our Customer. This Team has the ownership to define the process, debug all aspects of the Products\' functionality in its release cycle and work closely together with our Test and Framework Development Team to identify root causes, raise issues accordingly to feature or test developers and triage problems. This team also collaborates closely with the Customer\'s Developer Team on feature issues and thus reduce the number of flaws in the Product. The Customer relies on us to keep a healthy and real PASS rate of the tests in order to maintain a high performance product and demonstrable quality metrics (Quality Gate). The process needs to scale up to the agile release strategy of the Customer\'s products.</p>\n<p>Thus, the ideal candidate has deep knowledge of software development in testing / test automation, computer networking, as well as troubleshooting skills necessary to understand and debug efficiently the various testing scenarios (strong preference is Python, as the framework and tests are written in Python). Prior experience with distributed systems is highly desirable.</p>\n<p>Our current team: Our current Test and Framework Development Team is comprised of experienced Automation and Manual QA Engineers, working in an agile process of Product Lifecycle Management. This team provides close assistance to the Release Support Team.</p>\n<p>Tools and Technologies used: Python 2.x /3.x, Atlassian Suite, VMWare, Jenkins, Bitbucket, Git, KVM/vCenter, Linux, Docker, Ixia, </p>\n<p>Opportunities: Contribute to automated testcase development and framework development. Debug all functional aspects of the Products and Test Framework, gaining experience in a wide area of technologies and devices (Advanced Applied Python knowledge, Cisco, Juniper, Arista, Cumulus, etc.). Work with containerized environments. Define the Quality Gate process with the help of our existing team, maintaining it and having ownership over it. Collaborate closely with our  local team and with the Customer\'s team.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Primarily contribute to new test automation and framework development by writing complex Python scripts, tightly integrated within a state-of-the-art PTest everything-as-code infrastructure.</li>\n<li>Contribute to the quality strategy of the products by developing and maintaining the Quality Release Gate process</li>\n<li>Run and debug automated integration and system tests in Python per release needs.</li>\n<li>Work closely with the engineering team to isolate and resolve defects in a timely manner</li>\n<li>Work closely with our local team to debug framework and test related issues</li>\n<li>Create bug reports when issues arise and track them through completion.</li>\n<li>Triage failures per severity and prioritize as necessary, when needed.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(703,7219,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>The EBAM Consultant will support the design, implementation, and maintenance of EBAM solutions within the organization\'s Treasury and Banking environment. The role focuses on automating bank account management processes, ensuring compliance with internal controls, and improving visibility over global banking structures. The consultant will work closely with Treasury, IT, and Finance teams to streamline workflows for opening, modifying, and closing bank accounts while ensuring data accuracy and compliance with corporate and regulatory standards.</p>\n<p>Implement and configure EBAM solutions (SAP, Kyriba, or other platforms) to support end-to-end bank account management processes.</p>\n<p>Collaborate with Treasury, Finance, and Banking teams to define business requirements and translate them into system configurations.</p>\n<p>Ensure bank account master data accuracy, authorization controls, and proper approval workflows.</p>\n<p>Manage integrations between EBAM systems and banks (via SWIFT or host-to-host connections).</p>\n<p>Develop and maintain documentation for system processes, configurations, and governance standards.</p>\n<p>Support testing, training, and go-live activities for new EBAM functionalities.</p>\n<p>Provide ongoing production support and process improvement recommendations.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(704,7220,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>The TRAX Consultant will support the implementation, configuration, and optimization solution integrated with SAP systems. The role focuses on ensuring accurate indirect tax determination, compliance, and automation across multiple jurisdictions. The consultant will collaborate with tax, IT, and finance teams to align system functionality with business requirements and ensure smooth end-to-end tax processes.</p>\n<p>Implement and configure TRAX for indirect tax automation within SAP environments.</p>\n<p>Analyze business and tax requirements and translate them into system configurations.</p>\n<p>Collaborate with tax, finance, and IT stakeholders to ensure accurate tax determination and reporting.</p>\n<p>Manage and support TRAX-SAP integration (FI, SD, MM modules).</p>\n<p>Perform testing, troubleshooting, and issue resolution during implementation and production support.</p>\n<p>Provide user training, documentation, and continuous improvement recommendations.</p>\n<p>Support tax compliance processes and ensure system alignment with local tax regulations.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(705,7221,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"2-header\" aria-controls=\"2-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Co oferujemy<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"2-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"2-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Kontrakt B2B via Devire (120-145zł/h netto + vat)</li>\n<li>Hybryda z biura w Katowicach (3-4 dni w miesiącu)</li>\n<li>Współpraca długofalowa</li>\n<li>Współpraca z firmą o stabilnej pozycji na rynku</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(706,7222,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"2-header\" aria-controls=\"2-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Co oferujemy<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"2-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"2-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Pakiet benefitów (opieka medyczna, karta sportowa itp.),</li>\n<li>Możliwość współpracy z firmą o stabilnej pozycji na rynku,</li>\n<li>Długoterminowa współpraca.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(707,7223,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Our Purpose</h4>\n\n<p>Mastercard powers economies and empowers people in 200+ countries and territories worldwide. Together with our customers, we’re helping build a sustainable economy where everyone can prosper. We support a wide range of digital payments choices, making transactions secure, simple, smart and accessible. Our technology and innovation, partnerships and networks combine to deliver a unique set of products and services that help people, businesses and governments realize their greatest potential.</p>\n\n<h4>Title and Summary</h4>\n\n<p>Sales Development support</p>\n\n<p>Overview </p>\n\n<p>The Sales Development Team is looking for a Sales Analyst to provide cross support to our Account Managers, consistently learning and problem-solving. </p>\n\n<p>The ideal candidate is passionate about the customer experience journey, highly motivated, self-learner, intellectually curious and interacts well with other people from various areas.</p>\n\n<p>Role \nIn this position, you will: \n• Work collaboratively across multiple internal teams to support the Account Managers to address sales strategic objectives and customers needs; \n• Be responsible for preparation of the agreements and complex process of approval and signature;\n• Collaborate on strategy for customers in close cooperation with Account Managers and other teams; \n• Partner with our customers to identify business opportunities, solve problems, and deliver solutions; \n• Learn about the Mastercard strategy and solutions; \n• Participate in business conversations internally and externally; \n• Understand business and market dynamics, Mastercard’s product and service specifications and applications, and customers’ strategies and needs in order to identify opportunities and support the Sales Team to design tailored solutions which meet the customer’s needs.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(708,7224,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Truv</h4>\n\n<p>Truv is transforming the financial data industry with a secure and real-time API platform for payroll account access. Our technology streamlines income and employment verification, direct deposit switching, and more—eliminating outdated processes and unlocking greater financial opportunities. Backed by $30M from top investors like Kleiner Perkins and NYCA, we’re disrupting a $2B legacy market with cutting-edge innovation and a customer-first approach. Our leadership team brings expertise from industry giants like Apple, Carta, Venmo, MX, and Okta, driving the future of financial data access.</p>\n\n<p>What you’ll do:\n* Designing and developing ETL data pipelines.\n* Improving core data infrastructure.\n* Data modeling and hands-on development.\n* Measure data quality.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(709,7225,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Legend</h4>\n\n<p>We’re Legend. The team quietly building #1 products that make noise in the most competitive comparison markets in the world. iGaming. Sports Betting. Personal Finance.</p>\n\n<p>We exist to build better experiences. From amplified career paths to supercharged online journeys — for our people and our users, we deliver magic rooted in method. With over 500 Legends and counting, we’re helping companies turbocharge their brand growth in over 18 countries worldwide.</p>\n\n<p>If you’re looking for a company with momentum and the opportunity to progress at pace, Legend has it.</p>\n\n<p>Unlock the Legend in you.</p>\n\n<h4>The Role</h4>\n\n<p>Legend is hiring a Software Engineer in our SquadIntel team, reporting directly to our Senior Engineering Manager. You will support an in-house built, business intelligence platform that is used by hundreds of stakeholders across our whole business daily to make data driven decisions on product strategy and direction. This is a small team that moves fast to drive the success our entire product portfolio, so we’re looking for Python Backend Engineers who are excited to help Legend hyper optimise our brands and content.</p>\n\n<p>In this role, we value diverse perspectives and encourage you to apply even if you don\'t meet every qualification listed.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Your Impact:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Play a vital role in building features as part of our SquadIntel team delivering cutting edge analytics capabilities across our wide ranging portfolio of brands using a modern stack</li>\n<li>Help us build and validate Best In class internal user-facing features as part of SquadIntel</li>\n<li>Opportunity to optimise and scale a business critical product</li>\n<li>Contribute to a wider learning and knowledge sharing culture, building our engineering best practices</li>\n<li>Close collaboration with product manager and other stakeholders</li>\n<li>Development skills that follow the best practice and help maintaining a modular and scalable application</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(710,7226,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior DevOps Engineer</h4>\n\n<p>You will be part of an exceptional team responsible for solving challenging technical problems, often ones not solved before, alongside with peers with remarkable technical expertise. The solutions you build will be high impact and rolled out to our large customer base across the world.</p>\n\n<p>This role implies certain levels of autonomy; thus, we expect a candidate to be a self-motivated specialist, being able to take personal ownership of problems and drive them to solutions. At the same time, you’ll be playing a vital role in our engineering process, and you’ll be often invited for code and architectural reviews.</p>\n\n<p>We work with AWS, Kubernetes, Helm, GitHub, Github Actions, Terraform, PHP, Python, JavaScript, MySQL, MongoDB. And if you are excited to work in a dynamic environment, we would love to hear from you!</p>\n\n<p>Key responsibilities:\n* Be integral part of product development teams, and work closely with colleagues on launching new highly operable and performant systems into a cloud-native world\n* Ensure smooth operation of build and deploy workflows, production applications/workloads, and infrastructure\n* Define and implement monitoring and alerting to ensure visibility into systems’ health while avoiding alert fatigue; triage alerts, diagnose and resolve critical issues, perform root cause analysis, and remedy underlying causes\n* Identify and remediate security issues and vulnerabilities\n* Continuously improve processes and toolchain, which are in team’s ownership</p>\n\n<p>This will be for Dark Web ID, BullPhish ID (both AWS):</p>\n\n<p>Dark Web ID™ is the leading Dark Web monitoring platform in the Channel. The award-winning platform combines human and sophisticated Dark Web intelligence with search capabilities to identify, analyze and proactively monitor for an organization’s compromised or stolen employee and customer data.</p>\n\n<p>Monitoring the Dark Web for stolen credentials is critical for MSPs who want to provide comprehensive security to their customers. BullPhish ID™ complements that data with simulated phishing attacks and security awareness training campaigns to educate employees, making them the best defense against cybercrime.</p>\n\n<p>Join the Kaseya growth rocket ship and see how we are #ChangingLives !</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(711,7227,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Altium</h4>\n\n<p>Altium is transforming the way electronics are designed and built. From startups to world’s technology giants, our digital platforms give more power to PCB designers, supply chain, and manufacturing, letting them collaborate as never before.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Constant innovation has created a transformative technology, unique in its space</li>\n<li>More than 30,000 companies and 100,000 electronics engineers worldwide use Altium</li>\n<li>We are growing, debt-free, and financially strong, with the resources to become #1 in the EDA industry </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>About the role</h4>\n\n<p>We’re looking for a Sr. DevOps / Site Reliability Engineer to build and optimize scalable, resilient cloud infrastructure. You’ll partner with development teams to improve automation and CI/CD, while also owning incident response and system reliability. This includes monitoring, troubleshooting, and ensuring our services remain highly available and performant.</p>\n\n<p>‼️ <strong>Important</strong>: This is a <strong>hybrid</strong> role, which would require from you visitng our office 3 days a week. Moreover, we offer only \"umowa o pracę\" (employment of contract).</p>\n\n<h4>Key Responsibilities</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Respond to monitoring alerts, participate in incident calls, and guide them to resolution.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with software development teams to facilitate their daily operations.</li>\n<li>Design, configure, and optimize CI/CD pipelines.</li>\n<li>Build, monitor, and maintain a resilient and scalable infrastructure.</li>\n<li>Maintain documentation for processes, architectures, and configurations</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(712,7228,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Point Wild</h4>\n\n<p>Point Wild helps customers monitor, manage, and protect against the risks associated with their identities and personal information in a digital world. Backed by WndrCo, Warburg Pincus and General Catalyst, Point Wild is dedicated to creating the world’s most comprehensive portfolio of industry-leading cybersecurity solutions. Our vision is to become THE go-to resource for every cyber protection need individuals may face - today and in the future.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Join us for the ride!</p>\n\n<h4>Lat61 Mission</h4>\n\n<p>The Lat61 platform will power the next generation of cybersecurity and AI-enabled decision-making. As a <strong>Data Engineer</strong> on this team, you will help deliver:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Multi-Modal Data Ingestion:</strong> Bringing together logs, telemetry, threat intel, identity data, cryptographic assets, and third-party feeds into a unified lakehouse.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>AI Agent Enablement:</strong> Supporting Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) workflows, embeddings, and feature stores to fuel advanced AI use cases across Point Wild products.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Analytics &amp; Decision Systems:</strong> Providing real-time insights into risk posture, compliance, and security events through scalable pipelines and APIs.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Future-Proofing for Quantum:</strong> Laying the groundwork for automated remediation and transition to post-quantum cryptographic standards.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Your work won’t just be about pipelines and data models - it will directly shape how enterprises anticipate, prevent, and respond to cybersecurity risks in an era of quantum disruption.</p>\n\n<h4>About the Role:</h4>\n\n<p>We are seeking a highly skilled <strong>Data Engineer</strong> with deep experience in <strong>Databricks </strong>and modern lakehouse architectures to join the Lat61 platform team. This role is critical in designing, building, and optimizing the pipelines, data structures, and integrations that power Lat61.</p>\n\n<p>You will collaborate closely with data architects, AI engineers, and product leaders to deliver a scalable, resilient, and secure foundation for advanced analytics, machine learning, and cryptographic risk management use cases.</p>\n\n<h4>Your Day to Day:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Build and optimize data ingestion pipelines on Databricks (batch and streaming) to process structured, semi-structured, and unstructured data.</li>\n<li>Implement scalable data models and transformations leveraging Delta Lake and open data formats (Parquet, Delta).</li>\n<li>Design and manage workflows with Databricks Workflows, Airflow, or equivalent orchestration tools.</li>\n<li>Implement automated testing, lineage, and monitoring frameworks using tools like Great Expectations and Unity Catalog.</li>\n<li>Build integrations with enterprise and third-party systems via cloud APIs, Kafka/Kinesis, and connectors into Databricks.</li>\n<li>Partner with AI/ML teams to provision feature stores, integrate vector databases (Pinecone, Milvus, Weaviate), and support RAG-style architectures.</li>\n<li>Optimize Spark and SQL workloads for speed and cost efficiency across multi-cloud environments (AWS, Azure, GCP).</li>\n<li>Apply secure-by-design data engineering practices aligned with Point Wild’s cybersecurity standards and evolving post-quantum cryptographic frameworks.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Solve real customer problems. Point Wild’s point solutions allow consumers to address their immediate cyber protection needs. Our mandate is to continuously anticipate our customers’ evolving digital security needs to create best-in-class solutions aimed at keeping them safe.</h4>\n\n<h4>See your impact. We are a scrappy, nimble organization where individual contributions are needed and valued. You will see your impact every day.</h4>\n\n<h4>Accelerate your career. &nbsp;As we expand, you will have the opportunity to learn new technologies, products, and markets in a fast-paced, growth-oriented environment.</h4>\n\n<p>Most importantly, you’ll get to work with other talented people at a company where people matter. If you want to put your fingerprint on an organization and leapfrog your growth, this is the place for you.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(713,7229,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">Co będziesz robić<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Obsługa zgłoszeń użytkowników oraz bieżące wsparcie techniczne IT w obszarze oprogramowania użytkowego i licencji</li>\n<li>Wspieranie procesów instalacji, aktualizacji i wycofywania oprogramowania</li>\n<li>Monitorowanie wykorzystania licencji oraz zgłaszanie nieprawidłowości</li>\n<li>Bieżąca aktualizacja danych w narzędziach do zarządzania zasobami oprogramowania (Software Asset Management - SAM)</li>\n<li>Opracowywanie i aktualizowanie procedur oraz dokumentacji związanych z oprogramowaniem i licencjami</li>\n<li>Udział w procesach zakupowych oprogramowania oraz licencji na etapie określania zapotrzebowania i odbioru zakupionego oprogramowania.</li>\n<li>Przygotowywanie raportów dotyczących stanu i wykorzystania oprogramowania oraz licencji</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(714,7230,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><ul>\n<li>Design and develop robust backend services using Node.js and TypeScript</li>\n<li>Build secure, high-performance RESTful APIs and microservices</li>\n<li>Deploy and manage applications with AWS (Lambda, API Gateway, DynamoDB, S3, ECS)</li>\n<li>Implement CI/CD pipelines using AWS CodePipeline, CodeBuild, or similar tools</li>\n<li>Apply Test-Driven Development (TDD) and maintain high test coverage</li>\n<li>Collaborate through pair programming and cross-functional teamwork</li>\n<li>Write unit, integration, and end-to-end tests (Jest, Mocha)</li>\n<li>Contribute to system architecture and engineering best practices</li>\n<li>Troubleshoot and resolve issues across development and production environments</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(715,7231,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p><strong>THE WORK:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>Although no two days at Accenture are the same, your typical day might involve:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Assess&nbsp;MarTech/AdTech architecture and define future roadmap.</li>\n<li>Gather requirements and design AEP solutions (CDP, AJO, CJA).</li>\n<li>Build schemas, integrations, segments, and dashboards in AEP.</li>\n<li>Lead data strategies, platform evaluations, and vendor assessments.</li>\n<li>Ensure privacy compliance and deliver end-to-end marketing integrations.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This role is flexible, with most work conducted remotely. However, our ICH Europe consulting model often involves travel, with team members working closely with clients on-site, primarily across Europe. We prioritise in-person collaboration for specific engagements, learning, and relationship-building, ensuring flexibility to accommodate your work-life needs.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(716,7232,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p><strong>THE WORK:</strong></p>\n<p>Although no two days at Accenture are the same, your typical day might include:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Assess MarTech/AdTech architecture and define future roadmap.</li>\n<li>Gather requirements and design AEP solutions (CDP, AJO, CJA).</li>\n<li>Build schemas, integrations, segments, and dashboards in AEP.</li>\n<li>Lead data strategies, platform evaluations, and vendor assessments.</li>\n<li>Ensure privacy compliance and deliver end-to-end marketing integrations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span>This role is flexible, with most work conducted remotely. However, our Global Network consulting model often involves travel, with team members working closely with clients on-site, primarily across Europe. We prioritise in-person collaboration for specific engagements, learning, and relationship-building, ensuring flexibility to accommodate your work-life needs.</span></p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(717,7233,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Why project44?</h4>\n\n<p>At project44, <strong>we believe in better.</strong></p>\n\n<p>We challenge the status quo because we know a better supply chain isn’t just possible—it’s essential. Better for our customers. Better for their business. Better for the world.</p>\n\n<p>With our<strong> Decision Intelligence Platform, </strong><strong><em>Movement</em></strong><strong>,</strong> we’re redefining how global supply chains operate. By transforming fragmented logistics data into real-time, AI-powered insights, we empower companies to connect instantly, see clearly, act decisively, and automate intelligently. Our Supply Chain AI enhances visibility, drives smarter execution, and unlocks next-gen applications that keep businesses moving forward.</p>\n\n<p>Headquartered in Chicago, IL with a 2nd HQ in Bengaluru, India we are powered by a diverse global team that is tackling the toughest logistics challenges with innovation, urgency, and purpose.</p>\n\n<p>If you’re driven to solve meaningful problems, leverage AI to scale rapidly, drive impact daily, and be part of a high-performance team – we should talk.</p>\n\n<h4>Key Accountabilities:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Take ownership of customer issues and sees issues through to resolution. This includes, but is not limited to:</li>\n<li>Diagnosing, troubleshooting, and identifying solutions to reported problems</li>\n<li>Identifying potential code bugs and escalating as needed</li>\n<li>Maintaining prompt, ongoing, and accurate communications to customers and 3rd party stakeholders throughout the course of a reported issue</li>\n<li>Participating, with assistance, in customer calls as needed</li>\n<li>Gain comfort with database queries and review of data</li>\n<li>Consistent agreed-upon performance levels goals/metrics reached</li>\n<li>Lead Customer calls for issue resolution, education or escalation</li>\n<li>Take ownership of expanding internal and external knowledge base via technical notes and customer-facing articles</li>\n<li>Assist colleagues with continuing education when available</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>More about project44</h4>\n\n<p>Since 2014, project44 has been transforming the way one of the largest, most important global industries does business. As transportation and logistics continues to evolve and customer expectations around delivery become more demanding, industry technology must rise to the occasion. In just a few short years, we’ve created a digital infrastructure that eliminates the inefficiencies caused by dated technology and manual processes. Our Advanced Visibility Platform is used by the world’s leading brands to track shipments, collaborate with supply chain partners, drive operational efficiencies, and create outstanding customer experiences.</p>\n\n LI-Onsite</div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(718,7234,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Guidewire</h4>\n\n<p>Guidewire is the platform P&amp;C insurers trust to engage, innovate, and grow efficiently. We combine digital, core, analytics, and AI to deliver our platform as a cloud service. More than 540+ insurers in 40 countries, from new ventures to the largest and most complex in the world, run on Guidewire.</p>\n\n<p>As a partner to our customers, we continually evolve to enable their success. We are proud of our unparalleled implementation track record with 1600+ successful projects, supported by the largest R&amp;D team and partner ecosystem in the industry. Our Marketplace provides hundreds of applications that accelerate integration, localization, and innovation.</p>\n\n<p>For more information, please visit www.guidewire.com and follow us on Twitter: @Guidewire_PandC.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(719,7235,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior Project Manager (Intralogistics and Robotics)</h4>\n\n<p>Do you dream of deploying the perfect picking robots in warehouses all around the world? Are you ready to learn the new, exciting world of smart robots? Are you excited about joining a startup and contributing to building its future? Would you like to cooperate with top professionals in our industry?</p>\n\n<p>If your answers are mostly <strong>yes</strong>, then you should keep reading. </p>\n\n<p>At <strong>Nomagic</strong>, we’re on a mission to teach robots the real world. We’re now looking for a <strong>Senior Project Manager</strong> who’s ready to help us scale and deploy many robots in our clients’ warehouses!</p>\n\n<p>We build robots powered by AI\nWe already have them in production (this means being on call sometimes, but still!)\nWe test our code in unit tests, simulations and on real robots!\nWe’re still pretty small, so everyone has a direct impact on the final result\nWe have a very experienced engineering &amp; management team from Google, early unicorns (Criteo, Climate Corp...) &amp; top robotics companies (ABB, Softbank Robotics, Dematic)\nWe combine world-class research with top-notch engineering and apply it to solve real problems</p>\n\n<p>Some of the problems you may try to solve with us:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Manage the robot deployments project from the specification phase to the operations handover</li>\n<li>Coordinate internal resources for the flawless execution of multiple projects</li>\n<li>Track project performance, control the budget, and report to relevant stakeholders</li>\n<li>Meet with clients regularly to report on progress and discuss open items</li>\n<li>Perform risk management to minimise potential risks</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(720,7236,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Secure Global Money Transfers with Cutting-Edge Technology!</p>\n\n<p>We’re building a brand-new public API gateway to power seamless money transfers worldwide. \nAs a <b>Senior Golang Engineer </b>on our new Public Gateway team, you’ll design and implement a highly available, scalable, and secure entry point for millions of global transactions. \nThis is a greenfield project where you’ll have a direct impact on shaping the architecture, performance, and developer experience of our core platform.</p>\n\n<p>?<b> What You\'ll Do</b>\n- <b>Architect and build </b>backend microservices for a new public API gateway from the ground up\n- Design secure, reliable, and developer-friendly APIs\n- Implement rate limiting, authentication, monitoring, and resilience patterns at scale\n- <b>Collaborate</b> closely with platform, security, and product teams to define API standards\n- Optimize systems for high throughput and low latency processing\n- Take ownership across the <b>full development lifecycle</b> – from design to production operations</p>\n\n<p>? <b>Tech Stack</b>\n<b>Backend: </b>Golang\n<b>Databases:</b> MongoDB, Couchbase, distributed systems\n<b>Cloud &amp; Infrastructure:</b> AWS (EKS, Kafka, SQS), Kubernetes, Prometheus/Grafana</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(721,7237,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Rust Engineer (Greenfield project)</h4>\n\n<p>We are a team to design, develop, maintain, and improve software for various ventures projects, i.e., projects that are adjacent to our core businesses and are bootstrapped fast with a lean team. You will be actively involved in the design of various components behind scalable applications, from frontend UI to backend infrastructure.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Development activities include development, proposing architectural decisions, participating in designs, design review, code review, and implementation Identify issues and implement solutions to complex problems in the blockchain protocol</li>\n<li>Analyze and solve difficult problems across the blockchain protocol</li>\n<li>Work closely with operations and infrastructure to build high scale backend services</li>\n<li>Management of documentation of all code and functionalities implemented</li>\n<li>Work closely with DevOps and ecosystem engineers to improve tech stack for long-term engineering initiatives</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(722,7238,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Staff Software Engineer</h4>\n\n<p>Do you get excited when your software actually interacts with the physical world? Are you ready to learn the new, exciting world of smart robots? Do you feel tired of working in a big company? Would you like to cooperate with top professionals in our industry?</p>\n\n<p>If your answers are mostly <strong>yes</strong>, then you should keep reading.</p>\n\n<p>At <strong>Nomagic</strong>, we’re on a mission to teach robots the real world. We’re now looking for a <strong>Staff Software Engineer</strong> who’s ready to deep dive into the hard problems of physical manipulation (trying to match with software the millions of years of development leading to the human hand + eye) and share their software development and design expertise with our amazing team.</p>\n\n<p>Some of the problems you may try to solve with us:\n* Building modular and expandable control system for the robot actions that can be easily adapted to multiple customer use-cases\n* Use data to build heuristics for handling different categories of items\n* Detecting anomalies, e.g. using a combination of signals to determine if a robot picked more than one item at once or if one item is disassembling\n* Smart placing, tetris-like algorithms for real products\n* Interfaces and APIs for integration with warehouse management systems</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(723,7239,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Nomagic</h4>\n\n<p>At <strong>Nomagic</strong>, we’re on a mission to teach robots the real world. We’re now looking for a <strong>Senior Robotics/Software Engineer</strong>, who’s ready to deep dive into the hard problems of physical manipulation (trying to match with software the millions of years of development leading to the human hand + eye) and share his software development and design experience with our amazing team.</p>\n\n<h4>About the Role</h4>\n\n<p>We build robots powered by AI. We have them in production at scale and see their real impact on critical operations. We test our code in unit tests, simulations and on real robots! We’re still pretty small, so everyone has a direct impact on the final result.</p>\n\n<h4>Some of the problems you may try to solve with us:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Building modular and expandable control system for the robot actions that can be easily adapted to multiple customer use-cases</li>\n<li>Use data to build heuristics for handling different categories of items</li>\n<li>Detecting anomalies, e.g. using a combination of signals to determine if a robot picked more than one item at once or if one item is disassembling</li>\n<li>Building tools to quickly deploy robots at customer sites</li>\n<li>Interfaces and APIs for integration with warehouse management systems</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(724,7240,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Senior Machine Learning Research Engineer</h4>\n\n<p>Do you get excited when your ML models interact with the physical world? Are you ready to learn the new, exciting world of smart robots? Do you strive in a fast-paced and dynamic (startup) environment? Would you like to cooperate with top professionals in our industry?</p>\n\n<p>At Nomagic, we’re on a mission to teach robots the real world. We’re now looking for a Senior ML Research Engineer who’s ready to deep dive into the hard problems of understanding the real world (trying to match with software the millions of years of development leading to the human hand + eye) and share ML engineering experience and ideas with our amazing team.</p>\n\n<p>Some of the problems you may try to solve with us:\n* Develop cutting-edge deep learning approaches and apply them to the robotic handling of a vast variety of objects.\n* Increase our robots\' dexterity by collaborating with the hardware team on real-world, physical innovations.\n* Productionize novel approaches to anomaly detection (e.g. product disassembling in motion).\n* Automate data and model retraining pipelines.\n* Use data to influence company-level strategic decisions.\n* Evaluate and monitor ML models in production, detect data drifts and other reasons for degraded performance.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(725,7241,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About PredictX</h4>\n\n<p>Make a real difference at one of London’s foremost SaaS scale-ups: Be ready to pioneer the future of AI, data analytics, and technology. Step into PredictX, where we don\'t just see AI as a fashionable bandwagon but have lived and breathed AI &amp; ML in every aspect of our product for the past decade.</p>\n\n<p>As an Enterprise SaaS provider, we\'re revolutionising critical decision-making for many of the world’s largest businesses, including 3 FAANGs, seeking empowerment through our integrative AI technology and Predictive Analytics. </p>\n\n<p>We pride ourselves on our commitment to staying at the forefront of technological advancements. You\'ll be joining a team that actively explores and integrates the latest innovations to maintain our competitive edge.</p>\n\n<h4>The Role</h4>\n\n<p>As a Senior/Expert ML/Data Engineer, you will be at the forefront of our data science and machine learning initiatives, actively contributing to the evolution of our AI-powered solutions. You will be instrumental in designing, building, and maintaining our cutting-edge data infrastructure and machine learning pipelines, with a growing focus on leveraging the power of Large Language Models (LLMs) and other emerging AI technologies. </p>\n\n<p>This role demands a strong blend of data engineering prowess, machine learning understanding (including LLMs), and the ability to translate complex business needs into robust technical solutions. You will be expected to lead projects, mentor junior team members, and drive innovation within our rapidly evolving data and AI landscape. Candidates will be employed on a B2B basis.</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(726,7242,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><div>IDT is looking for an experienced <b>Lead Golang Software Engineer</b> to join the team running a global payment service for all IDT divisions.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>The service is called <b>IDTPay</b>. It supports all <b>card and bank payments</b> of B2B and B2C services and company applications with hundreds of millions of dollars in turnover.</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>IDT Pay is PCI compliant. It works with various payment processors such as Stripe and AWP, as well as other payment systems and directly with banks in the USA. And this is not the limit!</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>We are looking for someone who will play a major role in the technical and business development of the product. Your tasks will include <b>leading and expanding functionality and payment methods, providing support and improvements, and representing the team.</b>\n</div>\n<div></div>At IDT you will:: <li>Work on new features and bug fixes in the Scrum team.</li>\n<li>Take responsibility for the <b>full software development life-cycle</b>, from understanding the needs of the business through coding to deployment and maintenance.</li>\n<li><b>Collaborate with business</b> stakeholders and participate in product and sprint backlog meetings.</li>\n<li>Demonstrate your technology-agnostic positive attitude with the ability to learn and desire to implement solutions using various technologies.</li>\n<li>Work on high-performing, mission-critical, scalable, and resilient web-based applications and services.</li>\n<li>Drive technical excellence and tech debt reduction.</li></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(727,7243,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Legend</h4>\n\n<p>We’re Legend. The team quietly building #1 products that make noise in the most competitive comparison markets in the world. iGaming. Sports Betting. Personal Finance.</p>\n\n<p>We exist to build better experiences. From amplified career paths to supercharged online journeys — for our people and our users, we deliver magic rooted in method. With over 500 Legends and counting, we’re helping companies turbocharge their brand growth in over 18 countries worldwide.</p>\n\n<p>If you’re looking for a company with momentum and the opportunity to progress at pace, Legend has it.</p>\n\n<p>Unlock the Legend in you.</p>\n\n<h4>The Role</h4>\n\n<p>As an Engineering Manager at Legend, you\'ll lead a team focused on customer-facing feature development and optimisation. You\'ll manage and mentor a team of engineers, engaging in hands-on activities such as pair programming, addressing bugs and blockers, and contributing to technical design and architecture discussions. Your role will involve bridging the gap between business and technology, ensuring alignment and understanding on both sides.</p>\n\n<p>This is an exciting opportunity to be part of our flagship brand. As a pivotal squad leader within our Product Hub, you\'ll play a crucial role in driving the optimisation and scaling of our global product while contributing to a culture of knowledge sharing and growth across the business. You\'ll work with a diverse group of talented engineers and managers in a supportive environment that values your well-being and professional development. </p>\n\n<p>We value diverse perspectives and encourage you to apply even if you don\'t meet every qualification listed.</p>\n\n<h4>Your Impact:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Lead and Inspire:</strong> Effectively guide a high-performing engineering team, fostering a positive and collaborative culture while driving continuous improvement initiatives.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Solve Complex Problems:</strong> Apply strong problem-solving skills to tackle technical challenges, ensuring the successful completion of projects and initiatives.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Mentor and Guide:</strong> Provide technical guidance and mentorship to squad members, maintaining high standards and adherence to industry best practices.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Facilitate Collaboration:</strong> Work closely with cross-functional teams—including product management, content, design, SEO, and delivery—to ensure alignment and effective communication.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Promote Growth:</strong> Cultivate a culture of learning and development, supporting the professional growth of team members through ongoing training, mentorship, and skill-building opportunities.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(728,7244,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Veeva Systems is a mission-driven organization and pioneer in industry cloud, helping life sciences companies bring therapies to patients faster. As one of the fastest-growing SaaS companies in history, we surpassed $2B in revenue in our last fiscal year with extensive growth potential ahead.</p>\n\n<p>At the heart of Veeva are our values: Do the Right Thing, Customer Success, Employee Success, and Speed. We\'re not just any public company – we made history in 2021 by becoming a <a href=\"https://medium.com/@peter.gassner/public-benefit-corporation-pbc-486e1e9508a6\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">public benefit corporation</a> (PBC), legally bound to balancing the interests of customers, employees, society, and investors.</p>\n\n<p>As a <a href=\"https://medium.com/@peter.gassner/work-anywhere-is-about-trusting-and-empowering-employees-ef1beba56590\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Work Anywhere</a> company, we support your flexibility to work from home or in the office, so you can thrive in your ideal environment.</p>\n\n<p>Join us in <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TaPSP8cCSKY&amp;ab_channel=Forbes\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">transforming the life sciences industry</a>, committed to making a positive impact on its customers, employees, and communities.</p>\n\n<h4>The Role</h4>\n\n<p>We are seeking a talented Product Support Engineer to join our Product Support team. You will be part of a young and exciting company that is recognized as the market leader in the SaaS space with our Industry Cloud for Life Sciences.</p>\n\n<p>Our Product Support team is growing quickly in Poland and Hungary. As a member of the team, you will be tasked with supporting our customers and internal stakeholders, such as our Consulting and Sales Engineering teams. You will work closely with the Development and QA teams to diagnose, troubleshoot, and resolve complex issues. You will need to learn and adapt quickly, be persistent, and demonstrate “out-of-the-box” thinking.</p>\n\n<p>This is a full-time job with optional on-call responsibilities for weekend coverage. You must be based and eligible for employment in Poland, as Veeva does not anticipate providing support for an employment visa/permit process. You are applying for a Contract of Employment with Veeva Systems Poland sp. z o.o. There is no possibility for this role to be delivered through a business-to-business contract. Business hours are from 9 to 18, which include a one-hour unpaid lunch break.</p>\n\n<p>What You\'ll Do:\n* Provide global support covering all issues related to the Veeva product suite\n* Learn everything about our software and use that knowledge to ensure client success\n* Support the client administrators across multiple organizations\n* Troubleshoot critical production issues affecting end-users, including system unavailability and data integrity issues\n* Handle inquiries regarding all technical issues and information requests on application capabilities, navigation, installation, or configuration\n* Provide coordinated support for getting new releases and configuration changes into production\n* Gather information for analysis, carry out the necessary research, set up test environments, replicate issues locally, and propose resolutions or workarounds\n* Be a client-facing representative of the Development and Product teams\n* Document new processes and keep existing documentation and tools up to date as the environment changes\n* Interface with engineering, product management, and professional services when necessary\n* Attend daily meetings and provide status updates</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(729,7245,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Us:</h4>\n\n<p>Both Printify and Printful are pioneering production on-demand companies and platforms established in Latvia but with a global customer base.</p>\n\n<p>Printify is bringing the dream of financial freedom and business ownership to the world by connecting e-commerce entrepreneurs with over 100 print-on-demand facilities around the globe.</p>\n\n<p>Printful has built world-class in-house production facilities and helps people to build their brands, empowering thousands of businesses—including iconic names like Coca-Cola and MTV.</p>\n\n<p>Our team is at the heart of our success. You’ll be part of a culture where everyone is respected, included, and encouraged to grow. We value continuous learning, uphold a high work ethic, and have fun along the way.</p>\n\n<h4>About The Role</h4>\n\n<p>Product managers at Printul &amp; Printify are the essential drivers for our product vision and strategy and aim to deliver high-value solutions for both merchants &amp; print providers. Product managers connect the technical and business worlds. They work closely with engineers, designers, data scientists, researchers, and business leaders to build products and guide them throughout the execution cycle, building, positioning, and tailoring our solutions to our users.</p>\n\n<h4>Your Daily Tasks will Entail:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Product Development:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Develop a strategic roadmap for the team that aligns with the company\'s overall goals and product vision.</li>\n<li>Lead the end-to-end product development lifecycle, from idea generation to launch, focusing on features related to new merchant onboarding and activation.</li>\n<li>Collaborate closely with engineering and data teams to translate requirements into clear technical specifications and ensure timely project delivery.</li>\n<li>Engage with stakeholders to understand user needs, market dynamics, and competitive trends, shaping the product strategy accordingly.</li>\n<li>Iterate continuously on product features based on user feedback, usability tests, and data analysis to enhance onboarding and retention metrics.</li>\n<li>Prioritize feature enhancements and bug fixes considering their impact and resource availability.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Data Analysis:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Utilize data-driven insights to identify opportunities for optimizing onboarding and retention processes.</li>\n<li>Define key performance indicators (KPIs) and establish tracking mechanisms to evaluate the success of product initiatives.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>User Research:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Conduct user research through surveys, interviews, and usability studies to validate product hypotheses and gather actionable feedback.</li>\n<li>Advocate for user-centricity by integrating research findings into product decisions and enhancements.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Cross-functional Collaboration:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Work collaboratively with teams across departments like design, marketing, customer support, and sales to ensure cohesive alignment and successful product launches.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Documentation and Training:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Create comprehensive documentation, including user guides and internal training materials, to facilitate effective onboarding of new users and team members.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Market Analysis:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Monitor industry trends and competitor strategies related to onboarding and retention solutions to inform product differentiation and innovation efforts.</li>\n<li>Stay informed about regulatory requirements and compliance standards affecting product development.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Feedback Management:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Establish efficient feedback channels, such as customer feedback loops and support systems, to gather actionable insights for product improvement.</li>\n<li>Implement processes for prioritizing and addressing customer feedback in product updates.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Team Leadership:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Demonstrate leadership by fostering a customer-centric culture and promoting continuous improvement within the team.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(730,7246,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>About Us:</h4>\n\n<p>Both Printify and Printful are pioneering production on-demand companies and platforms established in Latvia but with a global customer base.</p>\n\n<p>Printify is bringing the dream of financial freedom and business ownership to the world by connecting e-commerce entrepreneurs with over 100 print-on-demand facilities around the globe.</p>\n\n<p>Printful has built world-class in-house production facilities and helps people to build their brands, empowering thousands of businesses—including iconic names like Coca-Cola and MTV.</p>\n\n<p>Our team is at the heart of our success. You’ll be part of a culture where everyone is respected, included, and encouraged to grow. We value continuous learning, uphold a high work ethic, and have fun along the way.</p>\n\n<h4>About The Role</h4>\n\n<p>As the Product Group Manager for Home&amp;Living or Apparel, you will be the commercial leader of this product category group, overseeing its strategic direction and driving growth across multiple sales channels and merchant segments. </p>\n\n<p>You will lead a team of experienced Category Managers, empowering them and setting the direction to drive the category performance and expand on market opportunities. </p>\n\n<p>In this role, you will be responsible for defining and executing the strategic vision for the Home&amp;Living or Apparel group, ensuring a balanced approach between core portfolio management and strategic new selections to maximize sales, profitability, and market positioning. </p>\n\n<p>Together with your team, you will ensure that our assortment features both bestselling products and innovative printing methods at competitive pricing, strengthening our market leadership. You will work closely with cross-functional teams—including product, operations, and finance—to execute key strategic initiatives.</p>\n\n<h4>Your Daily Tasks will Entail:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Setting Home&amp;Living/Apparel group strategic direction; developing and driving initiatives in alignment with company objectives</li>\n<li>Follow, analyze, and report Home&amp;Living/Apparel group results against KPIs and make data-driven decisions based on the analysis</li>\n<li>Leading a team of product category managers and associates, fostering a collaborative and performance-driven culture</li>\n<li>Proactively, independently, and frequently identify revenue opportunities and drive them to execution without the need for explicit direction</li>\n<li>Manage and refine the existing product catalog to ensure we maintain our market leadership; guarantee the competitiveness and quality of our products meet customer expectations</li>\n<li>Lead the creation and execution of new Home&amp;Living/Apparel product roadmap; ensure alignment with e-commerce trends, merchant needs and business objectives to maximize revenue</li>\n<li>Incorporate data, research, and market analysis to inform stakeholders about new product and initiative roadmap </li>\n<li>Collaborate with sourcing, onboarding, design and in-house development teams to bring new products to the catalogs</li>\n<li>Work closely with Sales and Marketing teams to develop and execute go-to-market strategies, maximizing revenue potential across core and new product selections</li>\n<li>Collaborate with product teams to improve new merchant onboarding journey, product discoverability in the catalog and improve product creation experience</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(731,7247,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Keyloop bridges the gap between dealers, manufacturers, technology suppliers and car buyers.</h4>\n\n<p>We empower car dealers and manufacturers to fully embrace digital transformation. How? By creating innovative technology that makes selling cars better for our customers, and buying and owning cars better for theirs.\nWe use cutting-edge technology to link our clients’ systems, departments and sites. We provide an open technology platform that’s shaping the industry for the future. We use data to help clients become more efficient, increase profitability and give more customers an amazing experience. Want to be part of it?</p>\n\n<h4>Purpose of Role:</h4>\n\n<p>The purpose of this role is to maintain the existing capabilities and implement new and enhanced capabilities for the Vehicle Hub software as a service platform through close collaboration with the Engineering and Product teams. This includes the development of the full software stack, collaboration with and support of other colleagues, and contributing to the ongoing operations and maintenance of the platform to keep it secure, stable and supported.\nAs a Senior Software Engineer the individual will take ownership of entire problem spaces and continually seek to push the Vehicle Hub platform forwards, aligned to our strategic product goals.</p>\n\n<h4>Key Responsibilities:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Development - This role will directly contribute to our platform growth ambitions. This role will work alongside the other engineers in expanding the feature-set of the platform.</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Enhance, refactor and maintain our existing software as a service platform.</li>\n<li>Determine a suitable approach for an identified problem space.</li>\n<li>Ensure the solution meets the acceptance criteria outlined for that problem space.</li>\n<li>Implement effective test coverage for the solution to ensure it behaves as expected.</li>\n<li>Conduct code reviews for pull requests.</li>\n<li>Be accountable for the solutions you implement.</li>\n<li>Manage development tasks from initial assignment through to release.</li>\n<li>Assist with the grooming of the backlog and the continual refinement of issues.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Support - As a member of the Engineering Team this role will provide ongoing support to our clients and the wider company to preserve the value of the platform.</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Build and maintain a personal knowledge base of the system’s functionality, data sources, data structures.</li>\n<li>Act as a technical expert to support colleagues.</li>\n<li>Answer technical queries posed by our other teams.</li>\n<li>Provide day-to-day support to the Vehicle Hub Engineering Team through collaboration and to help resolve development blocks.</li>\n<li>Identify enhancement opportunities in the system; whether because of technical debt, poor data quality, a poor or inconsistent user experience or through advancements in technology.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Platform - This role will contribute to the ongoing operations and maintenance of the Vehicle Hub platform to keep it secure, stable and supported.</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Update our software dependencies as required, including language and framework upgrades.</li>\n<li>Identify when our test coverage is lacking and enhance as appropriate.</li>\n<li>Maintain, update and build our application containers.</li>\n<li>Deploy to our non-production and production environments through our deployment process.</li>\n<li>Build and maintain a personal knowledge base of our infrastructure and associated technologies.</li>\n<li>Monitor our infrastructure to ensure it remains available and performant.</li>\n<li>Provide support to resolve infrastructure issues.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(732,7248,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Keyloop bridges the gap between dealers, manufacturers, technology suppliers and car buyers.</h4>\n\n<p>We empower car dealers and manufacturers to fully embrace digital transformation. How? By creating innovative technology that makes selling cars better for our customers, and buying and owning cars better for theirs. </p>\n\n<p>We use cutting-edge technology to link our clients’ systems, departments and sites. We provide an open technology platform that’s shaping the industry for the future. We use data to help clients become more efficient, increase profitability and give more customers an amazing experience. Want to be part of it?</p>\n\n<p>The purpose of this role is to maintain the existing capabilities and implement new and enhanced capabilities for the Vehicle Hub software as a service platform through close collaboration with the Engineering and Product teams. This includes the development of the full software stack, collaboration with and support of other colleagues, and contributing to the ongoing operations and maintenance of the platform to keep it secure, stable and supported.</p>\n\n<p>As a Software Engineer the individual will take ownership of specific problem spaces and continually seek to push the Vehicle Hub platform forwards, aligned to our strategic product goals.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Development - This role will directly contribute to our platform growth ambitions. This role will work alongside the other engineers in expanding the feature-set of the platform.</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Enhance, refactor and maintain our existing software as a service platform.</li>\n<li>Determine a suitable approach for an identified problem space.</li>\n<li>Ensure the solution meets the acceptance criteria outlined for that problem space.</li>\n<li>Implement effective test coverage for the solution to ensure it behaves as expected.</li>\n<li>Conduct code reviews for pull requests.</li>\n<li>Be accountable for the solutions you implement.</li>\n<li>Manage development tasks from initial assignment through to release.</li>\n<li>Assist with the grooming of the backlog and the continual refinement of issues.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Support - As a member of the Engineering Team this role will provide ongoing support to our clients and the wider company to preserve the value of the platform.</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Build and maintain a personal knowledge base of the system’s functionality, data sources, data structures.</li>\n<li>Act as a technical expert to support colleagues.</li>\n<li>Answer technical queries posed by our other teams.</li>\n<li>Provide day-to-day support to the Vehicle Hub Engineering Team through collaboration and to help resolve development blocks.</li>\n<li>Identify enhancement opportunities in the system; whether because of technical debt, poor data quality, a poor or inconsistent user experience or through advancements in technology.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Platform - This role will contribute to the ongoing operations and maintenance of the Vehicle Hub platform to keep it secure, stable and supported.</strong>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Update our software dependencies as required, including language and framework upgrades.</li>\n<li>Identify when our test coverage is lacking and enhance as appropriate.</li>\n<li>Maintain, update and build our application containers.</li>\n<li>Deploy to our non-production and production environments through our deployment process.</li>\n<li>Build and maintain a personal knowledge base of our infrastructure and associated technologies.</li>\n<li>Monitor our infrastructure to ensure it remains available and performant.</li>\n<li>Provide support to resolve infrastructure issues.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(733,7249,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Join Fresha, the leading marketplace platform transforming the beauty and wellness industry globally. With over 120,000 businesses and 450,000 stylists trusting our platform, we\'ve powered over 1 billion appointments worldwide. Fresha empowers businesses with an all-in-one platform for bookings, point-of-sale, marketing, and more, while connecting consumers to local services.</p>\n\n Your Impact as a Backend Engineer \n\n<p>Are you ready to make a significant impact in a fast-paced, autonomous environment? We\'re seeking an exceptional Backend Engineer to join our cross-functional product team in Warsaw.</p>\n\n<h4>What You\'ll Do:</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Collaborate closely with Product, Design, Frontend, Infrastructure, and Mobile engineers to take features from discovery to rollout and beyond.</li>\n<li>Be responsible for features from discovery to observability: technical design, implementation, testing, and rollout.</li>\n<li>Design, build, and maintain efficient, scalable, and reliable Ruby/Elixir code.</li>\n<li>Work with a polyglot stack (Ruby, Elixir, GraphQL, TypeScript, gRPC) and modern messaging systems (Kafka).</li>\n<li>Operate within a Kubernetes-driven environment as we continue moving to a microservice architecture.</li>\n<li>Embrace Domain-Driven Design to build high-quality, impactful products from inception to delivery.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(734,7250,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Location:</h4>\n\n<p>Warsaw, Poland - Hybrid (4 days on-site / 1 day remote)</p>\n\n<h4>Contract:</h4>\n\n<p>B2B · 25-40 k PLN net / month + RSUs</p>\n\n<h4>Why Fresha &amp; Why Now?</h4>\n\n<p>Fresha is re-imagining how the global beauty and wellness industry runs. 120k+ businesses, 450k+ professionals, millions of clients, and 1 billion+ appointments already rely on our platform for everything from bookings to payments.</p>\n\n<p>Join us at a moment of rapid scale - your work will surface on screens around the world within days, not quarters.</p>\n\n<h4>What You’ll Do</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Own and evolve our <strong>core booking &amp; scheduling engine</strong> - the heartbeat of Fresha - ensuring it scales smoothly and delivers seamless experiences for millions.</li>\n<li>Design, build, and ship new user-facing features in <strong>React + TypeScript</strong>, reaching millions of professionals and clients.</li>\n<li>Own features end-to-end: discovery, technical design, implementation, testing, rollout, and observability.</li>\n<li>Tap into (and extend) our <strong>Design System</strong> to ship polished UI quickly while raising the bar for consistency.</li>\n<li>Write robust automated tests (Cypress, Jest, React Testing Library) and keep the CI/CD pipeline green.</li>\n<li>Partner closely with Product, Design, Backend, Infrastructure, and Mobile engineers to take features from discovery to rollout and beyond.</li>\n<li>Accelerate with AI: harness AI agents, LLM-powered coding tools, and access to a wide range of AI tools (e.g., chatbots, dev assistants). </li>\n<li>Curious about backend, DevOps, or mobile? Great - we’ll support you in exploring any part of the stack.</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(735,7251,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><h4>Why Altium?</h4>\n\n<p>Altium is transforming the way electronics are designed and built. From startups to world’s technology giants, our digital platforms give more power to PCB designers, supply chain, and manufacturing, letting them collaborate as never before.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Constant innovation has created a transformative technology, unique in its space</li>\n<li>More than 30,000 companies and 100,000 electronics engineers worldwide use Altium</li>\n<li>We are growing, debt-free, and financially strong, with the resources to become #1 in the EDA industry </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Why Altium 365 Software Engineering?</h4>\n\n<p>Build the cloud platform that’s transforming electronics design. Altium 365 for cloud lets design engineers communicate, collaborate and bring their ideas to market more efficiently than any platform in the industry. These are some of the R&amp;D Software Engineering contributions you might make to Altium 365:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Building new cloud-native applications and scalable infrastructure</li>\n<li>Utilizing AI and ML to power advanced search capabilities</li>\n<li>Large-scale data processing; data modeling; holistic, intent-based API design</li>\n<li>Stateful and stateless servers, relational databases, ORM frameworks</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Altium offers the opportunity to conceive and build new product features for electronics engineers, and add your own ideas to the world’s most collaborative and efficient electronics design platform.</p>\n\n<h4>About the Role</h4>\n\n<p>As a Senior Backend Developer, your primary role will be product development for complex cloud applications with the Altium 365 R&amp;D team.</p>\n\n<h4>A Day in the Life of Our Senior Backend Developer</h4>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Work with a tech stack that includes Java and .NET Core, AWS, multi-tenant architecture, and distributed high-load systems</li>\n<li>Handle tech challenges different from most others on the market, a mixture of complex engineering software, microelectronics and cloud services</li>\n<li>Add to the team’s expertise through collaboration and sharing knowledge</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(736,7252,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>We are currently looking for an experienced and motivated Software Engineer (SAP BTP) to join our Product team. You will be responsible for developing modern solutions based on SAP S/4HANA and SAP BTP for the general ledger system, in line with business, architectural, technical, and security requirements.</p>\n<p><strong>How you will get the job done</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>analyzing integration needs from functional teams or business analysts</li>\n<li>designing and implementing iFlows using SAP BTP Integration Suite</li>\n<li>building and consuming APIs for SAP/non-SAP integration</li>\n<li>implementing message mapping, transformation (XSLT/Groovy), routing, alerting, logging, and retry logicdeveloping and maintaining CI/CD pipelines for integration artifacts</li>\n<li>documenting integration flows, architecture, APIs, and configurations</li>\n<li>monitoring, troubleshooting, and optimizing performance on SAP BTP</li>\n<li>resolving failed message flows and connectivity issues</li>\n<li>enhancing existing integrations for improved performance and reliability</li>\n<li>contributing to architectural and process improvement discussions</li>\n<li>staying current with the SAP BTP roadmap and new services</li>\n<li>demonstrating strong problem-solving skills in SAP general ledger implementations</li>\n<li>being proficient in SAP S/4HANA, SAP BTP, Datasphere, SAP RISE, and finance modules (FI-GL, FI, CO, AA)</li>\n<li>ensuring compliance with security and regulatory standards</li>\n<li>communicating effectively with stakeholders to align solutions with business needs</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(737,7253,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>About the project</p>\n<p>Join a strategic and high-impact initiative focused on transforming the Loan Analytics platform for one of the world\'s leading financial institutions. The program leverages modern technologies and automation to optimize risk forecasting, portfolio analytics, and financing systems. You\'ll work closely with global teams on a system that powers decision-making in the financial markets—from underwriting to real-time monitoring.</p>\n<p>About the team</p>\n<p>You\'ll be part of a cross-functional, international team operating at the intersection of finance and technology. The team includes senior engineers, business analysts, product owners, and QA specialists working on cutting-edge solutions in capital markets and risk technology. This is a fast-paced, collaborative environment where innovation and ownership are highly valued.</p>\n<p>Design, develop, and maintain scalable automated testing frameworks using Java</p>\n<p>Own the test automation strategy and lead its implementation across the team</p>\n<p>Review architecture, code, and test cases for quality assurance</p>\n<p>Drive best practices in automation, performance and system testing</p>\n<p>Testing Execution</p>\n<p>Create and execute test cases based on functional and business requirements</p>\n<p>Troubleshoot and resolve QA environment issues</p>\n<p>Analyze root causes and proactively mitigate issues</p>\n<p>Work with globally distributed teams to ensure high-quality deliveries</p>\n<p>Domain Expertise</p>\n<p>Bring insights from financial markets, especially in areas like loans, derivatives, FX, fixed income</p>\n<p>Collaborate with stakeholders across business and tech units</p>\n<p>Support testing of real-time trading and electronic platforms</p></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(738,7254,'<h3 class=\"text-c20\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"w-full text-left flex items-center\" id=\"1-header\" aria-controls=\"1-panel\" aria-expanded=\"true\">What you will do<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" width=\"20\" class=\"ml-auto\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11.47 7.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0l7.5 7.5a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L12 9.31l-6.97 6.97a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l7.5-7.5z\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\"></path></svg></button></h3><section id=\"1-panel\" aria-labelledby=\"1-header\" class=\"font-normal\"><div class=\"content list--check mt-6 -mb-6\"><p>Project is related to regulatory reporting for one of Clients from Investment Banking area. We are looking for professional QA Automation eager to work with legacy regression tests and converting these to a new automation framework as part of companywide initiative, with a long-term view to enhance with Continuous Integration automated test solution for mobile and web based applications.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Take ownership of designing and developing automated tests</li>\n<li>Contribute to technology solutions that address business challenges and reinforce our leadership in digital financial services</li>\n<li>Leverage a strong background in test automation to enhance quality and efficiency</li>\n<li>Share expertise in quality assurance and process optimization with the team</li>\n<li>Support the evolution and expansion of the Testing Automation Framework</li>\n<li>Engage in all phases of the software development lifecycle: requirements, architecture, design, development, testing, and deployment</li>\n<li>Participate in Agile project planning, including effort estimation and process improvement initiatives</li>\n<li>Mentor and support team members to foster growth and collaboration</li>\n<li>Demonstrate flexibility by performing manual testing when necessar</li>\n</ul></div></section>','',NULL,NULL),(739,7255,'ITDS Business Consultants is involved in many various, innovative and professional IT projects for international companies in the financial industry in Europe. We offer an environment for professional, ambitious, and driven people.','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">Minimum 2 years of experience in system analysis and IT solution design, preferably within banking or financial sectors.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Strong knowledge of SQL and experience working with databases.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Background in the banking or financial industry.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Proven experience in business and technical analysis, as well as solution modeling.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Familiarity with REST API design principles.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Ability to learn quickly and adapt to new technologies.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Excellent attention to detail, organizational skills, and independence.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Strong teamwork and communication skills with business and technical stakeholders.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Experience using modeling tools such as Enterprise Architect.</li>',NULL,NULL),(740,7256,'ITDS Business Consultants is involved in many various, innovative and professional IT projects for international companies in the financial industry in Europe. We offer an environment for professional, ambitious, and driven people.','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">5+ years of professional experience in data engineering or related fields</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Strong proficiency in Python and Shell scripting</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Solid hands-on experience with Linux, networking, and performance troubleshooting</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Expertise in building and managing data pipelines with ETL, time-series data handling (SQL, Pandas)</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Practical knowledge of containers and orchestration tools, including Airflow, ECS, or EKS exposure</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Familiarity with observability/metrics stacks such as Grafana, Prometheus, and ELK</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Experience with AWS cloud services, especially AWS S3, ECS, EKS, or similar platforms</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Ownership mindset, problem-solving drive, and eagerness to work closely with trading teams</li>',NULL,NULL),(741,7257,'☁️ Chmura: Google Cloud Platform (mile widziane także AWS, Azure)','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">Min. 5 lat doświadczenia w Infrastructure/ DevOps / administracji systemami / SRE, a także doświadczenie w prowadzeniu zespołu w roli lidera.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Doświadczenie w chmurze – najlepiej w Google Cloud Platform, ale jeśli znasz AWS lub Azure, też się odnajdziesz.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Osoba, która potrafi zaprojektować, utrzymać i rozwijać środowiska serwerowe, sieciowe i systemowe</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Pasja w automatyzacji – z praktyką w Terraform / Ansible (IaC) i pasją do upraszczania tego, co inni robią ręcznie.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Techniczny lider, który potrafi wyznaczać kierunki, wspierać zespół, rozwijać kompetencje i dbać o jakość każdego wdrożenia.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Entuzjasta CI/CD i konteneryzacji – znającego GitHub Actions, Jenkins, ArgoCD, Docker, Kubernetes, który potrafi optymalizować pipeline’y i środowiska produkcyjne.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Osoba z mindsetem proaktywności i nowoczesności – takiej, która reaguje, dba o bezpieczeństwo, skalowalność i chętnie testuje narzędzia AI ?</li>',NULL,NULL),(742,7258,'Creating an inspiring place to thrive for the talented, we use their expertise and courage to introduce the technology of the future into your business. - This is the foundation of Mindbox and the goal of our business and technology journey. We operate and develop in four areas:','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">Proactive and results-driven approach to project delivery.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Strong communication skills; able to influence discussions and drive progress.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Confident in technical conversations and quick to adapt to new technologies.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Skilled at presenting and engaging stakeholders in meaningful discussions.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Hands-on experience with IAM and modern authentication protocols.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Knowledge of Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) and Passwordless Authentication.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Familiarity with JIRA and Confluence to support project tracking and collaboration.</li>',NULL,NULL),(743,7259,'W PKO Banku Polskim sami tworzymy, rozwijamy oraz zabezpieczamy nasze systemy i produkty. Z rozmachem korzystamy z innowacyjnych rozwiązań oraz nowoczesnych technologii. Z sukcesem wdrożyliśmy blockchain i sztuczną inteligencję. To nie wszystko! Wspieramy startupy w ich drodze do sukcesu! Od lat wyznaczamy standardy na rynku polskiej bankowości. Aby utrzymać pozycję lidera, zatrudniamy najlepszych specjalistów i ekspertów. Dołącz do nas, żeby wspólnie tworzyć PKO Bank Przyszłości.','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">masz co najmniej 4-letnie doświadczenie komercyjne w programowaniu w języku Java (wersja 11 lub wyższa),</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">umiejętnie stosujesz dobre praktyki programowania obiektowego i wzorce projektowe (a gdy tego wymaga sytuacja, umiejętnie ich nie stosujesz),</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">wiesz z praktyki, jakie są zalety i wady architektury mikroserwisów,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">dobrze znasz framework Spring Boot,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">posiadasz doświadczenie w zastosowaniach SOAP, REST, JMS,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">znasz relacyjne bazy danych i SQL,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">sprawnie wykorzystujesz narzędzia: Git, Maven,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">masz wykształcenie wyższe informatyczne lub pokrewne,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">potrafisz pracować zespołowo.</li>',NULL,NULL),(744,7260,'W PKO Banku Polskim sami tworzymy, rozwijamy oraz zabezpieczamy nasze systemy i produkty. Z rozmachem korzystamy z innowacyjnych rozwiązań oraz nowoczesnych technologii. Z sukcesem wdrożyliśmy blockchain i sztuczną inteligencję. To nie wszystko! Wspieramy startupy w ich drodze do sukcesu! Od lat wyznaczamy standardy na rynku polskiej bankowości. Aby utrzymać pozycję lidera, zatrudniamy najlepszych specjalistów i ekspertów. Dołącz do nas, żeby wspólnie tworzyć PKO Bank Przyszłości.','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">studiujesz lub masz ukończone studia na kierunku informatyka, matematyka, ekonomia lub pokrewnym,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">mile widziany drugi kierunek studiów z obszaru finansów, rachunkowości lub kontrolingu finansowego,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">interesuje Cię praca z danymi,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">znasz Python, SQL,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">chcesz się rozwijać w obszarze uczenia maszynowego,</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">interesuje Cię obszar wykrywania i zapobiegania nadużyciom.</li>',NULL,NULL),(745,7261,'Novocure is a global publicly-traded commercial-stage oncology company developing a profoundly different cancer treatment therapy called tumor treating fields (TTFields) for patients with solid tumors. TTFields therapy is a non-invasive, novel, antimitotic treatment modality which utilizes proprietary technology attempting to slow or reverse tumor progression by inducing tumor cell death. Novocure\'s commercialized product, Optune, is approved for the treatment of adult patients with glioblastoma (GBM) in the USA, Europe and Israel. Novocure has ongoing or completed clinical trials and is further expanding its efforts into several other solid tumor indications - non-small cell lung cancer, pancreatic cancer and other types of solid cancers.','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">5+ years of QA experience including product functional testing</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Proven ability to manage other team members</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Technical training or equivalent experience</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">V&amp;V for medical device experience, or V&amp;V in a related field with similar controls</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Highly proficient with measuring instruments (e.g. calipers, DMM, oscilloscope, etc.)</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Experience with black-box software testing is a plus</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Professional verbal and written communication skills in English</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Organized and strong attention to detail, highly motivated, self-learner, and responsible</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Able to work in a team environment and execute responsibilities with minimal direct supervision</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Able to balance completion of assigned tasks with supporting requests and questions from other team members</li>',NULL,NULL),(746,7262,'Working at T-Mobile’s T Hub will offer you an unique and highly rewarding experience on IT market. As a leader in the telecommunications industry, T-Mobile not only provides a platform to hone your technical skills but also empowers you to be a catalyst for innovation. You\'ll have the opportunity to work at the forefront of cutting-edge technologies, from 5G to IoT and AI, shaping the future of connectivity. Our commitment to fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace means you\'ll collaborate with a wide range of talented professionals, learning and growing together. T-Mobile encourages a culture of continuous learning and development, offering mentorship and support to help you thrive in your career.','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">Background in Security domain is essential (Security literacy, security tooling, security processes, etc)</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Knowledge of DT\'s Security organization setup is an advantage</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Knowledge and experience with PSA process is an advantage</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Highly developed sense of ownership and accountability for work</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Ability to work independently and to drive security topics based on previously agreed objectives</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Excellent communication skills with a solid ability in both written and verbal presentation (in English)</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Strategic problem solver with the ability to define and evaluate alternatives, breaking high-level goals into specific project tasks</li>',NULL,NULL),(747,7263,'Jesteśmy ITHOUSE i od ponad 7 lat łączymy specjalistów IT z projektami, które naprawdę mają znaczenie i zmieniają sposób, w jaki Polacy korzystają z technologii na co dzień.','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">Minimum 2-letnie doświadczenie w projektowaniu architektury rozwiązań Big Data;</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Doświadczenie w roli Architekta IT w projektach realizowanych metodyką zwinną;</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Doświadczenie w tworzeniu dokumentacji projektów systemów informatycznych;</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Doświadczenie we wdrażaniu projektów Big Data z wykorzystaniem stosu technologicznego Hadoop lub równoważnego;</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Znajomość narzędzi: JIRA, Confluence oraz Enterprise Architect;</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Doświadczenie z Hadoop, bazami relacyjnymi i NoSQL, narzędziami analitycznymi;</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Znajomość zagadnień DevOps w obszarze Big Data;</li>',NULL,NULL),(748,7264,'Główne zadania:','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">Doświadczenie w wsparciu użytkowników (Windows, M365), podstawy sieci, administrowanie kontami i licencjami, skłonność do porządkowania i dokumentowania.</li>',NULL,NULL),(749,7265,'Założona w Brnie, Czechy, w 2004 roku, od pierwszego dnia współpracujemy z liderami branży IT na całym świecie. Jesteśmy doświadczoną firmą o głębokiej wiedzy w zakresie tworzenia wysoko wydajnych zespołów projektowych IT.','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">Minimum 3 lata doświadczenia zawodowego na stanowisku PMO lub w obszarach pokrewnych (koordynacja projektów, wsparcie operacyjne, zarządzanie budżetem)</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Znajomość pakietu MS Office, w szczególności Excel (praca z arkuszami, raportowanie, analiza danych)</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Znajomość języka angielskiego na poziomie co najmniej komunikatywnym (współpraca z międzynarodowym zespołem)</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Umiejętność organizacji pracy własnej i zarządzania wieloma zadaniami równolegle</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Dokładność, skrupulatność i odpowiedzialność w zakresie finansów oraz dokumentacji projektowej</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Zdolność do współpracy z różnymi interesariuszami (20+ osób) w ramach dużego departamentu</li>',NULL,NULL),(750,7266,'This is your chance to be at the forefront of mobile gaming, working on a project with a major IP to deliver AAA-quality experiences. If you\'re ready to unleash your technical prowess and impact the future of mobile gaming, we\'re eager to welcome you aboard. Let your creativity soar and shape the gaming world with us!','<li class=\"lxul5ps\">Proficiency in C# programming language is essential.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">At least 7 years of experience in professional software development.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Solid experience in network programming.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">An understanding of high performance, low latency and high availability.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Deep knowledge of multithreading and concurrency</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Hands-on experience with AWS public cloud.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Familiarity with messaging infrastructure like Kafka, or similar technologies.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">In-depth knowledge of SQL, NoSQL databases, and caching technologies (e.g., Redis).</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Practical experience in using Docker and Kubernetes.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to effectively interact with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Fluency in Polish and English enabling effective collaboration across teams.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Clear Communication: Ability to simplify and articulate complex technical concepts for diverse audiences (designers, developers).</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Active Listening: Strong listening skills to understand feedback, ideas, and concerns from team members and stakeholders.</li><li class=\"lxul5ps\">Presentation Skills: Comfortable presenting ideas and updates in a clear, structur